ils":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-04-01T11:52:15\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :   true (One or more child tests must be true. (OR))\nTest            :     true (Audit - IPSec Driver - Failure only)\nTest            :     false (Audit - IPSec Driver - Success and Failure)\n"},{"security_override_guidance":"","group_title":"SRG-OS-000471-GPOS-00215","third_party_tools":"","rule_title":"The system must be configured to audit System - Other System Events successes.","rule_id":"SV-253331r991579","weight":"10.0","stig_uuid":"677F401D-722B-1014-B949-B81E5231A214","ccis":["CCI-000172"],"ia_controls":"","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-OS-000471-GPOS-00215","id":"V-253331"},"group_id":"V-253331","mitigations":"","documentable":"false","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Windows Settings &gt;&gt; Security Settings &gt;&gt; Advanced Audit Policy Configuration &gt;&gt; System Audit Policies &gt;&gt; System &gt;&gt; \"Audit Other System Events\" with \"Success\" selected.","rule_id_src":"SV-253331r991579_rule","status":"open","group_id_src":"V-253331","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windows11:def:253331","href":"U_MS_Windows_11_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV16-oval.xml"},"reference_identifier":"5471","classification":"Unclassified","potential_impacts":"","severity":"medium","responsibility":"","comments":null,"rule_version":"WN11-AU-000130","check_content":"Security Option \"Audit: Force audit policy subcategory settings to override audit policy category settings\" must be set to \"Enabled\" (WN11-SO-000030) for the detailed auditing subcategories to be effective. \n\nUse the AuditPol tool to review the current Audit Policy configuration:\nOpen a Command Prompt with elevated privileges (\"Run as Administrator\").\nEnter \"AuditPol /get /category:*\"\n\nCompare the AuditPol settings with the following. If the system does not audit the following, this is a finding:\n\nSystem &gt;&gt; Other System Events - Success","false_positives":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"uuid":"67B5FC70-722B-1014-B523-80A454AB0D26","discussion":"Maintaining an audit trail of system activity logs can help identify configuration errors, troubleshoot service disruptions, and analyze compromises that have occurred, as well as detect attacks. Audit logs are necessary to provide a trail of evidence in case the system or network is compromised. Collecting this data is essential for analyzing the security of information assets and detecting signs of suspicious and unexpected behavior.\n\nAudit Other System Events records information related to cryptographic key operations and the Windows Firewall service.","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-04-01T11:52:15\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :   false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :     false ('Other System Events' is set to 'Success' or 'Success and Failure')\nResult Analysis :          other_system_events = 'AUDIT_NONE' failed test of 'equals' compared to 'AUDIT_SUCCESS_FAILURE' \n                : other_system_events = 'AUDIT_NONE' failed test of 'equals' compared to 'AUDIT_SUCCESS' \n"},{"security_override_guidance":"","group_title":"SRG-OS-000471-GPOS-00215","third_party_tools":"","rule_title":"The system must be configured to audit System - Other System Events failures.","rule_id":"SV-253332r991579","weight":"10.0","stig_uuid":"677F401D-722B-1014-B949-B81E5231A214","ccis":["CCI-000172"],"ia_controls":"","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-OS-000471-GPOS-00215","id":"V-253332"},"group_id":"V-253332","mitigations":"","documentable":"false","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Windows Settings &gt;&gt; Security Settings &gt;&gt; Advanced Audit Policy Configuration &gt;&gt; System Audit Policies &gt;&gt; System &gt;&gt; \"Audit Other System Events\" with \"Failure\" selected.","rule_id_src":"SV-253332r991579_rule","status":"open","group_id_src":"V-253332","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windows11:def:253332","href":"U_MS_Windows_11_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV16-oval.xml"},"reference_identifier":"5471","classification":"Unclassified","potential_impacts":"","severity":"medium","responsibility":"","comments":null,"rule_version":"WN11-AU-000135","check_content":"Security Option \"Audit: Force audit policy subcategory settings to override audit policy category settings\" must be set to \"Enabled\" (WN11-SO-000030) for the detailed auditing subcategories to be effective. \n\nUse the AuditPol tool to review the current Audit Policy configuration:\nOpen a Command Prompt with elevated privileges (\"Run as Administrator\").\nEnter \"AuditPol /get /category:*\"\n\nCompare the AuditPol settings with the following. If the system does not audit the following, this is a finding:\n\nSystem &gt;&gt; Other System Events - Failure","false_positives":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"uuid":"67B6013E-722B-1014-B2A5-95F507CA389F","discussion":"Maintaining an audit trail of system activity logs can help identify configuration errors, troubleshoot service disruptions, and analyze compromises that have occurred, as well as detect attacks. Audit logs are necessary to provide a trail of evidence in case the system or network is compromised. Collecting this data is essential for analyzing the security of information assets and detecting signs of suspicious and unexpected behavior.\n\nAudit Other System Events records information related to cryptographic key operations and the Windows Firewall service.","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-04-01T11:52:15\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :   false (All child tests must be true. (AN