ded files and attachments will be disabled.","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-04-01T11:54:19\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Windows Components\\Microsoft Defender Antivirus\\Real-time Protection\\Scan all downloaded files and attachments)\n"},{"security_override_guidance":"","group_title":"SRG-APP-000278","third_party_tools":"","rule_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must be configured to always enable real-time protection.","rule_id":"SV-213445r961194","weight":"10.0","stig_uuid":"7387268B-722B-1014-941A-E212739FAB8B","ccis":["CCI-001242"],"ia_controls":"","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000278","id":"V-213445"},"group_id":"V-213445","mitigations":"","documentable":"false","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Microsoft Defender Antivirus &gt;&gt; Real-time Protection &gt;&gt; \"Turn off real-time protection\" to \"Disabled\" or \"Not Configured\".","rule_id_src":"SV-213445r961194_rule","status":"not_a_finding","group_id_src":"V-213445","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.defenderantivirus:def:20","href":"U_MS_Defender_Antivirus_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV13-oval.xml"},"reference_identifier":"3985","classification":"Unclassified","potential_impacts":"","severity":"medium","responsibility":"","comments":null,"rule_version":"WNDF-AV-000021","check_content":"Verify the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Microsoft Defender Antivirus &gt;&gt; Real-time Protection &gt;&gt; \"Turn off real-time protection\" is set to \"Disabled\" or \"Not Configured\".\n \nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \nHKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Real-Time Protection\n\nCriteria: If the value \"DisableRealtimeMonitoring\" is REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.\n\nIf the value does not exist, this is not a finding.\n\nIf the value is 1, this is a finding.","false_positives":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-89907","V-75227"],"uuid":"738D9196-722B-1014-94C2-9E6A39A2F2E4","discussion":"This policy setting turns off real-time protection prompts for known malware detection. Microsoft Defender Antivirus alerts  when malware or potentially unwanted software attempts to install itself or to run on your computer. If this policy setting is enabled, Microsoft Defender Antivirus will not prompt users to take actions on malware detections. If this policy setting is disabled or not configured, Microsoft Defender Antivirus will prompt users to take actions on malware detections.","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-04-01T11:54:19\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Windows Components\\Microsoft Defender Antivirus\\Real-time Protection\\Turn off real-time protection)\n"},{"security_override_guidance":"","group_title":"SRG-APP-000210","third_party_tools":"","rule_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must be configured to enable behavior monitoring.","rule_id":"SV-213446r961092","weight":"10.0","stig_uuid":"7387268B-722B-1014-941A-E212739FAB8B","ccis":["CCI-001170"],"ia_controls":"","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000210","id":"V-213446"},"group_id":"V-213446","mitigations":"","documentable":"false","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Windows Defender Antivirus &gt;&gt; Real-time Protection &gt;&gt; \"Turn on behavior monitoring\" to \"Enabled \" or \"Not Configured\".","rule_id_src":"SV-213446r961092_rule","status":"not_a_finding","group_id_src":"V-213446","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.defenderantivirus:def:21","href":"U_MS_Defender_Antivirus_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV13-oval.xml"},"reference_identifier":"3985","classification":"Unclassified","potential_impacts":"","severity":"medium","responsibility":"","comments":null,"rule_version":"WNDF-AV-000022","check_content":"Verify the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Microsoft Defender Antivirus &gt;&gt; Real-time Protection &gt;&gt; \"Turn on behavior monitoring\" is set to \"Enabled\" or \"Not Configured\".\n \nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \nHKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Real-Time Protection\n\nCriteria: If the value \"DisableBehaviorMonitoring\" is REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.\n\nIf the value does not exist, this is not a finding.\n\nIf the value is 1, this is a finding.","false_positives":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-89909","V-75229"],"uuid":"738D9B40-722B-1014-AF9B-F5141667982E","discussion":"This policy setting allows configuration of behavior monitoring. If this setting is enabled or not configured, behavior monitoring will be enabled. If this setting is disabled, behavior monitoring will be disabled.","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-04-01T11:54:19\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Windows Components\\Microsoft Defender Antivirus\\Real-time Protection\\Turn on behavior monitoring)\n"},{"security_override_guidance":"","group_title":"SRG-APP-000278","third_party_tools":"","rule_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must be configured to process scanning when real-time protection is enabled.","rule_id":"SV-213447r961194","weight":"10.0","stig_uuid":"7387268B-722B-1014-941A-E212739FAB8B","ccis":["CCI-001242"],"ia_controls":"","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000278","id":"V-213447"},"group_id":"V-213447","mitigations":"","documentable":"false","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Microsoft Defender Antivirus &gt;&gt; Real-time Protection &gt;&gt; \"Turn on process scanning whenever real-time protection is enabled\" to \"Enabled\" or \"Not Configured\".","rule_id_src":"SV-213447r961194_rule","status":"not_a_finding","group_id_src":"V-213447","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.defenderantivirus:def:22","href":"U_MS_Defender_Antivirus_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV13-oval.xml"},"reference_identifier":"3985","classification":"Unclassified","potential_impacts":"","severity":"medium","responsibility":"","comments":null,"rule_version":"WNDF-AV-000023","check_content":"Verify the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Microsoft Defender Antivirus &gt;&gt; Real-time Protection &gt;&gt; \"Turn on process scanning whenever real-time protection is enabled\" is set to \"Enabled\" or \"Not Configured\".\n \nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \nHKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Real-Time Protection\n\nCriteria: If the value \"DisableScanOnRealtimeEnable\" is REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.\n\nIf the value does not exist, this is not a finding.\n\nIf the value is 1, this is a finding.","false_positives":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-89911","V-75231"],"uuid":"738DA5B8-722B-1014-B299-CC1C01739731","discussion":"This policy setting allows the configuration of process scanning when real-time protection is turned on. This helps to catch malware, which could start when real-time protection is turned off. If this setting is enabled or not configured, a process scan will be initiated when real-time protection is turned on. If this setting is disabled, a process scan will not be initiated when real-time protection is turned on.","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-04-01T11:54:19\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Windows Components\\Microsoft Defender Antivirus\\Real-time Protection\\Turn on process scanning whenever real-time protection is enabled)\n"},{"security_override_guidance":"","group_title":"SRG-APP-000278","third_party_tools":"","rule_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must be configured to scan archive files.","rule_id":"SV-213448r961194","weight":"10.0","stig_uuid":"7387268B-722B-1014-941A-E212739FAB8B","ccis":["CCI-001242"],"ia_controls":"","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000278","id":"V-213448"},"group_id":"V-213448","mitigations":"","documentable":"false","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Microsoft Defender Antivirus &gt;&gt; Scan &gt;&gt; \"Scan archive files\" to \"Enabled \" or \"Not Configured\".","rule_id_src":"SV-213448r961194_rule","status":"not_a_finding","group_id_src":"V-213448","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.defenderantivirus:def:23","href":"U_MS_Defender_Antivirus_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV13-oval.xml"},"reference_identifier":"3985","classification":"Unclassified","potential_impacts":"","severity":"medium","responsibility":"","comments":null,"rule_version":"WNDF-AV-000024","check_content":"Verify the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Microsoft Defender Antivirus &gt;&gt; Scan &gt;&gt; \"Scan archive files\" is set to \"Enabled\" or \"Not Configured\".\n \nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \nHKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Scan\n\nCriteria: If the value \"DisableArchiveScanning\" is REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.\n\nIf the value does not exist, this is not a finding.\n\nIf the value is 1, this is a finding.","false_positives":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-89913","V-75233"],"uuid":"738DAF6C-722B-1014-A934-C6E74A62BDAC","discussion":"This policy setting allows the configuration of scans for malicious software and unwanted software in archive files such as .ZIP or .CAB files. If this setting is enabled or not configured, archive files will be scanned. If this setting is disabled, archive files will not be scanned.","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-04-01T11:54:19\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Windows Components\\Microsoft Defender Antivirus\\Scan\\Scan archive files)\n"},{"security_override_guidance":"","group_title":"SRG-APP-000073","third_party_tools":"","rule_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must be configured to scan removable drives.","rule_id":"SV-213449r960852","weight":"10.0","stig_uuid":"7387268B-722B-1014-941A-E212739FAB8B","ccis":["CCI-000870"],"ia_controls":"","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000073","id":"V-213449"},"group_id":"V-213449","mitigations":"","documentable":"false","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Windows Defender Antivirus &gt;&gt; Scan &gt;&gt; \"Scan removable drives\" to \"Enabled\".","rule_id_src":"SV-213449r960852_rule","status":"open","group_id_src":"V-213449","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.defenderantivirus:def:24","href":"U_MS_Defender_Antivirus_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV13-oval.xml"},"reference_identifier":"3985","classification":"Unclassified","potential_impacts":"","severity":"medium","responsibility":"","comments":null,"rule_version":"WNDF-AV-000025","check_content":"Verify the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Microsoft Defender Antivirus &gt;&gt; Scan &gt;&gt; \"Scan removable drives\" is set to \"Enabled\".\n \nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \nHKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Scan\n\nCriteria: If the value \"DisableRemovableDriveScanning\" is REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.","false_positives":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-89915","V-75235"],"uuid":"738DB8D4-722B-1014-9813-B5A37A4BB21C","discussion":"This policy setting allows the management of whether or not to scan for malicious software and unwanted software in the contents of removable drives such as USB flash drives when running a full scan. If this setting is enabled, removable drives will be scanned during any type of scan. If this setting is disabled or not configured, removable drives will not be scanned during a full scan. Removable drives may still be scanned during quick scan and custom scan.","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-04-01T11:54:19\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Windows Components\\Microsoft Defender Antivirus\\Scan\\Scan removable drives)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Scan\\DisableRemovableDriveScanning'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n"},{"security_override_guidance":"","group_title":"SRG-APP-000277","third_party_tools":"","rule_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must be configured to perform a weekly scheduled scan.","rule_id":"SV-213450r961191","weight":"10.0","stig_uuid":"7387268B-722B-1014-941A-E212739FAB8B","ccis":["CCI-001241"],"ia_controls":"","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000277","id":"V-213450"},"group_id":"V-213450","mitigations":"","documentable":"false","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Microsoft Defender Antivirus &gt;&gt; Scan &gt;&gt; \"Specify the day of the week to run a scheduled scan\" to \"Enabled \" and select anything other than \"Never\" in the drop-down box.","rule_id_src":"SV-213450r961191_rule","status":"open","group_id_src":"V-213450","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.defenderantivirus:def:25","href":"U_MS_Defender_Antivirus_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV13-oval.xml"},"reference_identifier":"3985","classification":"Unclassified","potential_impacts":"","severity":"medium","responsibility":"","comments":null,"rule_version":"WNDF-AV-000026","check_content":"Verify the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Microsoft Defender Antivirus &gt;&gt; Scan &gt;&gt; \"Specify the day of the week to run a scheduled scan\" is set to \"Enabled\" and anything other than \"Never\" is selected in the drop-down box.\n  \nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \nHKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Scan\n\nCriteria: If the value \"ScheduleDay\" is REG_DWORD = 0x8, this is a finding.\n\nValues of 0x0 through 0x7 are acceptable and not a finding.","false_positives":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-89917","V-75237"],"uuid":"738DC23A-722B-1014-9F18-A80C859607ED","discussion":"This policy setting allows specifying the day of the week on which to perform a scheduled scan. The scan can also be configured to run every day or to never run at all. This setting can be configured with the following ordinal number values: \n(0x0) Every Day  \n(0x1) Sunday  \n(0x2) Monday  \n(0x3) Tuesday  \n(0x4) Wednesday  \n(0x5) Thursday  \n(0x6) Friday  \n(0x7) Saturday  \n(0x8) Never (default)  \n\nIf this setting is enabled, a scheduled scan will run at the frequency specified. If this setting is disabled or not configured, a scheduled scan will run at a default frequency.","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-04-01T11:54:19\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Windows Components\\Microsoft Defender Antivirus\\Scan\\Specify the day of the week to run a scheduled scan)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Scan\\ScheduleDay'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n"},{"security_override_guidance":"","group_title":"SRG-APP-000210","third_party_tools":"","rule_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must be configured to turn on e-mail scanning.","rule_id":"SV-213451r961092","weight":"10.0","stig_uuid":"7387268B-722B-1014-941A-E212739FAB8B","ccis":["CCI-001170"],"ia_controls":"","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000210","id":"V-213451"},"group_id":"V-213451","mitigations":"","documentable":"false","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Microsoft Defender Antivirus &gt;&gt; Scan &gt;&gt; \"Turn on e-mail scanning\" to \"Enabled\".","rule_id_src":"SV-213451r961092_rule","status":"open","group_id_src":"V-213451","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.defenderantivirus:def:26","href":"U_MS_Defender_Antivirus_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV13-oval.xml"},"reference_identifier":"3985","classification":"Unclassified","potential_impacts":"","severity":"medium","responsibility":"","comments":null,"rule_version":"WNDF-AV-000027","check_content":"Verify the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Microsoft Defender Antivirus &gt;&gt; Scan &gt;&gt; \"Turn on e-mail scanning\" is set to \"Enabled\".\n  \nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \nHKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Scan\n\nCriteria: If the value \"DisableEmailScanning\" is REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.","false_positives":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-89919","V-75239"],"uuid":"738DCB5F-722B-1014-AC11-8530332F23EE","discussion":"This policy setting allows the configuration of e-mail scanning. When e-mail scanning is enabled, the engine will parse the mailbox and mail files according to their specific format in order to analyze the mail bodies and attachments. Several e-mail formats are currently supported, for example: pst (Outlook), dbx mbx mime (Outlook Express), binhex (Mac). If this setting is enabled, e-mail scanning will be enabled. If this setting is disabled or not configured, e-mail scanning will be disabled.","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-04-01T11:54:19\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Windows Components/Microsoft Defender Antivirus/Scan/Turn on e-mail scanning is set to Enabled)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Scan\\DisableEmailScanning'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n"},{"security_override_guidance":"","group_title":"SRG-APP-000276","third_party_tools":"","rule_title":"Microsoft Defender AV spyware definition age must not exceed 7 days.","rule_id":"SV-213452r961188","weight":"10.0","stig_uuid":"7387268B-722B-1014-941A-E212739FAB8B","ccis":["CCI-001240"],"ia_controls":"","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000276","id":"V-213452"},"group_id":"V-213452","mitigations":"","documentable":"false","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Windows Defender Antivirus &gt;&gt; Signature Updates &gt;&gt; \"Define the number of days before spyware definitions are considered out of date\" to \"Enabled\" and select \"7\" or less in the drop-down box.\n\nDo not select a value of 0. This disables the option.","rule_id_src":"SV-213452r961188_rule","status":"open","group_id_src":"V-213452","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.defenderantivirus:def:27","href":"U_MS_Defender_Antivirus_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV13-oval.xml"},"reference_identifier":"3985","classification":"Unclassified","potential_impacts":"","severity":"high","responsibility":"","comments":null,"rule_version":"WNDF-AV-000028","check_content":"Verify the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Microsoft Defender Antivirus &gt;&gt; Security Intelligence Updates &gt;&gt; \"Define the number of days before spyware security intelligence considered out of date\" is set to \"Enabled\" and \"7\" or less is selected in the drop-down box (excluding \"0\", which is unacceptable).\n\nIf third-party antispyware is installed and up to date, the Windows Defender AV spyware age requirement will be NA.\n\nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \nHKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Signature Updates\n\nCriteria: If the value \"ASSignatureDue\" is REG_DWORD = 7, this is not a finding.\n\nA value of 1 - 6 is also acceptable and not a finding.\n\nA value of 0 is a finding.\n\nA value higher than 7 is a finding.","false_positives":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-89921","V-75241"],"uuid":"738DD572-722B-1014-883B-F087BCEF74E5","discussion":"This policy setting allows defining the number of days that must pass before spyware definitions are considered out of date. If definitions are determined to be out of date, this state may trigger several additional actions, including falling back to an alternative update source or displaying a warning icon in the user interface. By default this value is set to 14 days. \n\nIf this setting is enabled, spyware definitions will be considered out of date after the number of days specified have passed without an update. If this setting is disabled or not configured, spyware definitions will be considered out of date after the default number of days have passed without an update.","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-04-01T11:54:19\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Windows Components\\Microsoft Defender Antivirus\\Signature Updates\\Define the number of days before spyware definitions are considered out of date_less than 7)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Signature Updates\\ASSignatureDue'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\nTest            :   false (Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Windows Components\\Microsoft Defender Antivirus\\Signature Updates\\Define the number of days before spyware definitions are considered out of date_not 0)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Signature Updates\\ASSignatureDue'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n"},{"security_override_guidance":"","group_title":"SRG-APP-000276","third_party_tools":"","rule_title":"Microsoft Defender AV virus definition age must not exceed 7 days.","rule_id":"SV-213453r961188","weight":"10.0","stig_uuid":"7387268B-722B-1014-941A-E212739FAB8B","ccis":["CCI-001240"],"ia_controls":"","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000276","id":"V-213453"},"group_id":"V-213453","mitigations":"","documentable":"false","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Microsoft Defender Antivirus &gt;&gt; Signature Updates &gt;&gt; \"Define the number of days before virus definitions are considered out of date\" to \"Enabled\" and select \"7\" or less in the drop-down box.\n\nDo not select a value of 0. This disables the option.","rule_id_src":"SV-213453r961188_rule","status":"open","group_id_src":"V-213453","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.defenderantivirus:def:28","href":"U_MS_Defender_Antivirus_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV13-oval.xml"},"reference_identifier":"3985","classification":"Unclassified","potential_impacts":"","severity":"high","responsibility":"","comments":null,"rule_version":"WNDF-AV-000029","check_content":"Verify the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Microsoft Defender Antivirus &gt;&gt;Security Intelligence Updates &gt;&gt; \"Define the number of days before virus security intelligence considered out of date\" is set to \"Enabled\" and \"7\" or less is selected in the drop-down box (excluding \"0\", which is unacceptable).\n\nIf third-party antivirus protection is installed and up to date, the Windows Defender Antivirus age requirement is NA.\n\nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \nHKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Signature Updates\n\nCriteria: If the value \"AVSignatureDue\" is REG_DWORD = 7, this is not a finding.\n\nA value of 1 - 6 is also acceptable and not a finding.\n\nA value of 0 is a finding.\n\nA value higher than 7 is a finding.","false_positives":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-89923","V-75243"],"uuid":"738DDEDE-722B-1014-AEEC-D13D315BBA2B","discussion":"This policy setting allows defining the number of days that must pass before virus definitions are considered out of date. If definitions are determined to be out of date, this state may trigger several additional actions, including falling back to an alternative update source or displaying a warning icon in the user interface. By default, this value is set to 14 days. \n\nIf this setting is enabled, virus definitions will be considered out of date after the number of days specified have passed without an update. If this setting is disabled or not configured, virus definitions will be considered out of date after the default number of days have passed without an update.","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-04-01T11:54:19\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Windows Components\\Microsoft Defender Antivirus\\Signature Updates\\Define the number of days before virus definitions are considered out of date_less than 7)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Signature Updates\\AVSignatureDue'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\nTest            :   false (Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Windows Components\\Microsoft Defender Antivirus\\Signature Updates\\Define the number of days before virus definitions are considered out of date_not 0)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Signature Updates\\AVSignatureDue'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n"},{"security_override_guidance":"","group_title":"SRG-APP-000261","third_party_tools":"","rule_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must be configured to check for definition updates daily.","rule_id":"SV-213454r961161","weight":"10.0","stig_uuid":"7387268B-722B-1014-941A-E212739FAB8B","ccis":["CCI-001308"],"ia_controls":"","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000261","id":"V-213454"},"group_id":"V-213454","mitigations":"","documentable":"false","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Microsoft Defender Antivirus &gt;&gt; Signature Updates &gt;&gt; \"Specify the day of the week to check for definition updates\" to \"Enabled\" and select \"Every Day\" in the drop-down box.","rule_id_src":"SV-213454r961161_rule","status":"open","group_id_src":"V-213454","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.defenderantivirus:def:29","href":"U_MS_Defender_Antivirus_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV13-oval.xml"},"reference_identifier":"3985","classification":"Unclassified","potential_impacts":"","severity":"medium","responsibility":"","comments":null,"rule_version":"WNDF-AV-000030","check_content":"Verify the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Microsoft Defender Antivirus &gt;&gt; Security Intelligence Updates &gt;&gt; \"Specify the day of the week to check for security intelligence updates\" is set to \"Enabled\" and \"Every Day\" is selected in the drop-down box.\n  \nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \nHKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Signature Updates\n\nCriteria: If the value \"ScheduleDay\" is REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.","false_positives":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-89925","V-75245"],"uuid":"738DE855-722B-1014-BC01-E9700265CDAD","discussion":"This policy setting allows specifying the day of the week on which to check for definition updates. The check can also be configured to run every day or to never run at all. This setting can be configured with the following ordinal number values: \n(0x0) Every Day (default)  \n(0x1) Sunday   \n(0x2) Monday  \n(0x3) Tuesday  \n(0x4) Wednesday  \n(0x5) Thursday  \n(0x6) Friday  \n(0x7) Saturday  \n(0x8) Never  \n\nIf this setting is enabled, the check for definition updates will occur at the frequency specified. If this setting is disabled or not configured, the check for definition updates will occur at a default frequency.","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-04-01T11:54:19\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Windows Components\\Microsoft Defender Antivirus\\Signature Updates\\Specify the day of the week to check for definition updates)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Signature Updates\\ScheduleDay'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n"},{"security_override_guidance":"","group_title":"SRG-APP-000207","third_party_tools":"","rule_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must be configured for automatic remediation action to be taken for threat alert level Severe.","rule_id":"SV-213455r961086","weight":"10.0","stig_uuid":"7387268B-722B-1014-941A-E212739FAB8B","ccis":["CCI-001662"],"ia_controls":"","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000207","id":"V-213455"},"group_id":"V-213455","mitigations":"","documentable":"false","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Microsoft Defender Antivirus &gt;&gt; Threats &gt;&gt; \"Specify threat alert levels at which default action should not be taken when detected\" to \"Enabled\". \n\nSelect the \"Showâ¦\" option box and enter \"5\" in the \"Value name\" field and enter \"2\" in the \"Value\" field.","rule_id_src":"SV-213455r961086_rule","status":"open","group_id_src":"V-213455","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.defenderantivirus:def:30","href":"U_MS_Defender_Antivirus_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV13-oval.xml"},"reference_identifier":"3985","classification":"Unclassified","potential_impacts":"","severity":"medium","responsibility":"","comments":null,"rule_version":"WNDF-AV-000031","check_content":"Verify the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Microsoft Defender Antivirus &gt;&gt; Threats &gt;&gt; \"Specify threat alert levels at which default action should not be taken when detected\" is set to \"Enabled\".  \n\nClick the âShowâ¦â box option and verify the \"Value name\" field contains a value of \"5\" and the \"Value\" field  contains \"2\".  A value of \"3\" in the \"Value\" field is more restrictive and also an acceptable value.\n  \nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \nHKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Threats\\ThreatSeverityDefaultAction\n\nCriteria: If the value \"5\" is REG_SZ = 2 (or 3), this is not a finding.\n","false_positives":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-89927","V-75247"],"uuid":"738DF1CE-722B-1014-B936-82DA94CD22EE","discussion":"This policy setting allows the customization of which automatic remediation action will be taken for each threat alert level. Threat alert levels should be added under the Options for this setting. Each entry must be listed as a name value pair. The name defines a threat alert level. The value contains the action ID for the remediation action that should be taken. \n\nValid threat alert levels are:  \n1 = Low  \n2 =  Medium  \n4 = High  \n5 = Severe  \n\nValid remediation action values are: \n2 = Quarantine  \n3 = Remove  \n6 = Ignore","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-04-01T11:54:19\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Windows Components\\Microsoft Defender Antivirus\\Threats\\Specify threat alert levels at which default action should not be taken when detected-Severe)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Threats\\ThreatSeverityDefaultAction\\5'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n"},{"security_override_guidance":"","group_title":"SRG-APP-000210","third_party_tools":"","rule_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must be configured to block executable content from email client and webmail.","rule_id":"SV-213456r961092","weight":"10.0","stig_uuid":"7387268B-722B-1014-941A-E212739FAB8B","ccis":["CCI-001170"],"ia_controls":"","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000210","id":"V-213456"},"group_id":"V-213456","mitigations":"","documentable":"false","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Microsoft Defender Antivirus &gt;&gt; Windows Defender Exploit Guard &gt;&gt; Attack Surface Reduction &gt;&gt; \"Configure Attack Surface Reduction rules\" to \"Enabled\". \n\nClick \"Show...\". Set the Value name to \"BE9BA2D9-53EA-4CDC-84E5-9B1EEEE46550\" and the Value to \"1\".","rule_id_src":"SV-213456r961092_rule","status":"open","group_id_src":"V-213456","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.defenderantivirus:def:31","href":"U_MS_Defender_Antivirus_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV13-oval.xml"},"reference_identifier":"3985","classification":"Unclassified","potential_impacts":"","severity":"medium","responsibility":"","comments":null,"rule_version":"WNDF-AV-000032","check_content":"This setting is applicable starting with v1709 of Windows 10. It is NA for prior versions.\n\nVerify the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Microsoft Defender Antivirus &gt;&gt; Microsoft Defender Exploit Guard &gt;&gt; Attack Surface Reduction &gt;&gt; \"Configure Attack Surface Reduction rules\" is set to \"Enabledâ.  Click \"Show...\". Verify the rule ID in the Value name column and the desired state in the Value column is set as follows:\nValue name: BE9BA2D9-53EA-4CDC-84E5-9B1EEEE46550\nValue:  1\n\nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \nHKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Windows Defender Exploit Guard\\ASR\\Rules\n\nCriteria: If the value \"BE9BA2D9-53EA-4CDC-84E5-9B1EEEE46550\" is REG_SZ = 1, this is not a finding.","false_positives":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-92661","V-77965"],"uuid":"738DFC0F-722B-1014-9C6A-D016690C8BC5","discussion":"This rule blocks the following file types from being run or launched from an email seen in either Microsoft Outlook or webmail (such as Gmail.com or Outlook.com):\nExecutable files (such as .exe, .dll, or .scr)\nScript files (such as a PowerShell .ps, VisualBasic .vbs, or JavaScript .js file)\nScript archive files","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-04-01T11:54:19\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (One or more child tests must be true. (OR))\nTest            :   false (Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Windows Components\\Microsoft Defender Antivirus\\Microsoft Defender Exploit Guard\\Attack Surface Reduction\\Configure Attack Surface Reduction rules550)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Windows Defender Exploit Guard\\ASR\\Rules\\BE9BA2D9-53EA-4CDC-84E5-9B1EEEE46550'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\nCriteria        :   false (All child tests must be true. (AND)) (negated)\nTest            :     true (Verifies the version is v1709 or greater)\n"},{"security_override_guidance":"","group_title":"SRG-APP-000210","third_party_tools":"","rule_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must be configured block Office applications from creating child processes.","rule_id":"SV-213457r961092","weight":"10.0","stig_uuid":"7387268B-722B-1014-941A-E212739FAB8B","ccis":["CCI-001170"],"ia_controls":"","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000210","id":"V-213457"},"group_id":"V-213457","mitigations":"","documentable":"false","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Microsoft Defender Antivirus &gt;&gt; Windows Defender Exploit Guard &gt;&gt; Attack Surface Reduction &gt;&gt; \"Configure Attack Surface Reduction rules\" to \"Enabled\". \n\nClick \"Show...\". Set the Value name to \"D4F940AB-401B-4EFC-AADC-AD5F3C50688A\" and the Value to \"1\".","rule_id_src":"SV-213457r961092_rule","status":"open","group_id_src":"V-213457","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.defenderantivirus:def:32","href":"U_MS_Defender_Antivirus_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV13-oval.xml"},"reference_identifier":"3985","classification":"Unclassified","potential_impacts":"","severity":"medium","responsibility":"","comments":null,"rule_version":"WNDF-AV-000033","check_content":"This setting is applicable starting with v1709 of Windows 10. It is NA for prior versions.\n\nVerify the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Microsoft Defender Antivirus &gt;&gt; Microsoft Defender Exploit Guard &gt;&gt; Attack Surface Reduction &gt;&gt; \"Configure Attack Surface Reduction rules\" is set to \"Enabledâ.  Click \"Show...\". Verify the rule ID in the Value name column and the desired state in the Value column is set as follows:\nValue name: D4F940AB-401B-4EFC-AADC-AD5F3C50688A\nValue:  1\n\nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \nHKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Windows Defender Exploit Guard\\ASR\\Rules\n\nCriteria: If the value \"D4F940AB-401B-4EFC-AADC-AD5F3C50688A\" is REG_SZ = 1, this is not a finding.","false_positives":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-92663","V-77967"],"uuid":"738E0594-722B-1014-89C5-B6E7C64E5998","discussion":"Office apps, such as Word or Excel, will not be allowed to create child processes. This is a typical malware behavior, especially for macro-based attacks that attempt to use Office apps to launch or download malicious executables.","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-04-01T11:54:19\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (One or more child tests must be true. (OR))\nTest            :   false (Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Windows Components\\Microsoft Defender Antivirus\\Microsoft Defender Exploit Guard\\Attack Surface Reduction\\Configure Attack Surface Reduction rules)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Windows Defender Exploit Guard\\ASR\\Rules\\D4F940AB-401B-4EFC-AADC-AD5F3C50688A'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\nCriteria        :   false (All child tests must be true. (AND)) (negated)\nTest            :     true (Verifies the version is v1709 or greater)\n"},{"security_override_guidance":"","group_title":"SRG-APP-000210","third_party_tools":"","rule_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must be configured block Office applications from creating executable content.","rule_id":"SV-213458r961092","weight":"10.0","stig_uuid":"7387268B-722B-1014-941A-E212739FAB8B","ccis":["CCI-001170"],"ia_controls":"","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000210","id":"V-213458"},"group_id":"V-213458","mitigations":"","documentable":"false","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Microsoft Defender Antivirus &gt;&gt; Windows Defender Exploit Guard &gt;&gt; Attack Surface Reduction &gt;&gt; \"Configure Attack Surface Reduction rules\" to \"Enabled\". \n\nClick \"Show...\". Set the Value name to \"3B576869-A4EC-4529-8536-B80A7769E899\" and the Value to \"1\".","rule_id_src":"SV-213458r961092_rule","status":"open","group_id_src":"V-213458","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.defenderantivirus:def:33","href":"U_MS_Defender_Antivirus_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV13-oval.xml"},"reference_identifier":"3985","classification":"Unclassified","potential_impacts":"","severity":"medium","responsibility":"","comments":null,"rule_version":"WNDF-AV-000034","check_content":"This setting is applicable starting with v1709 of Windows 10. It is NA for prior versions.\n\nVerify the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Microsoft Defender Antivirus &gt;&gt; Microsoft Defender Exploit Guard &gt;&gt; Attack Surface Reduction &gt;&gt; \"Configure Attack Surface Reduction rules\" is set to \"Enabledâ.  Click \"Show...\". Verify the rule ID in the Value name column and the desired state in the Value column is set as follows:\nValue name: 3B576869-A4EC-4529-8536-B80A7769E899\nValue:  1\n \nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \nHKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Windows Defender Exploit Guard\\ASR\\Rules\n\nCriteria: If the value \"3B576869-A4EC-4529-8536-B80A7769E899\" is REG_SZ = 1, this is not a finding.","false_positives":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-92665","V-77969"],"uuid":"738E0EE5-722B-1014-8681-91EB9FC5833B","discussion":"This rule targets typical behaviors used by suspicious and malicious add-ons and scripts (extensions) that create or launch executable files. This is a typical malware technique. Extensions will be blocked from being used by Office apps. Typically these extensions use the Windows Scripting Host (.wsh files) to run scripts that automate certain tasks or provide user-created add-on features.","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-04-01T11:54:19\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (One or more child tests must be true. (OR))\nTest            :   false (Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Windows Components\\Microsoft Defender Antivirus\\Microsoft Defender Exploit Guard\\Attack Surface Reduction\\Configure Attack Surface Reduction rules)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Windows Defender Exploit Guard\\ASR\\Rules\\3B576869-A4EC-4529-8536-B80A7769E899'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\nCriteria        :   false (All child tests must be true. (AND)) (negated)\nTest            :     true (Verifies the version is v1709 or greater)\n"},{"security_override_guidance":"","group_title":"SRG-APP-000210","third_party_tools":"","rule_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must be configured to block Office applications from injecting into other processes.","rule_id":"SV-213459r961092","weight":"10.0","stig_uuid":"7387268B-722B-1014-941A-E212739FAB8B","ccis":["CCI-001170"],"ia_controls":"","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000210","id":"V-213459"},"group_id":"V-213459","mitigations":"","documentable":"false","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Microsoft Defender Antivirus &gt;&gt; Windows Defender Exploit Guard &gt;&gt; Attack Surface Reduction &gt;&gt; \"Configure Attack Surface Reduction rules\" to \"Enabled\".\n\nClick \"Show...\". Set the Value name to \"75668C1F-73B5-4CF0-BB93-3ECF5CB7CC84\" and the Value to \"1\".","rule_id_src":"SV-213459r961092_rule","status":"open","group_id_src":"V-213459","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.defenderantivirus:def:34","href":"U_MS_Defender_Antivirus_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV13-oval.xml"},"reference_identifier":"3985","classification":"Unclassified","potential_impacts":"","severity":"medium","responsibility":"","comments":null,"rule_version":"WNDF-AV-000035","check_content":"This setting is applicable starting with v1709 of Windows 10. It is NA for prior versions.\n\nVerify the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Microsoft Defender Antivirus &gt;&gt; Microsoft Defender Exploit Guard &gt;&gt; Attack Surface Reduction &gt;&gt; \"Configure Attack Surface Reduction rules\" is set to \"Enabledâ.  Click \"Show...\". Verify the rule ID in the Value name column and the desired state in the Value column is set as follows:\nValue name: 75668C1F-73B5-4CF0-BB93-3ECF5CB7CC84\nValue:  1\n\nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \nHKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Windows Defender Exploit Guard\\ASR\\Rules\n\nCriteria: If the value \"75668C1F-73B5-4CF0-BB93-3ECF5CB7CC84\" is REG_SZ = 1, this is not a finding.","false_positives":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-92667","V-77971"],"uuid":"738E18C0-722B-1014-A4D7-9316B0E8CC0F","discussion":"Office apps, such as Word, Excel, or PowerPoint, will not be able to inject code into other processes. This is typically used by malware to run malicious code in an attempt to hide the activity from antivirus scanning engines.","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-04-01T11:54:19\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (One or more child tests must be true. (OR))\nTest            :   false (Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Windows Components\\Microsoft Defender Antivirus\\Microsoft Defender Exploit Guard\\Attack Surface Reduction\\Configure Attack Surface Reduction rules)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Windows Defender Exploit Guard\\ASR\\Rules\\75668C1F-73B5-4CF0-BB93-3ECF5CB7CC84'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\nCriteria        :   false (All child tests must be true. (AND)) (negated)\nTest            :     true (Verifies the version is v1709 or greater)\n"},{"security_override_guidance":"","group_title":"SRG-APP-000210","third_party_tools":"","rule_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must be configured to impede JavaScript and VBScript to launch executables.","rule_id":"SV-213460r961092","weight":"10.0","stig_uuid":"7387268B-722B-1014-941A-E212739FAB8B","ccis":["CCI-001170"],"ia_controls":"","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000210","id":"V-213460"},"group_id":"V-213460","mitigations":"","documentable":"false","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Microsoft Defender Antivirus &gt;&gt; Windows Defender Exploit Guard &gt;&gt; Attack Surface Reduction &gt;&gt; \"Configure Attack Surface Reduction rules\" to \"Enabled\".\n\nClick \"Show...\". Set the Value name to \"D3E037E1-3EB8-44C8-A917-57927947596D\" and the Value to \"1\".","rule_id_src":"SV-213460r961092_rule","status":"open","group_id_src":"V-213460","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.defenderantivirus:def:35","href":"U_MS_Defender_Antivirus_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV13-oval.xml"},"reference_identifier":"3985","classification":"Unclassified","potential_impacts":"","severity":"medium","responsibility":"","comments":null,"rule_version":"WNDF-AV-000036","check_content":"This setting is applicable starting with v1709 of Windows 10. It is NA for prior versions.\n\nVerify the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Microsoft Defender Antivirus &gt;&gt; Microsoft Defender Exploit Guard &gt;&gt; Attack Surface Reduction &gt;&gt; \"Configure Attack Surface Reduction rules\" is set to \"Enabled\". Click \"Show...\". Verify the rule ID in the Value name column and the desired state in the Value column is set as follows:\nValue name: D3E037E1-3EB8-44C8-A917-57927947596D \nValue:  1\n\nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \nHKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Windows Defender Exploit Guard\\ASR\\Rules\n\nCriteria: If the value \"D3E037E1-3EB8-44C8-A917-57927947596D\" is REG_SZ = 1, this is not a finding.","false_positives":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-92669","V-77973"],"uuid":"738E2445-722B-1014-A361-F26B742C0B5F","discussion":"JavaScript and VBScript scripts can be used by malware to launch other malicious apps. This rule prevents these scripts from being allowed to launch apps, thus preventing malicious use of the scripts to spread malware and infect machines.","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-04-01T11:54:19\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (One or more child tests must be true. (OR))\nTest            :   false (Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Windows Components\\Microsoft Defender Antivirus\\Microsoft Defender Exploit Guard\\Attack Surface Reduction\\Configure Attack Surface Reduction rules)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Windows Defender Exploit Guard\\ASR\\Rules\\D3E037E1-3EB8-44C8-A917-57927947596D'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\nCriteria        :   false (All child tests must be true. (AND)) (negated)\nTest            :     true (Verifies the version is v1709 or greater)\n"},{"security_override_guidance":"","group_title":"SRG-APP-000210","third_party_tools":"","rule_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must be configured to block execution of potentially obfuscated scripts.","rule_id":"SV-213461r961092","weight":"10.0","stig_uuid":"7387268B-722B-1014-941A-E212739FAB8B","ccis":["CCI-001170"],"ia_controls":"","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000210","id":"V-213461"},"group_id":"V-213461","mitigations":"","documentable":"false","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Microsoft Defender Antivirus &gt;&gt; Windows Defender Exploit Guard &gt;&gt; Attack Surface Reduction &gt;&gt; \"Configure Attack Surface Reduction rules\" to \"Enabled\". \n\nClick \"Show...\". Set the Value name to \"5BEB7EFE-FD9A-4556-801D-275E5FFC04CC\" and the Value to \"1\".","rule_id_src":"SV-213461r961092_rule","status":"open","group_id_src":"V-213461","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.defenderantivirus:def:36","href":"U_MS_Defender_Antivirus_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV13-oval.xml"},"reference_identifier":"3985","classification":"Unclassified","potential_impacts":"","severity":"medium","responsibility":"","comments":null,"rule_version":"WNDF-AV-000037","check_content":"This setting is applicable starting with v1709 of Windows 10. It is NA for prior versions.\n\nVerify the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Microsoft Defender Antivirus &gt;&gt; Windows Defender Exploit Guard &gt;&gt; Attack Surface Reduction &gt;&gt; \"Configure Attack Surface Reduction rules\" is set to \"Enabledâ.  Click \"Show...\". Verify the rule ID in the Value name column and the desired state in the Value column is set as follows:\nValue name: 5BEB7EFE-FD9A-4556-801D-275E5FFC04CC\nValue:  1\n\nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \nHKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Windows Defender Exploit Guard\\ASR\\Rules\n\nCriteria: If the value \"5BEB7EFE-FD9A-4556-801D-275E5FFC04CC\" is REG_SZ = 1, this is not a finding.","false_positives":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-92671","V-77975"],"uuid":"738E2F19-722B-1014-958F-8A2479E01759","discussion":"Malware and other threats can attempt to obfuscate or hide their malicious code in some script files. This rule prevents scripts that appear to be obfuscated from running. It uses the AntiMalwareScanInterface (AMSI) to determine if a script is potentially obfuscated and then blocks such a script or blocks scripts when an attempt is made to access them.","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-04-01T11:54:19\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (One or more child tests must be true. (OR))\nTest            :   false (Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Windows Components\\Microsoft Defender Antivirus\\Microsoft Defender Exploit Guard\\Attack Surface Reduction\\Configure Attack Surface Reduction rules4CC)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Windows Defender Exploit Guard\\ASR\\Rules\\5BEB7EFE-FD9A-4556-801D-275E5FFC04CC'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\nCriteria        :   false (All child tests must be true. (AND)) (negated)\nTest            :     true (Verifies the version is v1709 or greater)\n"},{"security_override_guidance":"","group_title":"SRG-APP-000210","third_party_tools":"","rule_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must be configured to block Win32 imports from macro code in Office.","rule_id":"SV-213462r961092","weight":"10.0","stig_uuid":"7387268B-722B-1014-941A-E212739FAB8B","ccis":["CCI-001170"],"ia_controls":"","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000210","id":"V-213462"},"group_id":"V-213462","mitigations":"","documentable":"false","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Microsoft Defender Antivirus &gt;&gt; Windows Defender Exploit Guard &gt;&gt; Attack Surface Reduction &gt;&gt; \"Configure Attack Surface Reduction rules\" to \"Enabled\". \n\nClick \"Show...\". Set the Value name to \"92E97FA1-2EDF-4476-BDD6-9DD0B4DDDC7B\" and the Value to \"1\".","rule_id_src":"SV-213462r961092_rule","status":"open","group_id_src":"V-213462","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.defenderantivirus:def:37","href":"U_MS_Defender_Antivirus_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV13-oval.xml"},"reference_identifier":"3985","classification":"Unclassified","potential_impacts":"","severity":"medium","responsibility":"","comments":null,"rule_version":"WNDF-AV-000038","check_content":"This setting is applicable starting with v1709 of Windows 10. It is NA for prior versions.\n\nVerify the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Microsoft Defender Antivirus &gt;&gt; Microsoft Defender Exploit Guard &gt;&gt; Attack Surface Reduction &gt;&gt; \"Configure Attack Surface Reduction rules\" is set to \"Enabled\". Click \"Show...\". Verify the rule ID in the Value name column and the desired state in the Value column is set as follows:\nValue name: 92E97FA1-2EDF-4476-BDD6-9DD0B4DDDC7B\nValue:  1\n\nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \nHKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Windows Defender Exploit Guard\\ASR\\Rules\n\nCriteria: If the value \"92E97FA1-2EDF-4476-BDD6-9DD0B4DDDC7B\" is REG_SZ = 1, this is not a finding.","false_positives":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-92673","V-77977"],"uuid":"738E3964-722B-1014-8651-C732544BFF3D","discussion":"This rule blocks potentially malicious behavior by not allowing macro code to execute routines in the Win 32 dynamic link library (DLL).","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-04-01T11:54:19\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (One or more child tests must be true. (OR))\nTest            :   false (Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Windows Components\\Microsoft Defender Antivirus\\Microsoft Defender Exploit Guard\\Attack Surface Reduction\\Configure Attack Surface Reduction rules)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Windows Defender Exploit Guard\\ASR\\Rules\\92E97FA1-2EDF-4476-BDD6-9DD0B4DDDC7B'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\nCriteria        :   false (All child tests must be true. (AND)) (negated)\nTest            :     true (Verifies the version is v1709 or greater)\n"},{"security_override_guidance":"","group_title":"SRG-APP-000210","third_party_tools":"","rule_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must be configured to prevent user and apps from accessing dangerous websites.","rule_id":"SV-213463r961092","weight":"10.0","stig_uuid":"7387268B-722B-1014-941A-E212739FAB8B","ccis":["CCI-001170"],"ia_controls":"","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000210","id":"V-213463"},"group_id":"V-213463","mitigations":"","documentable":"false","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Microsoft Defender Antivirus &gt;&gt; Windows Defender Exploit Guard &gt;&gt; Network Protection &gt;&gt; \"Prevent users and apps from accessing dangerous websites\" to \"Enabled\" and select \"Block\" in the drop-down box.","rule_id_src":"SV-213463r961092_rule","status":"open","group_id_src":"V-213463","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.defenderantivirus:def:38","href":"U_MS_Defender_Antivirus_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV13-oval.xml"},"reference_identifier":"3985","classification":"Unclassified","potential_impacts":"","severity":"medium","responsibility":"","comments":null,"rule_version":"WNDF-AV-000039","check_content":"This setting is applicable starting with v1709 of Windows 10, it is NA for prior versions.\n\nVerify the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Microsoft Defender Antivirus &gt;&gt; Microsoft Defender Exploit Guard &gt;&gt; Network Protection &gt;&gt; \"Prevent users and apps from accessing dangerous websites\" is set to \"Enabledâ and \"Block\" is selected in the drop-down box.\n\nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \nHKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Windows Defender Exploit Guard\\Network Protection\n\nCriteria: If the value \"EnableNetworkProtection\" is REG_DWORD = 1, this is not a finding.","false_positives":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-92675","V-77979"],"uuid":"738E4343-722B-1014-AC1A-A73F63BAB2B4","discussion":"Enable Microsoft Defender Exploit Guard network protection to prevent employees from using any application to access dangerous domains that may host phishing scams, exploit-hosting sites, and other malicious content on the internet.","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-04-01T11:54:19\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (One or more child tests must be true. (OR))\nTest            :   false (Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Windows Components\\Microsoft Defender Antivirus\\Microsoft Defender Exploit Guard\\Network Protection\\Prevent users and apps from accessing dangerous websites)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Windows Defender Exploit Guard\\Network Protection\\EnableNetworkProtection'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\nCriteria        :   false (All child tests must be true. (AND)) (negated)\nTest            :     true (Verifies the version is v1709 or greater)\n"},{"security_override_guidance":"","group_title":"SRG-APP-000207","third_party_tools":"","rule_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must be configured for automatic remediation action to be taken for threat alert level High.","rule_id":"SV-213464r961086","weight":"10.0","stig_uuid":"7387268B-722B-1014-941A-E212739FAB8B","ccis":["CCI-001662"],"ia_controls":"","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000207","id":"V-213464"},"group_id":"V-213464","mitigations":"","documentable":"false","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Microsoft Defender Antivirus &gt;&gt; Threats &gt;&gt; \"Specify threat alert levels at which default action should not be taken when detected\" to \"Enabled\". \n\nSelect the \"Showâ¦\" option box and enter \"4\" in the \"Value name\" field and enter \"2\" in the \"Value\" field.","rule_id_src":"SV-213464r961086_rule","status":"open","group_id_src":"V-213464","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.defenderantivirus:def:40","href":"U_MS_Defender_Antivirus_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV13-oval.xml"},"reference_identifier":"3985","classification":"Unclassified","potential_impacts":"","severity":"medium","responsibility":"","comments":null,"rule_version":"WNDF-AV-000040","check_content":"Verify the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Microsoft Defender Antivirus &gt;&gt; Threats &gt;&gt; \"Specify threat alert levels at which default action should not be taken when detected\" is set to \"Enabled\". \n\nClick the \"Showâ¦\" box option and verify the \"Value name\" field contains a value of \"4\" and the \"Value\" field  contains a \"2\". A value of \"3\" in the \"Value\" field is more restrictive and also an acceptable value.\n  \nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \nHKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Threats\\ThreatSeverityDefaultAction\n\nCriteria: If the value \"4\" is REG_SZ = 2 (or 3), this is not a finding.","false_positives":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-94669","V-79965"],"uuid":"738E4E3F-722B-1014-A8C0-F0952BEE4A86","discussion":"This policy setting allows the customization of which automatic remediation action will be taken for each threat alert level. Threat alert levels should be added under the Options for this setting. Each entry must be listed as a name value pair. The name defines a threat alert level. The value contains the action ID for the remediation action that should be taken. \n\nValid threat alert levels are:  \n1 = Low  \n2 =  Medium  \n4 = High  \n5 = Severe  \n\nValid remediation action values are: \n2 = Quarantine  \n3 = Remove  \n6 = Ignore","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-04-01T11:54:19\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Windows Components\\Microsoft Defender Antivirus\\Threats\\Specify threat alert levels at which default action should not be taken when detected-High)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Threats\\ThreatSeverityDefaultAction\\4'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n"},{"security_override_guidance":"","group_title":"SRG-APP-000207","third_party_tools":"","rule_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must be configured for automatic remediation action to be taken for threat alert level Medium.","rule_id":"SV-213465r961086","weight":"10.0","stig_uuid":"7387268B-722B-1014-941A-E212739FAB8B","ccis":["CCI-001662"],"ia_controls":"","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000207","id":"V-213465"},"group_id":"V-213465","mitigations":"","documentable":"false","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Microsoft Defender Antivirus &gt;&gt; Threats &gt;&gt; \"Specify threat alert levels at which default action should not be taken when detected\" to \"Enabled\".  \n\nSelect the \"Showâ¦\" option box and enter \"2\" in the \"Value name\" field and enter \"2\" in the \"Value\" field.","rule_id_src":"SV-213465r961086_rule","status":"open","group_id_src":"V-213465","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.defenderantivirus:def:41","href":"U_MS_Defender_Antivirus_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV13-oval.xml"},"reference_identifier":"3985","classification":"Unclassified","potential_impacts":"","severity":"medium","responsibility":"","comments":null,"rule_version":"WNDF-AV-000041","check_content":"Verify the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Microsoft Defender Antivirus &gt;&gt; Threats &gt;&gt; \"Specify threat alert levels at which default action should not be taken when detected\" is set to \"Enabled\". \n\nClick the \"Showâ¦\" box option and verify the \"Value name\" field contains a value of \"2\" and the \"Value\" field  contains a \"2\". A value of \"3\" in the \"Value\" field is more restrictive and also an acceptable value.\n  \nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \nHKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Threats\\ThreatSeverityDefaultAction\n\nCriteria: If the value \"2\" is REG_SZ = 2 (or 3), this is not a finding.","false_positives":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-94671","V-79967"],"uuid":"738E5804-722B-1014-A63D-CE9883B84400","discussion":"This policy setting allows the customization of which automatic remediation action will be taken for each threat alert level. Threat alert levels should be added under the Options for this setting. Each entry must be listed as a name value pair. The name defines a threat alert level. The value contains the action ID for the remediation action that should be taken. \n\nValid threat alert levels are:  \n1 = Low  \n2 =  Medium  \n4 = High  \n5 = Severe  \n\nValid remediation action values are: \n2 = Quarantine  \n3 = Remove  \n6 = Ignore","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-04-01T11:54:19\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Windows Components\\Microsoft Defender Antivirus\\Threats\\Specify threat alert levels at which default action should not be taken when detected-Medium)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Threats\\ThreatSeverityDefaultAction\\2'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n"},{"security_override_guidance":"","group_title":"SRG-APP-000207","third_party_tools":"","rule_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must be configured for automatic remediation action to be taken for threat alert level Low.","rule_id":"SV-213466r961086","weight":"10.0","stig_uuid":"7387268B-722B-1014-941A-E212739FAB8B","ccis":["CCI-001662"],"ia_controls":"","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000207","id":"V-213466"},"group_id":"V-213466","mitigations":"","documentable":"false","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Microsoft Defender Antivirus &gt;&gt; Threats &gt;&gt; \"Specify threat alert levels at which default action should not be taken when detected\" to \"Enabled\".  \n\nSelect the \"Showâ¦\" option box and enter \"1\" in the \"Value name\" field and enter \"2\" in the \"Value\" field.","rule_id_src":"SV-213466r961086_rule","status":"open","group_id_src":"V-213466","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.defenderantivirus:def:42","href":"U_MS_Defender_Antivirus_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV13-oval.xml"},"reference_identifier":"3985","classification":"Unclassified","potential_impacts":"","severity":"medium","responsibility":"","comments":null,"rule_version":"WNDF-AV-000042","check_content":"Verify the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Microsoft Defender Antivirus &gt;&gt; Threats &gt;&gt; \"Specify threat alert levels at which default action should not be taken when detected\" is set to \"Enabled\".  \n\nClick the \"Showâ¦\" box option and verify the \"Value name\" field contains a value of \"1\" and the \"Value\" field  contains a \"2\".  A value of \"3\" in the \"Value\" field is more restrictive and also an acceptable value.\n  \nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \nHKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Threats\\ThreatSeverityDefaultAction\n\nCriteria: If the value \"1\" is REG_SZ = 2 (or 3), this is not a finding.","false_positives":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-94675","V-79971"],"uuid":"738E6199-722B-1014-9B2C-898DCE72911F","discussion":"This policy setting allows the customization of which automatic remediation action will be taken for each threat alert level. Threat alert levels should be added under the Options for this setting. Each entry must be listed as a name value pair. The name defines a threat alert level. The value contains the action ID for the remediation action that should be taken. \n\nValid threat alert levels are:  \n1 = Low  \n2 =  Medium  \n4 = High \n5 = Severe  \n\nValid remediation action values are: \n2 = Quarantine  \n3 = Remove  \n6 = Ignore","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-04-01T11:54:19\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Windows Components\\Microsoft Defender Antivirus\\Threats\\Specify threat alert levels at which default action should not be taken when detected-Low)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Threats\\ThreatSeverityDefaultAction\\1'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n"},{"security_override_guidance":"","group_title":"SRG-APP-000210","third_party_tools":"","rule_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must block Adobe Reader from creating child processes.","rule_id":"SV-278647r1144030","weight":"10.0","stig_uuid":"7387268B-722B-1014-941A-E212739FAB8B","ccis":["CCI-001170"],"ia_controls":"","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000210","id":"V-278647"},"group_id":"V-278647","mitigations":"","documentable":"false","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Microsoft Defender Antivirus &gt;&gt; Microsoft Defender Exploit Guard &gt;&gt; Attack Surface Reduction &gt;&gt; Configure Attack Surface Reduction rules to \"Enabled\".\n\nUnder the policy option \"Set the state for each ASR rule:\", then click \"Show\".\n\nEnter GUID \"7674ba52-37eb-4a4f-a9a1-f0f9a1619a2c\" in the \"Value Name\" column.\n\nEnter \"1\" in the \"Value\" column.\n\nClick \"OK\".\n\nClick \"Apply\".","rule_id_src":"SV-278647r1144030_rule","status":"open","group_id_src":"V-278647","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windowsdefav:def:278647","href":"U_MS_Defender_Antivirus_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV13-oval.xml"},"reference_identifier":"3985","classification":"Unclassified","potential_impacts":"","severity":"medium","responsibility":"","comments":null,"rule_version":"WNDF-AV-000043","check_content":"Verify the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Microsoft Defender Antivirus &gt;&gt; Microsoft Defender Exploit Guard &gt;&gt; Attack Surface Reduction &gt;&gt; Configure Attack Surface Reduction rules is set to \"Enabled\".\n\nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \nHKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Windows Defender Exploit Guard\\ASR\\Rules\n\nCriteria: If the value \"7674ba52-37eb-4a4f-a9a1-f0f9a1619a2c\" is REG_SZ = 1, this is not a finding.\n\nIf the value is other than 1, this is a finding.","false_positives":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"uuid":"738E6B40-722B-1014-9D1E-FB69C8B3ADC7","discussion":"This policy setting prevents Adobe Reader from launching other processes, which can help mitigate security risks associated with malicious PDF files.","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-04-01T11:54:19\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (7674ba52-37eb-4a4f-a9a1-f0f9a1619a2c == 1)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Windows Defender Exploit Guard\\ASR\\Rules\\7674ba52-37eb-4a4f-a9a1-f0f9a1619a2c'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n"},{"security_override_guidance":"","group_title":"SRG-APP-000210","third_party_tools":"","rule_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must block credential stealing from the Windows local security authority subsystem.","rule_id":"SV-278648r1144032","weight":"10.0","stig_uuid":"7387268B-722B-1014-941A-E212739FAB8B","ccis":["CCI-001170"],"ia_controls":"","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000210","id":"V-278648"},"group_id":"V-278648","mitigations":"","documentable":"false","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Microsoft Defender Antivirus &gt;&gt; Microsoft Defender Exploit Guard &gt;&gt; Attack Surface Reduction &gt;&gt; Configure Attack Surface Reduction rules to \"Enabled\".\n\nUnder the policy option \"Set the state for each ASR rule:\", then click \"Show\".\n\nEnter GUID \"9e6c4e1f-7d60-472f-ba1a-a39ef669e4b2\" in the \"Value Name\" column.\n\nEnter \"1\" in the \"Value\" column.\n\nClick \"OK\".\n\nClick \"Apply\".","rule_id_src":"SV-278648r1144032_rule","status":"open","group_id_src":"V-278648","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windowsdefav:def:278648","href":"U_MS_Defender_Antivirus_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV13-oval.xml"},"reference_identifier":"3985","classification":"Unclassified","potential_impacts":"","severity":"medium","responsibility":"","comments":null,"rule_version":"WNDF-AV-000044","check_content":"Verify the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Microsoft Defender Antivirus &gt;&gt; Microsoft Defender Exploit Guard &gt;&gt; Attack Surface Reduction &gt;&gt; Configure Attack Surface Reduction rules is set to \"Enabled\".\n\nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \nHKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Windows Defender Exploit Guard\\ASR\\Rules\n\nCriteria: If the value \"9e6c4e1f-7d60-472f-ba1a-a39ef669e4b2\" is REG_SZ = 1, this is not a finding.\n\nIf the value is other than 1, this is a finding.","false_positives":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"uuid":"738E7541-722B-1014-BA39-8C393E1EE173","discussion":"This policy setting helps prevent credential stealing by locking down Local Security Authority Subsystem Service (LSASS). ","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-04-01T11:54:19\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (9e6c4e1f-7d60-472f-ba1a-a39ef669e4b2 == 1)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Windows Defender Exploit Guard\\ASR\\Rules\\9e6c4e1f-7d60-472f-ba1a-a39ef669e4b2'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n"},{"security_override_guidance":"","group_title":"SRG-APP-000210","third_party_tools":"","rule_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must block untrusted and unsigned processes that run from USB.","rule_id":"SV-278649r1144034","weight":"10.0","stig_uuid":"7387268B-722B-1014-941A-E212739FAB8B","ccis":["CCI-001170"],"ia_controls":"","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000210","id":"V-278649"},"group_id":"V-278649","mitigations":"","documentable":"false","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Microsoft Defender Antivirus &gt;&gt; Microsoft Defender Exploit Guard &gt;&gt; Attack Surface Reduction &gt;&gt; Configure Attack Surface Reduction rules to \"Enabled\".\n\nUnder the policy option \"Set the state for each ASR rule:\", then click \"Show\".\n\nEnter GUID \"b2b3f03d-6a65-4f7b-a9c7-1c7ef74a9ba4\" in the \"Value Name\" column.\n\nEnter \"1\" in the \"Value\" column.\n\nClick \"OK\".\n\nClick \"Apply\".","rule_id_src":"SV-278649r1144034_rule","status":"open","group_id_src":"V-278649","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windowsdefav:def:278649","href":"U_MS_Defender_Antivirus_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV13-oval.xml"},"reference_identifier":"3985","classification":"Unclassified","potential_impacts":"","severity":"medium","responsibility":"","comments":null,"rule_version":"WNDF-AV-000045","check_content":"Verify the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Microsoft Defender Antivirus &gt;&gt; Microsoft Defender Exploit Guard &gt;&gt; Attack Surface Reduction &gt;&gt; Configure Attack Surface Reduction rules is set to \"Enabled\".\n\nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \nHKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Windows Defender Exploit Guard\\ASR\\Rules\n\nCriteria: If the value \"b2b3f03d-6a65-4f7b-a9c7-1c7ef74a9ba4\" is REG_SZ = 1, this is not a finding.\n\nIf the value is other than 1, this is a finding.","false_positives":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"uuid":"738E7EA6-722B-1014-AA83-A92AE1BAFEF7","discussion":"This policy setting helps prevents unsigned or untrusted executable files from running from USB removable drives, including SD cards. Blocked file types include executable files (such as .exe, .dll, or .scr). ","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-04-01T11:54:19\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (b2b3f03d-6a65-4f7b-a9c7-1c7ef74a9ba4 == 1)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Windows Defender Exploit Guard\\ASR\\Rules\\b2b3f03d-6a65-4f7b-a9c7-1c7ef74a9ba4'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n"},{"security_override_guidance":"","group_title":"SRG-APP-000210","third_party_tools":"","rule_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must use advanced protection against ransomware.","rule_id":"SV-278650r1144036","weight":"10.0","stig_uuid":"7387268B-722B-1014-941A-E212739FAB8B","ccis":["CCI-001170"],"ia_controls":"","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000210","id":"V-278650"},"group_id":"V-278650","mitigations":"","documentable":"false","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Microsoft Defender Antivirus &gt;&gt; Microsoft Defender Exploit Guard &gt;&gt; Attack Surface Reduction &gt;&gt; Configure Attack Surface Reduction rules to \"Enabled\".\n\nUnder the policy option \"Set the state for each ASR rule:\", then click \"Show\".\n\nEnter GUID \"c1db55ab-c21a-4637-bb3f-a12568109d35\" in the \"Value Name\" column.\n\nEnter \"1\" in the \"Value\" column.\n\nClick \"OK\".\n\nClick \"Apply\".","rule_id_src":"SV-278650r1144036_rule","status":"open","group_id_src":"V-278650","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windowsdefav:def:278650","href":"U_MS_Defender_Antivirus_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV13-oval.xml"},"reference_identifier":"3985","classification":"Unclassified","potential_impacts":"","severity":"medium","responsibility":"","comments":null,"rule_version":"WNDF-AV-000046","check_content":"Verify the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Microsoft Defender Antivirus &gt;&gt; Microsoft Defender Exploit Guard &gt;&gt; Attack Surface Reduction &gt;&gt; Configure Attack Surface Reduction rules is set to \"Enabled\".\n\nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \nHKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Windows Defender Exploit Guard\\ASR\\Rules\n\nCriteria: If the value \"c1db55ab-c21a-4637-bb3f-a12568109d35\" is REG_SZ = 1, this is not a finding.\n\nIf the value is other than 1, this is a finding.","false_positives":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"uuid":"738E87ED-722B-1014-B183-B6F2115BCCE2","discussion":"This policy setting provides an extra layer of protection against ransomware. It uses both client and cloud heuristics to determine whether a file resembles ransomware. \nThis rule doesn't block files that have one or more of the following characteristics:\n\n- The file is found to be unharmful in the Microsoft cloud.\n- The file is a valid signed file.\n-  The file is prevalent enough to not be considered as ransomware.\n- The rule tends to err on the side of caution to prevent ransomware. ","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-04-01T11:54:19\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (c1db55ab-c21a-4637-bb3f-a12568109d35 == 1)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Windows Defender Exploit Guard\\ASR\\Rules\\c1db55ab-c21a-4637-bb3f-a12568109d35'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n"},{"security_override_guidance":"","group_title":"SRG-APP-000210","third_party_tools":"","rule_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must block process creations originating from PSExec and WMI commands.","rule_id":"SV-278651r1144039","weight":"10.0","stig_uuid":"7387268B-722B-1014-941A-E212739FAB8B","ccis":["CCI-001170"],"ia_controls":"","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000210","id":"V-278651"},"group_id":"V-278651","mitigations":"","documentable":"false","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Microsoft Defender Antivirus &gt;&gt; Microsoft Defender Exploit Guard &gt;&gt; Attack Surface Reduction &gt;&gt; Configure Attack Surface Reduction rules to \"Enabled\".\n\nUnder the policy option \"Set the state for each ASR rule:\", then click \"Show\".\n\nEnter GUID \"d1e49aac-8f56-4280-b9ba-993a6d77406c\" in the \"Value Name\" column.\n\nEnter \"2\" in the \"Value\" column.\n\nClick \"OK\".\n\nClick \"Apply\".","rule_id_src":"SV-278651r1144039_rule","status":"open","group_id_src":"V-278651","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windowsdefav:def:278651","href":"U_MS_Defender_Antivirus_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV13-oval.xml"},"reference_identifier":"3985","classification":"Unclassified","potential_impacts":"","severity":"medium","responsibility":"","comments":null,"rule_version":"WNDF-AV-000047","check_content":"Verify the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Microsoft Defender Antivirus &gt;&gt; Microsoft Defender Exploit Guard &gt;&gt; Attack Surface Reduction &gt;&gt; Configure Attack Surface Reduction rules is set to \"Enabled\".\n\nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \nHKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Windows Defender Exploit Guard\\ASR\\Rules\n\nCriteria: If the value \"d1e49aac-8f56-4280-b9ba-993a6d77406c\" is REG_SZ = 2, this is not a finding.\n\nIf the value is other than 2, this is a finding.","false_positives":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"uuid":"738E9134-722B-1014-88DE-A18BB2AFAC6C","discussion":"This policy setting blocks processes created through PsExec and WMI from running. Both PsExec and WMI can remotely execute code. There is a risk of malware abusing functionality of PsExec and WMI for command and control purposes, or to spread an infection throughout an organization's network.","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-04-01T11:54:19\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (d1e49aac-8f56-4280-b9ba-993a6d77406c == 2)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Windows Defender Exploit Guard\\ASR\\Rules\\d1e49aac-8f56-4280-b9ba-993a6d77406c'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n"},{"security_override_guidance":"","group_title":"SRG-APP-000210","third_party_tools":"","rule_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must block persistence through WMI event subscription.","rule_id":"SV-278652r1144042","weight":"10.0","stig_uuid":"7387268B-722B-1014-941A-E212739FAB8B","ccis":["CCI-001170"],"ia_controls":"","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000210","id":"V-278652"},"group_id":"V-278652","mitigations":"","documentable":"false","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Microsoft Defender Antivirus &gt;&gt; Microsoft Defender Exploit Guard &gt;&gt; Attack Surface Reduction &gt;&gt; Configure Attack Surface Reduction rules to \"Enabled\".\n\nUnder the policy option \"Set the state for each ASR rule:\", then click \"Show\".\n\nEnter GUID \"e6db77e5-3df2-4cf1-b95a-636979351e5b\" in the \"Value Name\" column.\n\nEnter \"2\" in the \"Value\" column.\n\nClick \"OK\".\n\nClick \"Apply\".","rule_id_src":"SV-278652r1144042_rule","status":"open","group_id_src":"V-278652","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windowsdefav:def:278652","href":"U_MS_Defender_Antivirus_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV13-oval.xml"},"reference_identifier":"3985","classification":"Unclassified","potential_impacts":"","severity":"medium","responsibility":"","comments":null,"rule_version":"WNDF-AV-000048","check_content":"Verify the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Microsoft Defender Antivirus &gt;&gt; Microsoft Defender Exploit Guard &gt;&gt; Attack Surface Reduction &gt;&gt; Configure Attack Surface Reduction rules is set to \"Enabled\".\n\nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \nHKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Windows Defender Exploit Guard\\ASR\\Rules\n\nCriteria: If the value \"e6db77e5-3df2-4cf1-b95a-636979351e5b\" is REG_SZ = 2, this is not a finding.\n\nIf the value is other than 2, this is a finding.","false_positives":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"uuid":"738E9A75-722B-1014-A1EA-B745FC4AEA3A","discussion":"This policy setting prevents malware from abusing WMI to attain persistence on a device.\n\nFileless threats employ various tactics to stay hidden, to avoid being seen in the file system, and to gain periodic execution control. Some threats can abuse the WMI repository and event model to stay hidden.","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-04-01T11:54:19\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (e6db77e5-3df2-4cf1-b95a-636979351e5b == 2)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Windows Defender Exploit Guard\\ASR\\Rules\\c1db55ab-c21a-4637-bb3f-a12568109d35'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n"},{"security_override_guidance":"","group_title":"SRG-APP-000210","third_party_tools":"","rule_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must block executable files from running unless they meet a prevalence, age, or trusted list criterion.","rule_id":"SV-278653r1144045","weight":"10.0","stig_uuid":"7387268B-722B-1014-941A-E212739FAB8B","ccis":["CCI-001170"],"ia_controls":"","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000210","id":"V-278653"},"group_id":"V-278653","mitigations":"","documentable":"false","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Microsoft Defender Antivirus &gt;&gt; Microsoft Defender Exploit Guard &gt;&gt; Attack Surface Reduction &gt;&gt; Configure Attack Surface Reduction rules to \"Enabled\".\n\nUnder the policy option \"Set the state for each ASR rule:\", then click \"Show\".\n\nEnter GUID \"01443614-cd74-433a-b99e-2ecdc07bfc25\" in the \"Value Name\" column.\n\nEnter \"2\" in the \"Value\" column.\n\nClick \"OK\".\n\nClick \"Apply\".","rule_id_src":"SV-278653r1144045_rule","status":"open","group_id_src":"V-278653","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windowsdefav:def:278653","href":"U_MS_Defender_Antivirus_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV13-oval.xml"},"reference_identifier":"3985","classification":"Unclassified","potential_impacts":"","severity":"medium","responsibility":"","comments":null,"rule_version":"WNDF-AV-000049","check_content":"Verify the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Microsoft Defender Antivirus &gt;&gt; Microsoft Defender Exploit Guard &gt;&gt; Attack Surface Reduction &gt;&gt; Configure Attack Surface Reduction rules is set to \"Enabled\".\n\nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \nHKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Windows Defender Exploit Guard\\ASR\\Rules\n\nCriteria: If the value \"01443614-cd74-433a-b99e-2ecdc07bfc25\" is REG_SZ = 2, this is not a finding.\n\nIf the value is other than 2, this is a finding.","false_positives":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"uuid":"738EA3F3-722B-1014-8CDD-DC8A90A79771","discussion":"This policy setting blocks executable files, such as .exe, .dll, or .scr, from launching. Thus, launching untrusted or unknown executable files can be risky, as it might not be initially clear if the files are malicious.","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-04-01T11:54:19\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (01443614-cd74-433a-b99e-2ecdc07bfc25 == 2)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Windows Defender Exploit Guard\\ASR\\Rules\\01443614-cd74-433a-b99e-2ecdc07bfc25'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n"},{"security_override_guidance":"","group_title":"SRG-APP-000210","third_party_tools":"","rule_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must block Office communication application from creating child processes.","rule_id":"SV-278654r1144047","weight":"10.0","stig_uuid":"7387268B-722B-1014-941A-E212739FAB8B","ccis":["CCI-001170"],"ia_controls":"","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000210","id":"V-278654"},"group_id":"V-278654","mitigations":"","documentable":"false","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Microsoft Defender Antivirus &gt;&gt; Microsoft Defender Exploit Guard &gt;&gt; Attack Surface Reduction &gt;&gt; Configure Attack Surface Reduction rules to \"Enabled\".\n\nUnder the policy option \"Set the state for each ASR rule:\", then click \"Show\".\n\nEnter GUID \"26190899-1602-49e8-8b27-eb1d0a1ce869\" in the \"Value Name\" column.\n\nEnter \"1\" in the \"Value\" column.\n\nClick \"OK\".\n\nClick \"Apply\".","rule_id_src":"SV-278654r1144047_rule","status":"open","group_id_src":"V-278654","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windowsdefav:def:278654","href":"U_MS_Defender_Antivirus_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV13-oval.xml"},"reference_identifier":"3985","classification":"Unclassified","potential_impacts":"","severity":"medium","responsibility":"","comments":null,"rule_version":"WNDF-AV-000050","check_content":"Verify the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Microsoft Defender Antivirus &gt;&gt; Microsoft Defender Exploit Guard &gt;&gt; Attack Surface Reduction &gt;&gt; Configure Attack Surface Reduction rules is set to \"Enabled\".\n\nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \nHKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Windows Defender Exploit Guard\\ASR\\Rules\n\nCriteria: If the value \"26190899-1602-49e8-8b27-eb1d0a1ce869\" is REG_SZ = 1, this is not a finding.\n\nIf the value is other than 1, this is a finding.","false_positives":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"uuid":"738EAD7B-722B-1014-AF71-E92BFF5F2D18","discussion":"This policy setting prevents Outlook from creating child processes while still allowing legitimate Outlook functions. This rule protects against social engineering attacks and prevents exploiting code from abusing vulnerabilities in Outlook. It also protects against Outlook rules and forms exploits that attackers can use when a user's credentials are compromised.","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-04-01T11:54:19\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (26190899-1602-49e8-8b27-eb1d0a1ce869 == 1)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Windows Defender Exploit Guard\\ASR\\Rules\\26190899-1602-49e8-8b27-eb1d0a1ce869'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n"},{"security_override_guidance":"","group_title":"SRG-APP-000210","third_party_tools":"","rule_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must block abuse of exploited vulnerable signed drivers.","rule_id":"SV-278655r1144049","weight":"10.0","stig_uuid":"7387268B-722B-1014-941A-E212739FAB8B","ccis":["CCI-001170"],"ia_controls":"","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000210","id":"V-278655"},"group_id":"V-278655","mitigations":"","documentable":"false","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Microsoft Defender Antivirus &gt;&gt; Microsoft Defender Exploit Guard &gt;&gt; Attack Surface Reduction &gt;&gt; Configure Attack Surface Reduction rules to \"Enabled\".\n\nUnder the policy option \"Set the state for each ASR rule:\", then click \"Show\".\n\nEnter GUID \"56a863a9-875e-4185-98a7-b882c64b5ce5\" in the \"Value Name\" column.\n\nEnter \"1\" in the \"Value\" column.\n\nClick \"OK\".\n\nClick \"Apply\".","rule_id_src":"SV-278655r1144049_rule","status":"open","group_id_src":"V-278655","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windowsdefav:def:278655","href":"U_MS_Defender_Antivirus_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV13-oval.xml"},"reference_identifier":"3985","classification":"Unclassified","potential_impacts":"","severity":"medium","responsibility":"","comments":null,"rule_version":"WNDF-AV-000051","check_content":"Verify the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Microsoft Defender Antivirus &gt;&gt; Microsoft Defender Exploit Guard &gt;&gt; Attack Surface Reduction &gt;&gt; Configure Attack Surface Reduction rules is set to \"Enabled\".\n\nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \nHKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Windows Defender Exploit Guard\\ASR\\Rules\n\nCriteria: If the value \"56a863a9-875e-4185-98a7-b882c64b5ce5\" is REG_SZ = 1, this is not a finding.\n\nIf the value is other than 1, this is a finding.","false_positives":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"uuid":"738EB72B-722B-1014-8C59-D5825F0A05AE","discussion":"This policy setting prevents an application from writing a vulnerable signed driver to disk. Vulnerable signed drivers can be exploited by local applications that have sufficient privileges to gain access to the kernel. Vulnerable signed drivers enable attackers to disable or circumvent security solutions, eventually leading to system compromise.\n\nThe Block abuse of exploited vulnerable signed drivers rule does not block a driver already existing on the system from being loaded.","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-04-01T11:54:19\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (56a863a9-875e-4185-98a7-b882c64b5ce5 == 1)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Windows Defender Exploit Guard\\ASR\\Rules\\56a863a9-875e-4185-98a7-b882c64b5ce5'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n"},{"security_override_guidance":"","group_title":"SRG-APP-000210","third_party_tools":"","rule_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must configure local administrator merge behavior for lists.","rule_id":"SV-278656r1144051","weight":"10.0","stig_uuid":"7387268B-722B-1014-941A-E212739FAB8B","ccis":["CCI-001170"],"ia_controls":"","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000210","id":"V-278656"},"group_id":"V-278656","mitigations":"","documentable":"false","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Microsoft Defender Antivirus  &gt;&gt; Configure local administrator merge behavior for lists to \"Enabled\".\n\nClick \"OK\".\n\nClick \"Apply\".","rule_id_src":"SV-278656r1144051_rule","status":"open","group_id_src":"V-278656","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windowsdefav:def:278656","href":"U_MS_Defender_Antivirus_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV13-oval.xml"},"reference_identifier":"3985","classification":"Unclassified","potential_impacts":"","severity":"medium","responsibility":"","comments":null,"rule_version":"WNDF-AV-000052","check_content":"Verify the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Microsoft Defender Antivirus &gt;&gt; Configure local administrator merge behavior for lists is set to \"Enabled\". Otherwise, this is a finding.\n\nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \nHKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\n\nCriteria: If the value \"DisableLocalAdminMerge\" is REG_DWORD = 1, this is not a finding.\n\nIf the value is 0, this is a finding.","false_positives":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"uuid":"738EC0A9-722B-1014-9AE9-D30CDFB7AFB9","discussion":"This policy setting configures how locally defined lists are combined or merged with globally defined lists. This setting applies to exclusion lists, specified remediation lists, and attack surface reduction.","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-04-01T11:54:19\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false ('Local administrator merge behavior for lists' is 'Enabled')\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\DisableLocalAdminMerge'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n"},{"security_override_guidance":"","group_title":"SRG-APP-000210","third_party_tools":"","rule_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must control whether exclusions are visible to Local Admins.","rule_id":"SV-278658r1156519","weight":"10.0","stig_uuid":"7387268B-722B-1014-941A-E212739FAB8B","ccis":["CCI-001170"],"ia_controls":"","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000210","id":"V-278658"},"group_id":"V-278658","mitigations":"","documentable":"false","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Microsoft Defender Antivirus &gt;&gt; Control whether or not exclusions are visible to Local Admins to \"Enabled\".\n\nClick \"OK\".\n\nClick \"Apply\".","rule_id_src":"SV-278658r1156519_rule","status":"open","group_id_src":"V-278658","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windowsdefav:def:278658","href":"U_MS_Defender_Antivirus_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV13-oval.xml"},"reference_identifier":"3985","classification":"Unclassified","potential_impacts":"","severity":"medium","responsibility":"","comments":null,"rule_version":"WNDF-AV-000054","check_content":"Verify the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Microsoft Defender Antivirus &gt;&gt; Control whether or not exclusions are visible to Local Admins is set to \"Enabled\"; otherwise, this is a finding.\n\nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \nHKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\n\nCriteria: If the value \"HideExclusionsFromLocalAdmins\" is REG_DWORD = 1, this is not a finding.\n\nIf the value is \"0\", this is a finding.","false_positives":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"uuid":"738EC99F-722B-1014-A5D4-D9A5CFCD5E31","discussion":"Disabled (Default): If this setting is not configured or disabled, local admins can see exclusions in the Windows Security App or via PowerShell.\n\nEnabled: If this setting is enabled, local admins no longer see the exclusion list in Windows Security App or via PowerShell.O13.\n\nNote: Applying this setting will not remove exclusions, it only prevents them from being visible to local admins. This is reflected in?Get-MpPreference.I13.","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-04-01T11:54:19\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false ('Control whether or not exclusions are visible to Local Admins' is 'Enabled')\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\HideExclusionsFromLocalAdmins'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n"},{"security_override_guidance":"","group_title":"SRG-APP-000278","third_party_tools":"","rule_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must randomize scheduled task times.","rule_id":"SV-278659r1144055","weight":"10.0","stig_uuid":"7387268B-722B-1014-941A-E212739FAB8B","ccis":["CCI-001242"],"ia_controls":"","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000278","id":"V-278659"},"group_id":"V-278659","mitigations":"","documentable":"false","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Microsoft Defender Antivirus &gt;&gt; Randomize scheduled task times to \"Enabled\".\n\nClick \"OK\".\n\nClick \"Apply\".","rule_id_src":"SV-278659r1144055_rule","status":"open","group_id_src":"V-278659","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windowsdefav:def:278659","href":"U_MS_Defender_Antivirus_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV13-oval.xml"},"reference_identifier":"3985","classification":"Unclassified","potential_impacts":"","severity":"medium","responsibility":"","comments":null,"rule_version":"WNDF-AV-000055","check_content":"Verify the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Microsoft Defender Antivirus &gt;&gt; Randomize scheduled task times is set to \"Enabled\"; otherwise, this is a finding.\n\nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \nHKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\n\nCriteria: If the value \"RandomizeScheduleTaskTimes\" is REG_DWORD = 1, this is not a finding.\n\nIf the value is 0, this is a finding.","false_positives":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"uuid":"738ED3A1-722B-1014-ADF1-C7B662F5713C","discussion":"In Microsoft Defender Antivirus, randomize the start time of the scan to any interval from 0 to 23 hours. By default, scheduled tasks begin at a random time within four hours of the time specified in Task Scheduler.","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-04-01T11:54:19\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false ('Randomize scheduled task times' is 'Enabled')\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\RandomizeScheduleTaskTimes'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n"},{"security_override_guidance":"","group_title":"SRG-APP-000210","third_party_tools":"","rule_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must hide the Family options area.","rule_id":"SV-278660r1144057","weight":"10.0","stig_uuid":"7387268B-722B-1014-941A-E212739FAB8B","ccis":["CCI-001170"],"ia_controls":"","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000210","id":"V-278660"},"group_id":"V-278660","mitigations":"","documentable":"false","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Windows Security &gt;&gt; Family Options &gt;&gt; Hide the Family options area to \"Enabled\".\n\nClick \"OK\".\n\nClick \"Apply\".","rule_id_src":"SV-278660r1144057_rule","status":"open","group_id_src":"V-278660","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windowsdefav:def:278660","href":"U_MS_Defender_Antivirus_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV13-oval.xml"},"reference_identifier":"3985","classification":"Unclassified","potential_impacts":"","severity":"medium","responsibility":"","comments":null,"rule_version":"WNDF-AV-000056","check_content":"Verify the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Windows Security &gt;&gt; Family Options &gt;&gt; Hide the Family options area is set to \"Enabled\"; otherwise, this is a finding.\n\nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \nHKLM\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender Security Center\\Family options\n\nCriteria: If the value \"UILockdown\" is REG_DWORD = 1, this is not a finding.\n\nIf the value is 0, this is a finding.","false_positives":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"uuid":"738EDCE8-722B-1014-B4F0-AC8A85E8DA60","discussion":"The Family options section contains links to settings and further information for parents of a Windows PC. It is not intended for enterprise or business environments.\n\nThis section can be hidden from users of the machine. This option can be useful if you do not want users in the organization to see or have access to this section.","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-04-01T11:54:19\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false ('Hide the Family options area' is 'Enabled')\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender Security Center\\Family options\\UILockdown'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n"},{"security_override_guidance":"","group_title":"SRG-APP-000210","third_party_tools":"","rule_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must enable the file hash computation feature.","rule_id":"SV-278661r1144059","weight":"10.0","stig_uuid":"7387268B-722B-1014-941A-E212739FAB8B","ccis":["CCI-001170"],"ia_controls":"","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000210","id":"V-278661"},"group_id":"V-278661","mitigations":"","documentable":"false","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Microsoft Defender Antivirus &gt;&gt; MpEngine &gt;&gt;Enable file hash computation feature to \"Enabled\".\n\nClick \"OK\".\n\nClick \"Apply\".","rule_id_src":"SV-278661r1144059_rule","status":"open","group_id_src":"V-278661","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windowsdefav:def:278661","href":"U_MS_Defender_Antivirus_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV13-oval.xml"},"reference_identifier":"3985","classification":"Unclassified","potential_impacts":"","severity":"medium","responsibility":"","comments":null,"rule_version":"WNDF-AV-000057","check_content":"Verify the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Microsoft Defender Antivirus &gt;&gt; MpEngine &gt;&gt; Enable file hash computation feature is set to \"Enabled\"; otherwise, this is a finding.\n\nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \nHKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\MpEngine\n\nCriteria: If the value \"EnableFileHashComputation\" is REG_DWORD = 1, this is not a finding.\n\nIf the value is 0, this is a finding.","false_positives":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"uuid":"738EE6D8-722B-1014-B420-9EB01E067C01","discussion":"This policy drives the ability to enforce Indicators of Compromise (IoC) by using file hash allow/block indicators.","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-04-01T11:54:19\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Enable file hash computation feature' is 'Enabled')\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\MpEngine\\EnableFileHashComputation'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n"},{"security_override_guidance":"","group_title":"SRG-APP-000210","third_party_tools":"","rule_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must enable extended cloud check.","rule_id":"SV-278662r1144061","weight":"10.0","stig_uuid":"7387268B-722B-1014-941A-E212739FAB8B","ccis":["CCI-001170"],"ia_controls":"","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000210","id":"V-278662"},"group_id":"V-278662","mitigations":"","documentable":"false","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Microsoft Defender Antivirus &gt;&gt; MpEngine &gt;&gt; Configure extended cloud check to \"Enabled\" with a Policy Option value of \"50\".\n\nClick \"OK\".\n\nClick \"Apply\".","rule_id_src":"SV-278662r1144061_rule","status":"open","group_id_src":"V-278662","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windowsdefav:def:278662","href":"U_MS_Defender_Antivirus_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV13-oval.xml"},"reference_identifier":"3985","classification":"Unclassified","potential_impacts":"","severity":"medium","responsibility":"","comments":null,"rule_version":"WNDF-AV-000058","check_content":"Verify the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Microsoft Defender Antivirus &gt;&gt; MpEngine &gt;&gt; Configure extended cloud check is set to \"Enabled\" with a Policy Option value of \"50\"; otherwise, this is a finding.\n\nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \nHKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\MpEngine\n\nCriteria: If the value \"MpBafsExtendedTimeout\" is REG_DWORD = 50, this is not a finding.\n\nIf the value is other than 50, this is a finding.","false_positives":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"uuid":"738EEFD5-722B-1014-A37D-9F13903BC7F4","discussion":"When Microsoft Defender Antivirus finds a suspicious file, it can prevent the file from running while it queries the Microsoft Defender Antivirus cloud service.\n\nThe default period that the file is blocked is 10 seconds. Extending the cloud block timeout period can help ensure there is enough time to receive a proper determination from the Microsoft Defender Antivirus cloud service.","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-04-01T11:54:19\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (MpBafsExtendedTimeout == 50)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\MpEngine\\MpBafsExtendedTimeout'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n"},{"security_override_guidance":"","group_title":"SRG-APP-000278","third_party_tools":"","rule_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must enable script scanning.","rule_id":"SV-278668r1144063","weight":"10.0","stig_uuid":"7387268B-722B-1014-941A-E212739FAB8B","ccis":["CCI-001242"],"ia_controls":"","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000278","id":"V-278668"},"group_id":"V-278668","mitigations":"","documentable":"false","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Microsoft Defender Antivirus &gt;&gt; Real-time Protection &gt;&gt; Turn on script scanning to \"Enabled\".\n\nClick \"OK\".\n\nClick \"Apply\".","rule_id_src":"SV-278668r1144063_rule","status":"open","group_id_src":"V-278668","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windowsdefav:def:278668","href":"U_MS_Defender_Antivirus_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV13-oval.xml"},"reference_identifier":"3985","classification":"Unclassified","potential_impacts":"","severity":"medium","responsibility":"","comments":null,"rule_version":"WNDF-AV-000064","check_content":"Verify the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Microsoft Defender Antivirus &gt;&gt; Real-time Protection &gt;&gt; Turn on script scanning is set to \"Enabled\"; otherwise, this is a finding.\n\nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \nHKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Real-Time Protection\n\nCriteria: If the value \"DisableScriptScanning\" is REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.\n\nIf the value is 1, this is a finding.","false_positives":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"uuid":"738EF986-722B-1014-924F-CFF4DA1B016F","discussion":"Always-on protection consists of real-time protection, behavior monitoring, and heuristics to identify malware based on known suspicious and malicious activities. These activities include events, such as processes making unusual changes to existing files, modifying or creating automatic startup registry keys and startup locations (also known as autostart extensibility points, or ASEPs), and other changes to the file system or file structure.","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-04-01T11:54:19\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Turn on script scanning' is 'Enabled')\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Real-Time Protection\\DisableScriptScanning'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n"},{"security_override_guidance":"","group_title":"SRG-APP-000278","third_party_tools":"","rule_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must enable real-time protection and Security Intelligence Updates during OOBE.","rule_id":"SV-278669r1144065","weight":"10.0","stig_uuid":"7387268B-722B-1014-941A-E212739FAB8B","ccis":["CCI-001242"],"ia_controls":"","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000278","id":"V-278669"},"group_id":"V-278669","mitigations":"","documentable":"false","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Microsoft Defender Antivirus &gt;&gt; Real-time Protection &gt;&gt; Configure real-time protection and Security Intelligence Updates during OOBE to \"Enabled\".\n\nClick \"OK\".\n\nClick \"Apply\".","rule_id_src":"SV-278669r1144065_rule","status":"open","group_id_src":"V-278669","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windowsdefav:def:278669","href":"U_MS_Defender_Antivirus_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV13-oval.xml"},"reference_identifier":"3985","classification":"Unclassified","potential_impacts":"","severity":"medium","responsibility":"","comments":null,"rule_version":"WNDF-AV-000065","check_content":"Verify the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Microsoft Defender Antivirus &gt;&gt; Real-time Protection &gt;&gt; Configure real-time protection and Security Intelligence Updates during OOBE is set to \"Enabled\"; otherwise, this is a finding.\n\nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \nHKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Real-Time Protection\n\nCriteria: If the value \"OobeEnableRtpAndSigUpdate\" is REG_DWORD = 1, this is not a finding.\n\nIf the value is 0, this is a finding.","false_positives":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"uuid":"738F02E9-722B-1014-840F-BFDA59262E41","discussion":"Always-on protection consists of real-time protection, behavior monitoring, and heuristics to identify malware based on known suspicious and malicious activities. These activities include events, such as processes making unusual changes to existing files, modifying or creating automatic startup registry keys and startup locations (also known as autostart extensibility points, or ASEPs), and other changes to the file system or file structure.","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-04-01T11:54:19\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Configure real-time protection and Security Intelligence Updates during OOBE' is 'Enabled')\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Real-Time Protection\\OobeEnableRtpAndSigUpdate'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n"},{"security_override_guidance":"","group_title":"SRG-APP-000210","third_party_tools":"","rule_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must enable network protection to be configured into block or audit mode on Windows Server.","rule_id":"SV-278672r1144067","weight":"10.0","stig_uuid":"7387268B-722B-1014-941A-E212739FAB8B","ccis":["CCI-001170"],"ia_controls":"","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000210","id":"V-278672"},"group_id":"V-278672","mitigations":"","documentable":"false","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Microsoft Defender Antivirus &gt;&gt; Microsoft Defender Exploit Guard &gt;&gt; Network Protection &gt;&gt; This settings controls whether Network Protection is allowed to be configured into block or audit mode on Windows Server to \"Enabled\".\n\nClick \"OK\".\n\nClick \"Apply\".","rule_id_src":"SV-278672r1144067_rule","status":"open","group_id_src":"V-278672","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windowsdefav:def:278672","href":"U_MS_Defender_Antivirus_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV13-oval.xml"},"reference_identifier":"3985","classification":"Unclassified","potential_impacts":"","severity":"medium","responsibility":"","comments":null,"rule_version":"WNDF-AV-000068","check_content":"Verify the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Microsoft Defender Antivirus &gt;&gt; Microsoft Defender Exploit Guard &gt;&gt; Network Protection &gt;&gt; This settings controls whether Network Protection is allowed to be configured into block or audit mode on Windows Server is set to \"Enabled\".\n\nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \nHKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Windows Defender Exploit Guard\\Network Protection\n\nCriteria: If the value \"AllowNetworkProtectionOnWinServer\" is REG_DWORD = 1, this is not a finding.\n\nIf the value is 0, this is a finding.","false_positives":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"uuid":"738F0CCF-722B-1014-955B-DE40EE3E1424","discussion":"Microsoft's Exploit Guard comprises several techniques to defend against phishing attacks and malware. These include controlled folder access, attack surface reduction, and network protection.","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-04-01T11:54:19\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false ('This settings controls whether Network Protection is allowed to be configured into block or audit mode on Windows Server' is 'Enabled')\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Windows Defender Exploit Guard\\Network Protection\\AllowNetworkProtectionOnWinServer'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n"},{"security_override_guidance":"","group_title":"SRG-APP-000210","third_party_tools":"","rule_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must enable EDR in block mode.","rule_id":"SV-278674r1144071","weight":"10.0","stig_uuid":"7387268B-722B-1014-941A-E212739FAB8B","ccis":["CCI-001170"],"ia_controls":"","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000210","id":"V-278674"},"group_id":"V-278674","mitigations":"","documentable":"false","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Microsoft Defender Antivirus &gt;&gt; Features &gt;&gt; Enable EDR in block mode to \"Enabled\".\n\nClick \"OK\".\n\nClick \"Apply\".","rule_id_src":"SV-278674r1144071_rule","status":"open","group_id_src":"V-278674","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windowsdefav:def:278674","href":"U_MS_Defender_Antivirus_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV13-oval.xml"},"reference_identifier":"3985","classification":"Unclassified","potential_impacts":"","severity":"medium","responsibility":"","comments":null,"rule_version":"WNDF-AV-000070","check_content":"Verify the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Microsoft Defender Antivirus &gt;&gt; Features &gt;&gt; Enable EDR in block mode is set to \"Enabled\"; otherwise, this is a finding.\n\nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \nHKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Features\n\nCriteria: If the value \"PassiveRemediation\" is REG_DWORD = 1, this is not a finding.\n\nIf the value is 0, this is a finding.","false_positives":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"uuid":"738F1627-722B-1014-8A42-9BB84ED6E3BD","discussion":"EDR in block mode allows Microsoft Defender Antivirus to take actions on post-breach, behavioral EDR detections. EDR in block mode is integrated with threat and vulnerability management capabilities. ","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-04-01T11:54:19\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (PassiveRemediation == 1)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Features\\PassiveRemediation'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n"},{"security_override_guidance":"","group_title":"SRG-APP-000210","third_party_tools":"","rule_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must report Dynamic Signature dropped events.","rule_id":"SV-278675r1144073","weight":"10.0","stig_uuid":"7387268B-722B-1014-941A-E212739FAB8B","ccis":["CCI-001170"],"ia_controls":"","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000210","id":"V-278675"},"group_id":"V-278675","mitigations":"","documentable":"false","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Microsoft Defender Antivirus &gt;&gt; Reporting &gt;&gt; Configure whether to report Dynamic Signature dropped events to \"Enabled\".\n\nClick \"OK\".\n\nClick \"Apply\".","rule_id_src":"SV-278675r1144073_rule","status":"open","group_id_src":"V-278675","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windowsdefav:def:278675","href":"U_MS_Defender_Antivirus_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV13-oval.xml"},"reference_identifier":"3985","classification":"Unclassified","potential_impacts":"","severity":"medium","responsibility":"","comments":null,"rule_version":"WNDF-AV-000071","check_content":"Verify the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Microsoft Defender Antivirus &gt;&gt; Reporting &gt;&gt; Configure whether to report Dynamic Signature dropped events is set to \"Enabled\"; otherwise, this is a finding.\n\nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \nHKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Reporting\n\nCriteria: If the value \"EnableDynamicSignatureDroppedEventReporting\" is REG_DWORD = 1, this is not a finding.\n\nIf the value is 0, this is a finding.","false_positives":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"uuid":"738F1FA5-722B-1014-9BDC-9FE765A91137","discussion":"Microsoft Defender Antivirus logs \"Dynamic Signature dropped\" events when it blocks or removes a file based on a dynamically updated signature, but the signature itself is dropped, meaning it was not fully processed or applied. This can indicate a potential issue with signature updates or the system's ability to handle them.","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-04-01T11:54:19\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (EnableDynamicSignatureDroppedEventReporting == 1)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Reporting\\EnableDynamicSignatureDroppedEventReporting'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n"},{"security_override_guidance":"","group_title":"SRG-APP-000278","third_party_tools":"","rule_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must scan excluded files and directories during quick scans.","rule_id":"SV-278676r1144075","weight":"10.0","stig_uuid":"7387268B-722B-1014-941A-E212739FAB8B","ccis":["CCI-001242"],"ia_controls":"","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000278","id":"V-278676"},"group_id":"V-278676","mitigations":"","documentable":"false","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Microsoft Defender Antivirus &gt;&gt; Scan &gt;&gt; Scan excluded files and directories during quick scans to \"Enabled\".\n\nClick \"OK\".\n\nClick \"Apply\".","rule_id_src":"SV-278676r1144075_rule","status":"open","group_id_src":"V-278676","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windowsdefav:def:278676","href":"U_MS_Defender_Antivirus_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV13-oval.xml"},"reference_identifier":"3985","classification":"Unclassified","potential_impacts":"","severity":"medium","responsibility":"","comments":null,"rule_version":"WNDF-AV-000072","check_content":"Verify the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Microsoft Defender Antivirus &gt;&gt; Scan &gt;&gt; Scan excluded files and directories during quick scans is set to \"Enabled\"; otherwise, this is a finding.\n\nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \nHKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Scan\n\nCriteria: If the value \"QuickScanIncludeExclusions\" is REG_DWORD = 1, this is not a finding.\n\nIf the value is 0, this is a finding.","false_positives":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"uuid":"738F292B-722B-1014-960F-8E4E11331B2A","discussion":"In Microsoft Defender Antivirus, when an exclusion for a file or folder is created, it will generally be skipped during both real-time protection and on-demand scans (including quick scans and full scans). However, with newer releases, the option exists to configure quick scans to include files and directories that are otherwise excluded from real-time protection.","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-04-01T11:54:19\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (QuickScanIncludeExclusions == 1)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Scan\\QuickScanIncludeExclusions'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n"},{"security_override_guidance":"","group_title":"SRG-APP-000210","third_party_tools":"","rule_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must convert warn verdict to block.","rule_id":"SV-278677r1144077","weight":"10.0","stig_uuid":"7387268B-722B-1014-941A-E212739FAB8B","ccis":["CCI-001170"],"ia_controls":"","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000210","id":"V-278677"},"group_id":"V-278677","mitigations":"","documentable":"false","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Microsoft Defender Antivirus &gt;&gt; MpEngine &gt;&gt; Convert warn verdict to block to \"Enabled\".\n\nClick \"OK\".\n\nClick \"Apply\".","rule_id_src":"SV-278677r1144077_rule","status":"open","group_id_src":"V-278677","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windowsdefav:def:278677","href":"U_MS_Defender_Antivirus_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV13-oval.xml"},"reference_identifier":"3985","classification":"Unclassified","potential_impacts":"","severity":"medium","responsibility":"","comments":null,"rule_version":"WNDF-AV-000074","check_content":"Verify the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Microsoft Defender Antivirus &gt;&gt; Network Inspection System &gt;&gt; Convert warn verdict to block is set to \"Enabled\"; otherwise, this is a finding.\n\nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \nHKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\NIS\n\nCriteria: If the value \"EnableConvertWarnToBlock\" is REG_DWORD = 1, this is not a finding.\n\nIf the value is 0, this is a finding.","false_positives":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"uuid":"738F32C5-722B-1014-9A9F-E76D8808D41F","discussion":"If a site URL has an unknown or uncertain reputation, a toast notification presents the user with the following options:\n\n- Ok: The toast notification is released (removed), and the attempt to access the site is ended.\n\n- Unblock: The user has access to the site for 24 hours, at which point the block is reenabled. The user can continue to use Unblock to access the site until such time that the administrator prohibits (blocks) the site, thus removing the option to Unblock.\n\n- Feedback: The toast notification presents the user with a link to submit a ticket, which the user can use to submit feedback to the administrator in an attempt to justify access to the site.","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-04-01T11:54:19\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (EnableConvertWarnToBlock == 1)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\NIS\\EnableConvertWarnToBlock'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n"},{"security_override_guidance":"","group_title":"SRG-APP-000210","third_party_tools":"","rule_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must enable asynchronous inspection.","rule_id":"SV-278678r1144079","weight":"10.0","stig_uuid":"7387268B-722B-1014-941A-E212739FAB8B","ccis":["CCI-001170"],"ia_controls":"","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000210","id":"V-278678"},"group_id":"V-278678","mitigations":"","documentable":"false","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Microsoft Defender Antivirus &gt;&gt; MpEngine &gt;&gt; Turn on asynchronous inspection to \"Enabled\".\n\nClick \"OK\".\n\nClick \"Apply\".","rule_id_src":"SV-278678r1144079_rule","status":"open","group_id_src":"V-278678","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windowsdefav:def:278678","href":"U_MS_Defender_Antivirus_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV13-oval.xml"},"reference_identifier":"3985","classification":"Unclassified","potential_impacts":"","severity":"medium","responsibility":"","comments":null,"rule_version":"WNDF-AV-000075","check_content":"Verify the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Microsoft Defender Antivirus &gt;&gt; Network Inspection System &gt;&gt; Turn on asynchronous inspection is set to \"Enabled\"; otherwise, this is a finding.\n\nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \nHKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\NIS\n\nCriteria: If the value \"AllowSwitchToAsyncInspection\" is REG_DWORD = 1, this is not a finding.\n\nIf the value is 0, this is a finding.","false_positives":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"uuid":"738F3C52-722B-1014-B2E4-8101EAF8F2F9","discussion":"Network protection includes performance optimization that allows block mode to asynchronously inspect long-lived connections, which might provide a performance improvement. This optimization can also help with app compatibility problems.","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-04-01T11:54:19\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Turn on asynchronous inspection' is 'Enabled')\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\NIS\\AllowSwitchToAsyncInspection'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n"},{"security_override_guidance":"","group_title":"SRG-APP-000278","third_party_tools":"","rule_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must scan packed executables.","rule_id":"SV-278679r1144081","weight":"10.0","stig_uuid":"7387268B-722B-1014-941A-E212739FAB8B","ccis":["CCI-001242"],"ia_controls":"","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000278","id":"V-278679"},"group_id":"V-278679","mitigations":"","documentable":"false","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Microsoft Defender Antivirus &gt;&gt; Scan &gt;&gt; Scan packed executables to \"Enabled\".\n\nClick \"OK\".\n\nClick \"Apply\".","rule_id_src":"SV-278679r1144081_rule","status":"open","group_id_src":"V-278679","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windowsdefav:def:278679","href":"U_MS_Defender_Antivirus_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV13-oval.xml"},"reference_identifier":"3985","classification":"Unclassified","potential_impacts":"","severity":"medium","responsibility":"","comments":null,"rule_version":"WNDF-AV-000076","check_content":"Verify the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Microsoft Defender Antivirus &gt;&gt; Scan &gt;&gt; Scan packed executables is set to \"Enabled\"; otherwise, this is a finding.\n\nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \nHKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Scan\n\nCriteria: If the value \"DisablePackedExeScanning\" is REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.\n\nIf the value is 1, this is a finding.","false_positives":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"uuid":"738F45C7-722B-1014-B9E6-FC4343155778","discussion":"This policy setting manages whether Microsoft Defender Antivirus scans packed executables. Packed executables are executable files that contain compressed code.","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-04-01T11:54:19\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false ('Scan packed executables' is 'Enabled')\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Scan\\DisablePackedExeScanning'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n"},{"security_override_guidance":"","group_title":"SRG-APP-000278","third_party_tools":"","rule_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must enable heuristics.","rule_id":"SV-278680r1144083","weight":"10.0","stig_uuid":"7387268B-722B-1014-941A-E212739FAB8B","ccis":["CCI-001242"],"ia_controls":"","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000278","id":"V-278680"},"group_id":"V-278680","mitigations":"","documentable":"false","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Microsoft Defender Antivirus &gt;&gt; Scan &gt;&gt; Turn on heuristics to \"Enabled\".\n\nClick \"OK\".\n\nClick \"Apply\".","rule_id_src":"SV-278680r1144083_rule","status":"open","group_id_src":"V-278680","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windowsdefav:def:278680","href":"U_MS_Defender_Antivirus_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV13-oval.xml"},"reference_identifier":"3985","classification":"Unclassified","potential_impacts":"","severity":"medium","responsibility":"","comments":null,"rule_version":"WNDF-AV-000077","check_content":"Verify the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Microsoft Defender Antivirus &gt;&gt; Scan &gt;&gt; Turn on heuristics is set to \"Enabled\"; otherwise, this is a finding.\n\nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \nHKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Scan\n\nCriteria: If the value \"DisableHeuristics\" is REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.\n\nIf the value is 1, this is a finding.","false_positives":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"uuid":"738F4F3F-722B-1014-B05B-CCB2DC4C9E68","discussion":"Always-on protection consists of real-time protection, behavior monitoring, and heuristics to identify malware based on known suspicious and malicious activities.","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-04-01T11:54:19\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Turn on heuristics is 'Enabled')\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Scan\\DisableHeuristics'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n"},{"security_override_guidance":"","group_title":"SRG-APP-000210","third_party_tools":"","rule_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must set cloud protection level to High.","rule_id":"SV-278863r1144086","weight":"10.0","stig_uuid":"7387268B-722B-1014-941A-E212739FAB8B","ccis":["CCI-001170"],"ia_controls":"","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000210","id":"V-278863"},"group_id":"V-278863","mitigations":"","documentable":"false","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Microsoft Defender Antivirus &gt;&gt; MpEngine &gt;&gt; Select cloud protection level to \"Enabled\".\n\nSet policy value \"Select cloud blocking level\" to \"High blocking level\".\n\nClick \"OK\".\n\nClick \"Apply\".","rule_id_src":"SV-278863r1144086_rule","status":"open","group_id_src":"V-278863","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windowsdefav:def:278863","href":"U_MS_Defender_Antivirus_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV13-oval.xml"},"reference_identifier":"3985","classification":"Unclassified","potential_impacts":"","severity":"medium","responsibility":"","comments":null,"rule_version":"WNDF-AV-000073","check_content":"Verify the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Microsoft Defender Antivirus &gt;&gt; MpEngine &gt;&gt; Select cloud protection level is set to \"Enabled\". Verify the policy value for \"Select cloud blocking level\" is set to \"High blocking level\"; otherwise, this is a finding.\n\nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \nHKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\MpEngine\n\nCriteria: If the value \"MpCloudBlockLevel\" is REG_DWORD = 2, this is not a finding.\n\nIf the value is other than 2, this is a finding.","false_positives":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"uuid":"738F5960-722B-1014-B9BE-A14883885893","discussion":"Cloud protection in Microsoft Defender Antivirus delivers accurate, real-time, and intelligent protection. Cloud protection should be enabled by default.","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-04-01T11:54:19\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false ('Cloud blocking level' is 'High blocking level')\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\MpEngine\\MpCloudBlockLevel'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n"}],"size":67,"uuid":"7387268B-722B-1014-941A-E212739FAB8B","display_name":"Microsoft Defender Antivirus","stig_id":"MS_Defender_Antivirus","release_info":"Release: 7 Benchmark Date: 05 Jan 2026","version":"2"},{"stig_name":"Microsoft DotNet Framework 4.0 Security Technical Implementation Guide","reference_identifier":"4213","classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","rules":[{"security_override_guidance":"","group_title":"SRG-APP-000175","third_party_tools":"","rule_title":"Digital signatures assigned to strongly named assemblies must be verified.","rule_id":"SV-225223r961038","weight":"10.0","stig_uuid":"A16E2E6A-722B-1014-BDE7-9A88D219B55B","ccis":["CCI-000185"],"ia_controls":"","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000175","id":"V-225223"},"group_id":"V-225223","mitigations":"","documentable":"false","fix_text":"Use regedit to remove the values stored in Windows registry key HKLM\\Software\\Microsoft\\StrongName\\Verification. There should be no assemblies or hash values listed under this registry key.\n\nAll assemblies must require strong name verification in a production environment.\n\nStrong name assemblies that do not require verification in a development or test environment must have documented approvals from the IAO.\n","rule_id_src":"SV-225223r961038_rule","status":"not_a_finding","group_id_src":"V-225223","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.dotnet:def:2","href":"U_MS_DotNet_Framework_4-0_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV13-oval.xml"},"reference_identifier":"4213","classification":"Unclassified","potential_impacts":"","severity":"medium","responsibility":"","comments":null,"rule_version":"APPNET0031","check_content":"Use regedit to review the Windows registry key \nHKLM\\Software\\Microsoft\\StrongName\\Verification. \nThere should be no assemblies or hash values listed under this registry key. If the StrongName\\Verification key does not exist, this is not a finding.\n\nIf there are assemblies or hash values listed in this key, each value represents a distinct application assembly that does not have the application strong name verified.  \n\nIf any assemblies are listed as omitting strong name verification in a production environment, this is a finding.\n\nIf any assemblies are listed as omitting strong name verification in a development or test environment and the IAO has not provided documented approvals, this is a finding.","false_positives":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-7438","V-7055"],"uuid":"A16EA287-722B-1014-BAD2-B9E5CDDED1D2","discussion":"A strong name consists of the assembly's identity, simple text name, version number, and culture information (if provided)âplus a public key and a digital signature.  Strong names serve to identify the author of the code.  If digital signatures used to sign strong name assemblies are not verified, any self signed code can be impersonated.  This can lead to a loss of system integrity. ","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-04-01T11:54:25\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (No assemblies or hash values under HKLM\\Software\\Microsoft\\StrongName\\Verification)\n"},{"security_override_guidance":"","group_title":"SRG-APP-000175","third_party_tools":"","rule_title":"The Trust Providers Software Publishing State must be set to 0x23C00.","rule_id":"SV-225224r961038","weight":"10.0","stig_uuid":"A16E2E6A-722B-1014-BDE7-9A88D219B55B","ccis":["CCI-000185"],"ia_controls":"","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000175","id":"V-225224"},"group_id":"V-225224","mitigations":"","documentable":"false","fix_text":"This fix must be performed for each user on the system.\n\nUsing regedit, change the hexadecimal value of the \"HKEY_USER\\[UNIQUE USER SID VALUE]\\Software\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\WinTrust\\Trust Providers\\Software Publishing\\State\" registry key to 0x23C00.\n","rule_id_src":"SV-225224r961038_rule","status":"not_a_finding","group_id_src":"V-225224","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.dotnet:def:225224","href":"U_MS_DotNet_Framework_4-0_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV13-oval2.xml"},"reference_identifier":"4213","classification":"Unclassified","potential_impacts":"","severity":"medium","responsibility":"","comments":null,"rule_version":"APPNET0046","check_content":"If the system or application being reviewed is SIPR based, this finding is NA.\n\nThis check must be performed for each user on the system. \n\nUse regedit to locate \"HKEY_USER\\[UNIQUE USER SID VALUE]\\Software\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\WinTrust\\Trust Providers\\Software Publishing\\State\".  \n\nIf the State value for any user is not set to the hexadecimal value of 0x23C00, this is a finding.\n","false_positives":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-7444","V-7061"],"uuid":"A16EAC8C-722B-1014-A628-AA97C1406C40","discussion":"Microsoft Windows operating systems provide a feature called Authenticode.  Authenticode technology and its underlying code signing mechanisms serve to provide a structure to identify software publishers and ensure that software applications have not been tampered with.  Authenticode technology relies on digital certificates and is based on Public Key Cryptography Standards (PKCS) #7 (encrypted key specification), PKCS #10 (certificate request formats), X.509 (certificate specification), and Secure Hash Algorithm (SHA) and MD5 hash algorithms.\n\nThe manner in which the Authenticode technology validates a certificate and determines what is considered a valid certificate can be modified to meet the mission of the Microsoft Windows system.  Each facade of certificate validation is controlled through the bits that makeup the hexadecimal value for the Authenticode setting.  An improper setting will allow non-valid certificates to be accepted and can put the integrity of the system into jeopardy.\n\nThe hexadecimal value of 0x23C00 will implement the following certificate enforcement policy:\n- Trust the Test Root = FALSE\n- Use expiration date on certificates = TRUE\n- Check the revocation list = TRUE\n- Offline revocation server OK (Individual) = TRUE\n- Offline revocation server OK (Commercial) = TRUE\n- Java offline revocation server OK (Individual) = TRUE\n- Java offline revocation server OK (Commercial) = TRUE\n- Invalidate version 1 signed objects = FALSE\n- Check the revocation list on Time Stamp Signer = FALSE\n- Only trust items found in the Trust DB = FALSE","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-04-01T11:54:25\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Developer certificates used with the .NET Publisher Membership Condition must be approved by the ISSO.)\n"},{"security_override_guidance":"","group_title":"SRG-APP-000175","third_party_tools":"","rule_title":"Developer certificates used with the .NET Publisher Membership Condition must be approved by the ISSO.","rule_id":"SV-225225r961038","weight":"10.0","stig_uuid":"A16E2E6A-722B-1014-BDE7-9A88D219B55B","ccis":["CCI-000185"],"ia_controls":"","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000175","id":"V-225225"},"group_id":"V-225225","mitigations":"","documentable":"false","fix_text":"Trust must be established when utilizing Publishers Membership Condition. All publisher's certificates must have documented approvals from the ISSO.","rule_id_src":"SV-225225r961038_rule","status":"not_reviewed","group_id_src":"V-225225","check_content_ref":{"name":"ocil:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.dotnet:questionnaire:501","href":"U_MS_DotNet_Framework_4-0_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV13-ocil.xml"},"reference_identifier":"4213","classification":"Unclassified","potential_impacts":"","severity":"medium","responsibility":"","comments":null,"rule_version":"APPNET0048","check_content":"The infrastructure to enable Code Access Security (CAS) exists only in .NET Framework 2.x-4.x. \n\nThis requirement is Not Applicable (NA) for .NET Framework greater than 4.x.\n\n(Note: The infrastructure is deprecated and is not receiving servicing or security fixes.)\n\nCaspol.exe is a Microsoft tool used for working with .Net policy. Use caspol.exe to list the code groups and any publisher membership conditions.\n\nThe location of the caspol utility is dependent upon the system architecture of the system running .Net.\n\nFor 32 bit systems, caspol.exe is located at %SYSTEMROOT%\\Microsoft.NET\\Framework\\v4.0.30319.\n \nFor 64 bit systems, caspol.exe is located at %SYSTEMROOT%\\Microsoft.NET\\Framework64\\v4.0.30319.\n\nExample:\n\ncd %SYSTEMROOT%\\Microsoft.NET\\Framework\\v4.0.30319\n\nTo check code groups for the machine, run the following command:\n\ncaspol.exe -m -lg\n\nSample Results:\nMicrosoft (R) .NET Framework CasPol 4.0.30319.1\nCopyright (c) Microsoft Corporation.  All rights reserved.\n\nPolicy change prompt is ON\n\nLevel = Machine\n\nCode Groups:\n\n1.  All code: Nothing\n   1.1.  Zone - MyComputer: FullTrust (LevelFinal)\n      1.1.1.  StrongName - : FullTrust\n      1.1.2.  StrongName - 00000000000000000400000000000000: FullTrust\n   1.2.  Zone - Intranet: LocalIntranet\n      1.2.1.  All code: Same site Web\n      1.2.2.  All code: Same directory FileIO - 'Read, PathDiscovery'\n   1.3.  Zone - Internet: Internet\n      1.3.1.  All code: Same site Web\n   1.4.  Zone - Untrusted: Nothing\n   1.5.  (First Match) Zone - Trusted: Internet\n      1.5.1.  All code: Same site Web\n   1.6.  Publisher - 30818902818100E47B359ACC061D70C237B572FA276C9854CFABD469DFB74E77D026630BEE2A0C2F8170A823AE69FDEB65704D7FD446DEFEF1F6BA12B6ACBDB1BFA7B9B595AB9A40636467CFF7C73F198B53A9A7CF177F6E7896EBC591DD3003C5992A266C0AD9FBEE4E2A056BE7F7ED154D806F7965F83B0AED616C192C6416CFCB46FC2F5CFD0203010001: FullTrust\nSuccess\n\nSection 1.6 above indicates the presence of a publisher's key that meets the Publisher's Membership Condition and is also given full trust.\n\nIf the Publisher Membership Condition is used on a nondefault Code Group and the use of that publisher's certificate is not documented and approved by the ISSO, this is a finding.","false_positives":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-7446","V-7063"],"uuid":"A16EB521-722B-1014-9353-E8D7277063BC","discussion":"A .Net assembly will satisfy the Publisher Membership Condition if it is signed with a software publisherâs Authenticode X.509v3 digital certificate that can be verified by the Windows operating system as having a chain of trust that leads to a trusted root certificate stored in the userâs certificate store. The Publisher Membership Condition can be used to identify an organization, developer, vendor, or other entity as the ultimate source of the assembly, even if the code itself was obtained from a third party, such as a mirror site. Access to system resources, such as file systems or printers, may then be granted to the assembly based on the trust relationship with the identified entity.\n\nCertificates used to sign assemblies so the Publisher Member Condition may be applied must originate from a trusted source. Using a certificate that is not from a trusted source could potentially violate system integrity and confidentiality.","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-04-01T11:54:25\nResult: notcheckedCriteria        : NOT_TESTED (All child tests must be true.)\nTest            :   NOT_TESTED (CAT II, V-225225, SV-225225r961038, SRG-APP-000175)\n"},{"security_override_guidance":"","group_title":"SRG-APP-000176","third_party_tools":"","rule_title":"Encryption keys used for the .NET Strong Name Membership Condition must be protected.","rule_id":"SV-225226r961041","weight":"10.0","stig_uuid":"A16E2E6A-722B-1014-BDE7-9A88D219B55B","ccis":["CCI-000186"],"ia_controls":"","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000176","id":"V-225226"},"group_id":"V-225226","mitigations":"","documentable":"false","fix_text":"Ask the Systems Programmer how the private keys used to sign the assembly are protected.\n\nPrivate keys are simply values stored as strings of data. Keys can be stored in files on the file system or in a centralized data repository. \n\nAdequate protection methods include, but are not limited to:\n- utilizing centralized key management;\n- using strict file permissions to limit access; and\n- tying strong pass phrases to the key.\n\nThe private key(s) used to sign the assembly must be protected. Utilize centralized key management or strict file permissions along with strong pass phrases and/or other well-established industry practices for managing and controlling access to private keys.","rule_id_src":"SV-225226r961041_rule","status":"not_a_finding","group_id_src":"V-225226","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.dotnet:def:225226","href":"U_MS_DotNet_Framework_4-0_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV13-oval2.xml"},"reference_identifier":"4213","classification":"Unclassified","potential_impacts":"","severity":"medium","responsibility":"","comments":null,"rule_version":"APPNET0052","check_content":"If the application is a COTS product, this requirement is Not Applicable (NA).\n\nThe infrastructure to enable Code Access Security (CAS) exists only in .NET Framework 2.x-4.x.\n\nThe requirement is Not Applicable (NA) for .NET Framework greater than 4.x.\n\n(Note: The infrastructure is deprecated and is not receiving servicing or security fixes.)\n\nCaspol.exe is a Microsoft tool used for working with .Net policy. Use caspol.exe to list the code groups and any publisher membership conditions.\n\nThe location of the caspol utility is dependent upon the system architecture of the system running .Net.\n\nFor 32 bit systems, caspol.exe is located at %SYSTEMROOT%\\Microsoft.NET\\Framework\\v4.0.30319.\n \nFor 64 bit systems, caspol.exe is located at %SYSTEMROOT%\\Microsoft.NET\\Framework64\\v4.0.30319.\n\nExample:\n\ncd %SYSTEMROOT%\\Microsoft.NET\\Framework\\v4.0.30319\n\nTo check code groups, run the following command:\n\ncaspol.exe -all -lg\n\nSample response:\nMicrosoft (R) .NET Framework CasPol 4.0.30319.1\n\nSecurity is ON\nExecution checking is ON\nPolicy change prompt is ON\n\nLevel = Machine\n\nCode Groups:\n\n1.  All code: Nothing\n   1.1.  Zone - MyComputer: FullTrust (LevelFinal)\n      1.1.1.  StrongName - : FullTrust\n      1.1.2.  StrongName - 00000000000000000400000000000000: FullTrust\n   1.2.  Zone - Intranet: LocalIntranet\n      1.2.1.  All code: Same site Web\n      1.2.2.  All code: Same directory FileIO - 'Read, PathDiscovery'\n   1.3.  Zone - Internet: Internet\n      1.3.1.  All code: Same site Web\n   1.4.  Zone - Untrusted: Nothing\n   1.5.  (First Match) Zone - Trusted: Internet\n      1.5.1.  All code: Same site Web\n   1.6.  Publisher - 30818902818100E47B359ACC061D70C237B572FA276C9854CFABD469DFB74E77D026630BEE2A0C2F8170A823AE69FDEB65704D7FD446DEFEF1F6BA12B6ACBDB1BFA7B9B595AB9A40636467CFF7C73F198B53A9A7CF177F6E7896EBC591DD3003C5992A266C0AD9FBEE4E2A056BE7F7ED154D806F7965F83B0AED616C192C6416CFCB46FC2F5CFD0203010001: FullTrust\nSuccess\n\nAn assembly will satisfy the StrongNameMembershipCondition if its metadata contains the strongly identifying data associated with the specified strong name. At the least, this means it has been digitally signed with the private key associated with the public key recorded in the policy.\n\nThe presence of the encryption key values in the StrongName field indicates the use of StrongNameMembershipCondition. \n\nIf a Strong Name Membership Condition is assigned to a non-default Code Group the private key must be adequately protected by the software developer or the entity responsible for signing the assemblies. \n\nAsk the Systems Programmer how the private keys are protected. \n\nPrivate keys are simply values stored as strings of data.  Keys can be stored in files on the file system or in a centralized data repository. \n\nAdequate protection methods include, but are not limited to:\n- utilizing centralized key management;\n- using strict file permissions to limit access; and\n- tying strong pass phrases to the key.\n\nIf the private key used to sign the assembly is not adequately protected, this is a finding.","false_positives":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-7450","V-7067"],"uuid":"A16EBD00-722B-1014-BDFD-A56114D100B2","discussion":"The Strong Name Membership condition requires that member assemblies be defined with Strong Names. A strong name consists of the assembly's identity, simple text name, version number, and culture information (if provided) â plus a public key and a digital signature. If assemblies do not have a strong name assigned, the assembly cannot be unique and the author of the code cannot be uniquely identified. In order to create the strong name, the developer must use a cryptographic key pair to sign the assembly. If the developer does not protect the key, the key can be stolen and used to sign any application, including malware applications. This could adversely affect application integrity and confidentiality.","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-04-01T11:54:25\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Encryption keys used for the .NET Strong Name Membership Condition must be protected.)\n"},{"security_override_guidance":"","group_title":"SRG-APP-000120","third_party_tools":"","rule_title":"CAS and policy configuration files must be backed up.","rule_id":"SV-225227r960936","weight":"10.0","stig_uuid":"A16E2E6A-722B-1014-BDE7-9A88D219B55B","ccis":["CCI-000164"],"ia_controls":"","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000120","id":"V-225227"},"group_id":"V-225227","mitigations":"","documentable":"false","fix_text":"All CAS policy and policy configuration files must be included in the system backup. \n\nAll CAS policy and policy configuration files must be backed up prior to migration, deployment, and reconfiguration.\n\nCAS policy configuration files must be included in disaster recovery plan documentation.","rule_id_src":"SV-225227r960936_rule","status":"not_reviewed","group_id_src":"V-225227","check_content_ref":{"name":"ocil:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.dotnet:questionnaire:901","href":"U_MS_DotNet_Framework_4-0_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV13-ocil.xml"},"reference_identifier":"4213","classification":"Unclassified","potential_impacts":"","severity":"medium","responsibility":"","comments":null,"rule_version":"APPNET0055","check_content":"The infrastructure to enable Code Access Security (CAS) exists only in .NET Framework 2.x-4.x.\n\nThe requirement is Not Applicable (NA) for .NET Framework greater than 4.x.\n\n(Note: The infrastructure is deprecated and is not receiving servicing or security fixes.)\n\nAsk the System Administrator if all CAS policy and policy configuration files are included in the system backup. If they are not, this is a finding.\n\nAsk the System Administrator if the policy and configuration files are backed up prior to migration, deployment, and reconfiguration. If they are not, this is a finding.\n\nAsk the System Administrator for documentation that shows CAS Policy configuration files are backed up as part of a disaster recovery plan. If they have no documentation proving the files are backed up, this is a finding.","false_positives":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-7452","V-7069"],"uuid":"A16EC503-722B-1014-A86D-8F6DC779A9EA","discussion":"A successful disaster recovery plan requires that CAS policy and CAS policy configuration files are identified and included in systems disaster backup and recovery events. Documentation regarding the location of system and application specific CAS policy configuration files and the frequency in which backups occur is required. If these files are not identified and the information is not documented, there is the potential that critical application configuration files may not be included in disaster recovery events which could lead to an availability risk.","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-04-01T11:54:25\nResult: notcheckedCriteria        : NOT_TESTED (All child tests must be true.)\nTest            :   NOT_TESTED (CAT II, V-225227, SV-225227r960936, SRG-APP-000120)\n"},{"security_override_guidance":"","group_title":"SRG-APP-000219","third_party_tools":"","rule_title":"Remoting Services HTTP channels must utilize authentication and encryption.","rule_id":"SV-225228r1043178","weight":"10.0","stig_uuid":"A16E2E6A-722B-1014-BDE7-9A88D219B55B","ccis":["CCI-001184"],"ia_controls":"","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000219","id":"V-225228"},"group_id":"V-225228","mitigations":"","documentable":"false","fix_text":"If .NET remoting with HTTP channel is not used, this fix is Not Applicable.\n\nEnsure encryption and message integrity are used for HTTP remoting channels.\n\nThe HTTP channel only supports encryption and message integrity when the remote object is hosted in Internet Information Services (IIS) using TLS.\n\nHTTP channels are protected via TLS (HTTPS). \n&lt;channels&gt; \n   &lt;channel ref=âhttp serverâ port=â443â/&gt; \n&lt;/channels&gt; \n\nChange the channel ref parameter to utilize a TLS port and leverage TLS on the remote IIS server.","rule_id_src":"SV-225228r1043178_rule","status":"not_a_finding","group_id_src":"V-225228","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.dotnet:def:225228","href":"U_MS_DotNet_Framework_4-0_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV13-oval2.xml"},"reference_identifier":"4213","classification":"Unclassified","potential_impacts":"","severity":"medium","responsibility":"","comments":null,"rule_version":"APPNET0060","check_content":"If .NET remoting with HTTP channel is not used, this check is Not Applicable.\n\nReview the machine.config file and the [application name].exe.config file.\n\nFor 32-bit systems, the \"machine.config\" file is contained in the following folder: %SYSTEMROOT%\\Microsoft.NET\\Framework\\v4.0.30319\\Config \n\nFor 64-bit systems, the \"machine.config\" file is contained in the following folder: %SYSTEMROOT%\\Microsoft.NET\\Framework64\\v4.0.30319\\Config.\n\nMicrosoft specifies locating the [application].config file in the same folder as the application executable (.exe) file. However, the developer does have the capability to specify a different location when the application is compiled.  Therefore, if the file is not found in the application home folder, a search of the system is required. If the [application name].exe.config file is not found on the system, then only a check of the machine.config file is required.\n\nSample machine/application config file:\n\n&lt;application name=âremoteserverâ&gt; \n  &lt;service&gt; \n    &lt;activated type=âsample.my.object, myobjectsâ/&gt; \n  &lt;/service&gt; \n  &lt;channels&gt; \n    &lt;channel ref=âhttp serverâ port=â80â/&gt; \n  &lt;/channels&gt; \n&lt;/application&gt;\n\n&lt;serverProviders&gt;\n  &lt;provider ref=\"wsdl\" /&gt;\n  &lt;formatter ref=\"soap\" typeFilterLevel=\"Low\" /&gt; \n  &lt;formatter ref=\"binary\" typeFilterLevel=\"Low\" /&gt; \n&lt;/serverProviders&gt; \n\nMicrosoft provides three \"channels\" that are used for remoting connectivity. They are the HTTP, TCP, and IPC channels. The channel that is used is specified via the &lt;channels&gt; element in the config file.  \n\nHTTP channel example:\n&lt;channel ref=âhttp serverâ port=â80â/&gt; \n\nThe HTTP channel only supports encryption and message integrity when the remote object is hosted in Internet Information Services (IIS) using TLS.\n\nThe above example shows the well-known TLS port of 443 is not being used. \n\nIf the HTTP remoting channel is not configured to protect the channel by using TLS encryption, this is a finding.","false_positives":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-7453","V-7070"],"uuid":"A16ECC83-722B-1014-A704-F012E10AE28E","discussion":"Note: Microsoft recommends using the Windows Communication Framework (WCF) rather than using .Net remoting. New development projects should refrain from using .Net remoting capabilities whenever possible.\n\n.NET remoting provides the capability to build widely distributed applications. The application components may reside all on one computer or they may be spread out across the enclave. .NET client applications can make remoting calls to use objects in other processes on the same computer or on any other computer that is reachable over the network. .NET remoting can also be used to communicate with other application domains within the same process. Remoting is achieved via the exposure of endpoints that can be used to establish remote connectivity.\n\nNormally when application code attempts to access a protected resource, a stack walk is performed to ensure that all stack frames have permission to access the resource. However, with .Net 4.0, when a call is made on a remote object, this stack walk is not performed across the remoting boundary. The .Net remoting infrastructure requires FullTrust permission to execute on either the client or the server. \n\nDue to the fact that FullTrust permission is required, Remoting endpoints should be authenticated and encrypted in order to protect the system and the data. \n\nMicrosoft provides three different \"channels\" that are used for remoting. They are HTTP, TCP, and IPC.\n\nAny unauthorized use of a remoting application provides unauthorized access with FullTrust permissions to the system. This can potentially result in a loss of system integrity or confidentiality.","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-04-01T11:54:25\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Http channel must use TLS on port 443.)\n"},{"security_override_guidance":"","group_title":"SRG-APP-000516","third_party_tools":"","rule_title":".Net Framework versions installed on the system must be supported.","rule_id":"SV-225229r1107247","weight":"10.0","stig_uuid":"A16E2E6A-722B-1014-BDE7-9A88D219B55B","ccis":["CCI-000366"],"ia_controls":"","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000516","id":"V-225229"},"group_id":"V-225229","mitigations":"","documentable":"false","fix_text":"Remove unsupported versions of the .NET Framework and upgrade legacy applications that utilize unsupported versions of the .NET framework.","rule_id_src":"SV-225229r1107247_rule","status":"not_a_finding","group_id_src":"V-225229","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.dotnet:def:225229","href":"U_MS_DotNet_Framework_4-0_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV13-oval2.xml"},"reference_identifier":"4213","classification":"Unclassified","potential_impacts":"","severity":"medium","responsibility":"","comments":null,"rule_version":"APPNET0061","check_content":"Determine which versions of the .NET Framework are installed by opening the directory %systemroot%\\Microsoft.NET.\n\nThe folder named \"%systemroot%\\Microsoft.NET\\Framework\" contains .NET files for 32 bit systems. The folder named \"%systemroot%\\Microsoft.NET\\Framework64\" contains .NET files for 64 bit systems. 64 bit systems will have both the 32 bit and the 64 bit folders. 32 bit systems do not have a Framework64 folder.\n\nWithin each of the folders are the individual folder names that contain the corresponding versions of the .NET Framework:\n\nv4.0.30319\nv3.5\nv3.0\nv2.0.50727\nv1.1.4322\nv1.0.3705\n\nSearch for all the Mscorlib.dll files in the %systemroot%\\Microsoft.NET\\Framework folder and the %systemroot%\\Microsoft.NET\\Framework64 folder if the folder exists. Click on each of the files, view properties, and click the version tab to determine the version installed. If there is no Mscorlib.dll, there is no installed version of .Net Framework in that directory.\n\nMore specific information on determining versions of .Net Framework installed can be found at the following link. http://support.microsoft.com/kb/318785\n\nVerify extended support is available for the installed versions of .Net Framework.\n\nVerify the .Net Framework support dates with Microsoft Product Lifecycle Search link.\nhttp://support.microsoft.com/lifecycle/search/?sort=PN&amp;alpha=.NET+Framework\n\nBeginning with .NET 3.5 SP1, the .NET Framework is considered a Component of the Windows OS. Components follow the Support Lifecycle policy of their parent product or platform.\n\n .NET Framework 3.5 cannot function without the .NET Framework 2.0 and the .NET Framework 3.0, because there is no common language runtime (CLR) in the .NET Framework 3.5 layer. Therefore, when the .NET Framework 3.5 product is installed, the .NET Framework 2.0 and the .NET Framework 3.0 SP products are also installed. Installation of .NET 2.0 and 3.0 SP products as part of .NET Framework 3.5 is Not a Finding. (https://support.microsoft.com/en-us/topic/clarification-on-the-support-life-cycle-for-the-net-framework-3-5-the-net-framework-3-0-and-the-net-framework-2-0-28621c7b-226c-7682-27f5-2e2a42db39c3)\n \nIf any versions of the .Net Framework are installed and support is no longer available, this is a finding.\n","false_positives":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-55642","V-18395"],"uuid":"A16ED471-722B-1014-B9FA-C7806411DB48","discussion":"Unsupported software introduces risks and violates DOD policy. Applications utilizing unsupported versions of .NET introduce substantial risk to the host, network, and the enclave because they leverage an architecture that is no longer updated by the vendor. This introduces potential application integrity, availability, or confidentiality issues.","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-04-01T11:54:25\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (One or more child tests must be true. (OR))\nCriteria        :   false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :     false (.Net Framework 3.5 is not installed)\nTest            :     false (Verify that 32 bit .NET framwork installs are 4.6.2 and later)\nTest            :     false (Verify that 64 bit .NET framwork installs are 4.6.2 and later)\nCriteria        :   true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :     true (.Net Framework 3.5 is installed)\nTest            :     true (Verify that 32 bit .NET framwork installs are 2.0.50727 (required for .NET Framework 3.5 SP1) or 4.6.2 and later)\nTest            :     true (Verify that 64 bit .NET framwork installs are 2.0.50727 (required for .NET Framework 3.5 SP1) or 4.6.2 and later)\n"},{"security_override_guidance":"","group_title":"SRG-APP-000635","third_party_tools":"","rule_title":"The .NET CLR must be configured to use FIPS approved encryption modules.","rule_id":"SV-225230r961908","weight":"10.0","stig_uuid":"A16E2E6A-722B-1014-BDE7-9A88D219B55B","ccis":["CCI-002450"],"ia_controls":"","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000635","id":"V-225230"},"group_id":"V-225230","mitigations":"","documentable":"false","fix_text":"Examine the .NET CLR configuration files to find the runtime element and then the \"enforceFIPSPolicy\" element.\n\nExample:\n&lt;configuration&gt; \n  &lt;runtime&gt; \n                &lt;enforceFIPSPolicy enabled=\"true|false\" /&gt;\n  &lt;/runtime&gt;\n&lt;/configuration&gt;\n\nDelete the \"enforceFIPSPolicy\" runtime element, change the setting to \"true\" or there must be documented IAO approvals for the FIPS setting.","rule_id_src":"SV-225230r961908_rule","status":"open","group_id_src":"V-225230","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.dotnet:def:9","href":"U_MS_DotNet_Framework_4-0_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV13-oval.xml"},"reference_identifier":"4213","classification":"Unclassified","potential_impacts":"","severity":"medium","responsibility":"","comments":null,"rule_version":"APPNET0062","check_content":"\nExamine the .NET CLR configuration files from the vulnerability discussion to find the runtime element and then the \"enforceFIPSPolicy\" element.\n\nExample:\n&lt;configuration&gt; \n  &lt;runtime&gt; \n                &lt;enforceFIPSPolicy enabled=\"true|false\" /&gt;\n  &lt;/runtime&gt;\n&lt;/configuration&gt;\n\nBy default, the .NET \"enforceFIPSPolicy\" element is set to \"true\".\n\nIf the \"enforceFIPSPolicy\" element does not exist within the \"runtime\" element of the CLR configuration, this is not a finding.\n\nIf the \"enforceFIPSPolicy\" element exists and is set to \"false\", and the IAO has not accepted the risk and documented the risk acceptance, this is a finding. \n\n","false_positives":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-40966","V-30926"],"uuid":"A16EDD20-722B-1014-BB9A-8823246B1DB8","discussion":"FIPS encryption is configured via .NET configuration files.  There are numerous configuration files that affect different aspects of .Net behavior.  The .NET config files are described below.\n \nMachine Configuration Files:\nThe machine configuration file, Machine.config, contains settings that apply to an entire computer. This file is located in the %SYSTEMROOT%\\Microsoft.NET\\Framework\\v4.0.30319\\Config directory for 32 bit .NET 4 installations and %SYSTEMROOT%\\Microsoft.NET\\Framework64\\v4.0.30319\\Config for 64 bit systems.   Machine.config contains configuration settings for machine-wide assembly binding, built-in remoting channels, and ASP.NET.\n\nApplication Configuration Files:\nApplication configuration files contain settings specific to an application. If checking these files, a .NET review of a specific .NET application is most likely being conducted. These files contain configuration settings that the Common Language Runtime reads (such as assembly binding policy, remoting objects, and so on), and settings that the application can read. \n\nThe name and location of the application configuration file depends on the application's host, which can be one of the following: \n\nExecutableâhosted application configuration files. \n\nThe configuration file for an application hosted by the executable host is in the same directory as the application. The name of the configuration file is the name of the application with a .config extension. For example, an application called myApp.exe can be associated with a configuration file called myApp.exe.config. \n\nInternet Explorer-hosted application configuration files. \n\nIf an application hosted in Internet Explorer has a configuration file, the location of this file is specified in a &lt;link&gt; tag with the following syntax.\n\n&lt;link rel=\"ConfigurationFileName\" href=\"location\"&gt;\n\nIn this tag, \"location\" represents a URL that point to the configuration file. This sets the application base. The configuration file must be located on the same web site as the application. \n\n.NET 4.0 allows the CLR runtime to be configured to ignore FIPS encryption requirements.  If the CLR is not configured to use FIPS encryption modules, insecure encryption modules might be employed which could introduce an application confidentiality or integrity issue.","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-04-01T11:54:25\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Application configiguration files are configured to use FIPS approved encryption modules)\nResult Analysis :        C:\\Program Files (x86)\\Lenovo\\System Update\\TvsuCommandLauncher.exe.config xpath = count(/configuration/runtime/enforceFIPSPolicy/@enabled) = 0 or /configuration/runtime/enforceFIPSPolicy/@enabled = \"true\" = '0' failed test of 'equals' compared to '1' \n                : C:\\Program Files (x86)\\Lenovo\\System Update\\Tvsukernel.exe.config xpath = count(/configuration/runtime/enforceFIPSPolicy/@enabled) = 0 or /configuration/runtime/enforceFIPSPolicy/@enabled = \"true\" = '0' failed test of 'equals' compared to '1' \n                : C:\\Program Files (x86)\\Lenovo\\System Update\\uncsetting.exe.config xpath = count(/configuration/runtime/enforceFIPSPolicy/@enabled) = 0 or /configuration/runtime/enforceFIPSPolicy/@enabled = \"true\" = '0' failed test of 'equals' compared to '1' \n                : C:\\Program Files (x86)\\Lenovo\\System Update\\ConfigScheduledTask.exe.config xpath = count(/configuration/runtime/enforceFIPSPolicy/@enabled) = 0 or /configuration/runtime/enforceFIPSPolicy/@enabled = \"true\" = '0' failed test of 'equals' compared to '1' \n                : C:\\Program Files (x86)\\Lenovo\\System Update\\SUService.exe.config xpath = count(/configuration/runtime/enforceFIPSPolicy/@enabled) = 0 or /configuration/runtime/enforceFIPSPolicy/@enabled = \"true\" = '0' failed test of 'equals' compared to '1' \n                : C:\\Program Files (x86)\\Lenovo\\System Update\\UNCServer.exe.config xpath = count(/configuration/runtime/enforceFIPSPolicy/@enabled) = 0 or /configuration/runtime/enforceFIPSPolicy/@enabled = \"true\" = '0' failed test of 'equals' compared to '1' \nTest            :   true (Machine configiguration files are configured to use FIPS approved encryption modules)\n"},{"security_override_guidance":"","group_title":"SRG-APP-000175","third_party_tools":"","rule_title":".NET must be configured to validate strong names on full-trust assemblies.","rule_id":"SV-225231r961038","weight":"10.0","stig_uuid":"A16E2E6A-722B-1014-BDE7-9A88D219B55B","ccis":["CCI-000185"],"ia_controls":"","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000175","id":"V-225231"},"group_id":"V-225231","mitigations":"","documentable":"false","fix_text":"For 32 bit production systems: \nSet âHKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\.NETFramework\\AllowStrongNameBypass\" to a âDWORDâ value of â0â.\nOn 64-bit production systems:\nSet âHKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\.NETFramework\\ AllowStrongNameBypassâ and âHKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\\Wow6432Node\\Microsoft\\.NETFramework\\ AllowStrongNameBypassâ to a âDWORDâ value of â0â.\nOr, obtain documented ISSO risk acceptance for each .Net application installed on the system. \n\nApproval documentation will include complete list of all installed .Net applications, application versions, and acknowledgement of ISSO trust of each installed application.\n","rule_id_src":"SV-225231r961038_rule","status":"open","group_id_src":"V-225231","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.dotnet:def:225231","href":"U_MS_DotNet_Framework_4-0_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV13-oval2.xml"},"reference_identifier":"4213","classification":"Unclassified","potential_impacts":"","severity":"medium","responsibility":"","comments":null,"rule_version":"APPNET0063","check_content":"If there is documented ISSO risk acceptance for development systems, this is not a finding.\nFor 32 bit production systems: \nUse regedit to examine the âHKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\.NETFrameworkâ key.  \nOn 64-bit production systems:\nUse regedit to examine both the âHKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\.NETFrameworkâ and âHKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\\Wow6432Node\\Microsoft\\.NETFrameworkâ keys.\nIf the \"AllowStrongNameBypass\" value does not exist, or if the âDWORDâ value is set to â1â, this is a finding.\n\nDocumentation must include a complete list of installed .Net applications, application versions, and acknowledgement that ISSO trusts each installed application.\n\nIf application versions installed on the system do not match approval documentation, this is a finding.\n\n","false_positives":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-40977","V-30935"],"uuid":"A16EE495-722B-1014-9322-81B0112BFBA2","discussion":"The \"bypassTrustedAppStrongNames\" setting specifies whether the bypass feature that avoids validating strong names for full-trust assemblies is enabled. By default the bypass feature is enabled in .Net 4, therefore strong names are not validated for correctness when the assembly/program is loaded. Not validating strong names provides a faster application load time but at the expense of performing certificate validation. \n\nFull trust assemblies are .Net applications launched from the local host. Strong names are digital signatures tied to .Net applications/assemblies.  .Net 4 considers applications installed locally to be fully trusted by default and grants these applications full permissions to access host resources. \n\nThe bypass feature applies to any assembly signed with a strong name and having the following characteristics:\n\n    Fully trusted without the StrongName evidence (for example, has MyComputer zone evidence).\n\n    Loaded into a fully trusted AppDomain.\n\n    Loaded from a location under the ApplicationBase property of that AppDomain.\n\n    Not delay-signed.\n\nNot validating the certificates used to sign strong name assemblies will provide a faster application load time, but falsely assumes that signatures used to sign the application are to be implicitly trusted.  Not validating strong name certificates introduces an integrity risk to the system.","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-04-01T11:54:25\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Verify registry key for 64 bit version of .NET must be configured to validate strong names on full-trust assemblies.)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\.NETFramework\\AllowStrongNameBypass'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\nTest            :   false (Verify registry key for 32 bit version of .NET must be configured to validate strong names on full-trust assemblies.)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\\Wow6432Node\\Microsoft\\.NETFramework\\AllowStrongNameBypass'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n"},{"security_override_guidance":"","group_title":"SRG-APP-000516","third_party_tools":"","rule_title":".Net applications that invoke NetFx40_LegacySecurityPolicy must apply previous versions of .NET STIG guidance.","rule_id":"SV-225232r1050651","weight":"10.0","stig_uuid":"A16E2E6A-722B-1014-BDE7-9A88D219B55B","ccis":["CCI-000366"],"ia_controls":"","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000516","id":"V-225232"},"group_id":"V-225232","mitigations":"","documentable":"false","fix_text":"The infrastructure to enable CAS exists only in .NET Framework 2.x - 4.x.\n\nThe requirement is Not Applicable (NA) for .NET Framework &gt; 4.x.\n\n(Note: The infrastructure is deprecated and is not receiving servicing or security fixes.)\n\nApply the .NET Framework Security Checklist for .Net versions 1 through 3.5 when using the NetFx40_LegacySecurityPolicy setting.","rule_id_src":"SV-225232r1050651_rule","status":"not_a_finding","group_id_src":"V-225232","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.dotnet:def:225232","href":"U_MS_DotNet_Framework_4-0_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV13-oval2.xml"},"reference_identifier":"4213","classification":"Unclassified","potential_impacts":"","severity":"low","responsibility":"","comments":null,"rule_version":"APPNET0064","check_content":"The infrastructure to enable Code Access Security (CAS) exists only in .NET Framework 2.x - 4.x.\n\nThe requirement is Not Applicable (NA) for .NET Framework &gt; 4.x.\n\n(Note: The infrastructure is deprecated and is not receiving servicing or security fixes.)\n\nOpen Windows explorer and search for all *.exe.config files. This requirement does not apply to the caspol.exe assembly or other assemblies provided with the Windows OS or the Windows Secure Host Baseline (SHB).\n\nTo find relevant files, run the FINDSTR command from an elevated (admin) command prompt: \nFINDSTR /i /s \"NetFx40_LegacySecurityPolicy\" c:\\*.exe.config \n\nThis command will search all .\"exe.config\" files on the c: drive partition for the \"LegacySecurityPolicy\" setting. Repeat the command for each drive partition on the system.\n\nIf the .NET application configuration file uses the legacy policy element, and .NET STIG guidance that covers these legacy versions has not been applied, this is a finding.\n","false_positives":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-40979","V-30937"],"uuid":"A16EEBCC-722B-1014-937F-E77D647A7002","discussion":"CAS policy is .NET runtime version-specific.  In .NET Framework version 4, CAS policy is disabled by default however; it can be re-enabled by using the NetFx40_LegacySecurityPolicy setting on a per application basis. Caspol.exe is provided by Microsoft to set security policy on .Net applications prior to version 4.0. This requirement does not apply to the caspol.exe assembly or other assemblies provided with the Windows OS or the Windows Secure Host Baseline (SHB).\n\nWhen invoking the NetFx40_LegacySecurityPolicy setting in .NET 4, earlier versions of the .NET Framework CAS policy will become active therefore previous .NET STIG guidance that applies to the reactivated versions must also be applied. \n\nFailure to apply applicable versions of STIG guidance can result in the loss of system confidentiality, integrity or availability.  ","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-04-01T11:54:25\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (.Net applications that invoke NetFx40_LegacySecurityPolicy must apply previous versions of .NET STIG guidance.)\n"},{"security_override_guidance":"","group_title":"SRG-APP-000431","third_party_tools":"","rule_title":"Trust must be established prior to enabling the loading of remote code in .Net 4.","rule_id":"SV-225233r961608","weight":"10.0","stig_uuid":"A16E2E6A-722B-1014-BDE7-9A88D219B55B","ccis":["CCI-002530"],"ia_controls":"","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000431","id":"V-225233"},"group_id":"V-225233","mitigations":"","documentable":"false","fix_text":".Net application code loaded from a remote source must be run in a controlled environment.  \n\nA controlled environment consists of a sandbox, such as running in an Internet Explorer host environment or employing OS based software access controls, such as AppLocker or Software Security Policies, when application design permits.  \n\nObtain documented IAO approvals for all remotely loaded code.","rule_id_src":"SV-225233r961608_rule","status":"open","group_id_src":"V-225233","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.dotnet:def:225233","href":"U_MS_DotNet_Framework_4-0_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV13-oval2.xml"},"reference_identifier":"4213","classification":"Unclassified","potential_impacts":"","severity":"medium","responsibility":"","comments":null,"rule_version":"APPNET0065","check_content":"Open Windows explorer and search for *.exe.config.\n\nSearch each config file found for the \"loadFromRemoteSources\" element.\n\nIf the loadFromRemoteSources element is enabled  \n(\"loadFromRemoteSources enabled = true\"), and the remotely loaded application is not run in a sandboxed environment, or if OS based software controls, such as AppLocker or Software Security Policies, are not utilized, this is a finding.\n","false_positives":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-41010","V-30968"],"uuid":"A16EF44C-722B-1014-A8FB-B81EE40DBBF9","discussion":"In the .NET Framework version 3.5 and earlier versions, if an application assembly loaded code/objects from a remote location, that assembly would run partially trusted with a permissions grant set that depended on the zone in which it was loaded. For example, if an assembly was loaded from a web site, it was loaded into the Internet zone and granted the Internet permission set. In other words, it was executed in an Internet sandbox.\n\nIf the same program is run in the .NET Framework version 4, an exception is thrown which effectively states; either explicitly create a sandbox for the assembly or run it in full trust.\n\nThe &lt;loadFromRemoteSources&gt; element specifies the assemblies that run partially trusted in earlier versions of the .NET Framework will be run fully trusted in the .NET Framework 4.\n\nIf loadFromRemoteSources is set to true, the remotely loaded application code is granted full trust.  This could create an integrity vulnerability on the system.  The required method to address this is to explicitly create a sandboxed environment for the remotely loaded code to run in rather than allowing remotely loaded code to run with full trust.\n\nThe appropriate level of trust must be established prior to enabling the loading of remote code in .Net 4 applications and that code must be run in a controlled environment.  The following is an example of the use of loadFromRemoteSources.\n\n&lt;configuration&gt;\n&lt;runtime&gt;\n    &lt;loadFromRemoteSources enabled=\"true\" \"https://my.dodorg.gov\" /&gt;\n    &lt;loadFromRemoteSources enabled=\"true\" \"https://192.168.0.*\" /&gt;\n    &lt;loadFromRemoteSources enabled=\"false\" \"*\" /&gt;\n&lt;/runtime&gt;\n&lt;/configuration&gt;","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-04-01T11:54:25\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Trust must be established prior to enabling the loading of remote code in .Net 4.)\nResult Analysis :        C:\\Users\\katessem\\OneDrive - Maxim Healthcare Services\\Desktop\\1- Projects &amp; Bios\\SaRACmd_17_01_2276_000\\SaRACmd.exe.config xpath = /configuration/runtime/loadFromRemoteSources/@enabled = 'true' failed test of 'case insensitive not equal' compared to 'true' \n"},{"security_override_guidance":"","group_title":"SRG-APP-000516","third_party_tools":"","rule_title":".NET default proxy settings must be reviewed and approved.","rule_id":"SV-225234r961863","weight":"10.0","stig_uuid":"A16E2E6A-722B-1014-BDE7-9A88D219B55B","ccis":["CCI-000366"],"ia_controls":"","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000516","id":"V-225234"},"group_id":"V-225234","mitigations":"","documentable":"false","fix_text":"Open Windows explorer and search for all \"*.exe.config\" and \"machine.config\" files.\n\nSearch each file for the \"defaultProxy\" element.\n\nClear the values contained in the \"defaultProxy\" element, and the \"bypasslist\", \"module\", and \"proxy\" child elements.\n\nThe IAO must provide documented approvals of any non-default proxy servers.","rule_id_src":"SV-225234r961863_rule","status":"not_a_finding","group_id_src":"V-225234","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.dotnet:def:225234","href":"U_MS_DotNet_Framework_4-0_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV13-oval2.xml"},"reference_identifier":"4213","classification":"Unclassified","potential_impacts":"","severity":"low","responsibility":"","comments":null,"rule_version":"APPNET0066","check_content":"Open Windows explorer and search for all \"*.exe.config\" and \"machine.config\" files.\n\nSearch each file for the \"defaultProxy\" element.\n\n&lt;defaultProxy\n  enabled=\"true|false\"\n  useDefaultCredentials=\"true|false\"\n  &lt;bypasslist&gt; â¦ &lt;/bypasslist&gt;\n  &lt;proxy&gt; â¦ &lt;/proxy&gt;\n  &lt;module&gt; â¦ &lt;/module&gt;\n/&gt;\n\nIf the \"defaultProxy\" setting \"enabled=false\" or if the \"bypasslist\", \"module\", or \"proxy\" child elements have configuration entries and there are no documented approvals from the IAO, this is a finding.\n\n If the \"defaultProxy\" element is empty or ifÂ \"useSystemDefault =TrueâÂ then the framework is using default browser settings, this is not a finding.","false_positives":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-41014","V-30972"],"uuid":"A16EFBE8-722B-1014-A27D-8BD29177807E","discussion":"The .Net framework can be configured to utilize a different proxy or altogether bypass the default proxy settings in the client's browser.  This may lead to the framework using a proxy that is not approved for use.  If the proxy is malicious, this could lead to a loss of application integrity and confidentiality.","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-04-01T11:54:25\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :   true (One or more child tests must be true. (OR))\nTest            :     true (If the defaultProxy setting enabled=false this is a finding)\nTest            :     true (DefaultProxy bypasslist should not exist)\nTest            :     true (DefaultProxy module should not exist)\nTest            :     true (DefaultProxy proxy should not exist)\nTest            :   true (If the 'defaultProxy' element is empty or if 'useSystemDefault =True' then the framework is using default browser settings, this is not a finding.)\n"},{"security_override_guidance":"","group_title":"SRG-APP-000095","third_party_tools":"","rule_title":"Event tracing for Windows (ETW) for Common Language Runtime events must be enabled.","rule_id":"SV-225235r960891","weight":"10.0","stig_uuid":"A16E2E6A-722B-1014-BDE7-9A88D219B55B","ccis":["CCI-000130"],"ia_controls":"","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000095","id":"V-225235"},"group_id":"V-225235","mitigations":"","documentable":"false","fix_text":"Open Windows explorer and search for all .NET config files including application config files (*.exe.config).\n\nExamine the configuration settings for \n&lt;etwEnable enabled=\"false\" /&gt;.\n\nEnable ETW Tracing by setting the etwEnable flag to \"true\" or obtain documented IAO approvals.","rule_id_src":"SV-225235r960891_rule","status":"not_a_finding","group_id_src":"V-225235","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.dotnet:def:12","href":"U_MS_DotNet_Framework_4-0_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV13-oval.xml"},"reference_identifier":"4213","classification":"Unclassified","potential_impacts":"","severity":"medium","responsibility":"","comments":null,"rule_version":"APPNET0067","check_content":"Open Windows explorer and search for all .NET config files including application config files (*.exe.config)\n\nNOTE:\nBeginning with Windows Vista and Windows Server 2008, ETW Tracing is enabled by default and the \"etwEnable\" setting is not required in order for Event Tracing to be enabled.  An etwEnable setting of \"true\" IS required in earlier versions of Windows as ETW is disabled by default. \n\nExamine the configuration settings for \n&lt;etwEnable enabled=\"false\" /&gt;.\n\nIf the \"etwEnable\" element is set to \"true\", this is not a finding.\n\nIf the \"etwEnable\" element is set to \"false\" and documented approvals by the IAO are not provided, this is a finding.\n","false_positives":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-41075","V-31026"],"uuid":"A16F03D7-722B-1014-8F08-A73EF7211BEF","discussion":"Event tracing captures information about applications utilizing the .NET CLR and the .NET CLR itself. This includes security oriented information, such as Strong Name and Authenticode verification.  \n\nBeginning with Windows Vista, ETW is enabled by default however, the .Net CLR and .Net applications can be configured to not utilize Event Tracing. If ETW event tracing is disabled, critical events that occurred within the runtime will not be captured in event logs.","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-04-01T11:54:25\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Event tracing for Windows (ETW) for Common Language Runtime events is enabled for application configiguration files)\nTest            :   true (Event tracing for Windows (ETW) for Common Language Runtime events is enabled for machine configiguration files)\n"},{"security_override_guidance":"","group_title":"SRG-APP-000431","third_party_tools":"","rule_title":"Software utilizing .Net 4.0 must be identified and relevant access controls configured.","rule_id":"SV-225236r1069477","weight":"10.0","stig_uuid":"A16E2E6A-722B-1014-BDE7-9A88D219B55B","ccis":["CCI-002530"],"ia_controls":"","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000431","id":"V-225236"},"group_id":"V-225236","mitigations":"","documentable":"false","fix_text":"Document the existence of all .Net 4.0 applications that are not provided by the host Windows OS or the Windows Secure Host Baseline (SHB).\n\nDocument the corresponding runtime hosts that are used to invoke the applications.\n\nDocument the applications security control requirements (restricting application access to resources or user access to the application).","rule_id_src":"SV-225236r1069477_rule","status":"not_reviewed","group_id_src":"V-225236","check_content_ref":{"name":"ocil:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.dotnet:questionnaire:2701","href":"U_MS_DotNet_Framework_4-0_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV13-ocil.xml"},"reference_identifier":"4213","classification":"Unclassified","potential_impacts":"","severity":"medium","responsibility":"","comments":null,"rule_version":"APPNET0070","check_content":"This requirement does not apply to the \"caspol.exe\" assembly or other assemblies provided with the Windows OS or the Windows Secure Host Baseline (SHB).\n\nAsk the system administrator to provide documentation that identifies:\n\n- Each .Net 4.0 application run on the system.\n- The .Net runtime host that invokes the application. \n- The security measures employed to control application access to system resources or user access to application.\n\nFor additional insight run: tasklist /fi \"modules eq mscoree.dll\"\n\nIf all .Net applications, runtime hosts and security protections have been documented or if there are no .Net 4.0 applications existing on the system, this is not a finding.\n\nIf there is no documentation that identifies the existence of .NET 4.0 applications or the lack thereof, this is a finding.\n\nIf the runtime hosts have not been identified, this is a finding.\n\nIf the security protections have not been identified, this is a finding.\n","false_positives":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-41030","V-30986"],"uuid":"A16F0BAA-722B-1014-A964-C9014FB77DA4","discussion":"With the advent of .Net 4.0, the .Net framework no longer directly configures or enforces security policy for .Net applications.  This task is now relegated to the operating system layer and the security protections built-in to .Net application \"runtime hosts\" that run on the O.S. \n\nExamples of these .Net \"runtime hosts\" include; Internet Explorer, Windows Shell, ASP.NET, Database Engines or any other \"runtime hosts\" that utilize .Net and load the .Net CLR.\n\nSecurity protections include utilizing runtime host security controls such as sandboxing to restrict or control application behavior as designed or required.  \n\nTo compensate for these design changes, Windows provides native solutions such as Software Security Policies (SSP) and Application Locker (AL) which are technologies that can be implemented via Group Policy (GPO).  SSP, AL and similar third party solutions serve to restrict execution of applications, scripts and libraries based upon cryptographic hash, security zones, path and certificate values that are associated with the application files.  Additionally, application developers will utilize \"sandboxing\" techniques within their code in order to isolate 3rd party code libraries from critical system resources.\n\nIn order to assign protections to .Net 4.0 applications, the applications must first be identified and the appropriate hosting security mechanisms configured to accomplish that task.  \n\n.Net STIG guidance cannot be applied if .Net applications are not identified and documented.  The lack of an application inventory introduces confidentiality, availability and integrity vulnerabilities to the system.","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-04-01T11:54:25\nResult: notcheckedCriteria        : NOT_TESTED (All child tests must be true.)\nTest            :   NOT_TESTED (CAT II, V-225236, SV-225236r1069477, SRG-APP-000431)\n"},{"security_override_guidance":"","group_title":"SRG-APP-000219","third_party_tools":"","rule_title":"Remoting Services TCP channels must utilize authentication and encryption.","rule_id":"SV-225237r1043178","weight":"10.0","stig_uuid":"A16E2E6A-722B-1014-BDE7-9A88D219B55B","ccis":["CCI-001184"],"ia_controls":"","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000219","id":"V-225237"},"group_id":"V-225237","mitigations":"","documentable":"false","fix_text":"If .NET remoting with TCP channel is not used, this fix is Not Applicable.\n\nEnsure encryption and message integrity are used for TCP remoting channels.\n\nTCP remoting connections are protected via the secure=true configuration parameter.\n&lt;channels&gt;\n   &lt;channel ref=\"tcp\" secure=\"true\" /&gt;\n&lt;/channels&gt;\n\nInclude the secure=\"true\" flag in the channel ref parameter of the machine.config and [application name].exe.config file if the [application name].exe.config file exists on the system.","rule_id_src":"SV-225237r1043178_rule","status":"not_a_finding","group_id_src":"V-225237","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.dotnet:def:225237","href":"U_MS_DotNet_Framework_4-0_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV13-oval2.xml"},"reference_identifier":"4213","classification":"Unclassified","potential_impacts":"","severity":"medium","responsibility":"","comments":null,"rule_version":"APPNET0071","check_content":"If .NET remoting with TCP channel is not used, this check is Not Applicable.\n\nCheck the machine.config and the [application executable name].exe.config configuration files. \n\nFor 32-bit systems, the \"machine.config\" file is contained in the following folder. %SYSTEMROOT%\\Microsoft.NET\\Framework\\v4.0.30319\\Config \n\nFor 64-bit systems, the \"machine.config\" file is contained in the following folder. %SYSTEMROOT%\\Microsoft.NET\\Framework64\\v4.0.30319\\Config.\n\nMicrosoft specifies locating the application config file in the same folder as the application executable (.exe) file. However, the developer does have the capability to specify a different location when the application is compiled.  Therefore, if the config file is not found in the application home folder, a search of the system is required. If the [application name].exe.config file is not found on the system, then only a check of the machine.config file is required.\n\nSample machine/application config file:\n\n&lt;application name=âremoteserverâ&gt; \n  &lt;service&gt; \n    &lt;activated type=âsample.my.object, myobjectsâ/&gt; \n  &lt;/service&gt; \n  &lt;channels&gt; \n    &lt;channel ref=âtcp serverâ port=â6134â/&gt; \n  &lt;/channels&gt; \n&lt;/application&gt;\n\n&lt;serverProviders&gt;\n  &lt;provider ref=\"wsdl\" /&gt;\n  &lt;formatter ref=\"soap\" typeFilterLevel=\"Full\" /&gt; \n  &lt;formatter ref=\"binary\" typeFilterLevel=\"Full\" /&gt; \n&lt;/serverProviders&gt; \n\nMicrosoft provides three \"channels\" that are used for remoting connectivity. They are the HTTP, TCP, and IPC channels. The channel that is used is specified via the &lt;channels&gt; element in the config file.  \n\nTCP channel example:\n&lt;channel ref=âtcpâ port=â6134â secure=\"true\"/&gt; \n\nThe TCP channel provides encryption and message integrity when the \"secure\" flag is set to \"true\" as shown in the above example.\n\nIf the \"secure\" flag is not set to \"true\" for the TCP channel, this is a finding.","false_positives":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-42341","V-32025"],"uuid":"A16F1410-722B-1014-B8C8-B5A7C5741EDA","discussion":"Note: Microsoft recommends using the Windows Communication Framework (WCF) rather than .Net remoting. New development projects should refrain from using .Net remoting capabilities whenever possible.\n\n.NET remoting provides the capability to build widely distributed applications. The application components may reside all on one computer or they may be spread out across the enclave. .NET client applications can make remoting calls to use objects in other processes on the same computer or on any other computer that is reachable over the network. .NET remoting can also be used to communicate with other application domains within the same process. Remoting is achieved via the exposure of endpoints that can be used to establish remote connectivity.\n\nNormally when application code attempts to access a protected resource, a stack walk is performed to ensure that all stack frames have permission to access the resource. However, with .Net 4.0, when a call is made on a remote object, this stack walk is not performed across the remoting boundary. The .Net remoting infrastructure requires FullTrust permission to execute on either the client or the server. \n\nDue to the fact that FullTrust permission is required, Remoting endpoints should be authenticated and encrypted in order to protect the system and the data. \n\nMicrosoft provides three different \"channels\" that are used for remoting. They are HTTP, TCP, and IPC.\n\nAny unauthorized use of a remoting application provides unauthorized access with FullTrust permissions to the system. This can potentially result in a loss of system integrity or confidentiality.","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-04-01T11:54:25\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Remoting Services TCP channels must utilize authentication and encryption.)\n"},{"security_override_guidance":"","group_title":"SRG-APP-000383","third_party_tools":"","rule_title":"Update and configure the .NET Framework to support TLS.","rule_id":"SV-225238r1069480","weight":"10.0","stig_uuid":"A16E2E6A-722B-1014-BDE7-9A88D219B55B","ccis":["CCI-001762"],"ia_controls":"","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000383","id":"V-225238"},"group_id":"V-225238","mitigations":"","documentable":"false","fix_text":"1. SchUseStrongCrypto enabled:\n\nUse regedit to access the following registry key.\n\nFor 32-bit systems:\nHKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\.NETFramework\\v4.0.30319\\\n\nFor 64-bit systems: \nHKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\.NETFramework\\v4.0.30319\\\nHKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\\Wow6432Node\\Microsoft\\.NETFramework\\v4.0.30319\\\n\nModify or create the following Windows registry value: SchUseStrongCrypto.\n\nSet SchUseStrongCrypto to a REG_DWORD value of \"1\".\n\n2. SystemDefaultTlsVersions enabled (.NET Framework &gt;4.6):\nFor 64-bit Windows, create a .reg file with the following content and apply it:\nWindows Registry Editor Version 5.00\n\n[HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\.NETFramework\\v4.0.30319]\n\"SystemDefaultTlsVersions\"=dword:00000001\n\n[HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\\Wow6432Node\\Microsoft\\.NETFramework\\v4.0.30319]\n\"SystemDefaultTlsVersions\"=dword:00000001\n\n3. Restart the system for changes to take effect.","rule_id_src":"SV-225238r1069480_rule","status":"open","group_id_src":"V-225238","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.dotnet:def:16","href":"U_MS_DotNet_Framework_4-0_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV13-oval.xml"},"reference_identifier":"4213","classification":"Unclassified","potential_impacts":"","severity":"medium","responsibility":"","comments":null,"rule_version":"APPNET0075","check_content":"In older Windows systems (Windows Server 2012 or earlier), TLS 1.2 must be enabled systemwide by setting \"SchUseStrongCrypto\".\n\nSystemDefaultTlsVersions is a configuration switch in .NET Framework (starting from 4.6) that allows the application to use the default TLS version supported by the underlying Windows operating system instead of hardcoding a specific TLS version (like TLS 1.2).\n\nCheck Registry:\nUse regedit to review the following Windows registry keys:\nFor 32-bit systems: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\.NETFramework\\v4.0.30319\\\n\nFor 64 bit systems:\nHKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\.NETFramework\\v4.0.30319\\\nHKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\\Wow6432Node\\Microsoft\\.NETFramework\\v4.0.30319\\\n\n1. If the \"SchUseStrongCrypto\" value name does not exist, or is not a REG_DWORD type set to \"1\", this is a finding.\n\n2. For .NET Framework &gt;4.6, use the default TLS version supported by the underlying Windows operating system.\nIf the \"SystemDefaultTlsVersions\" value name does not exist, or is not a REG_DWORD type set to \"1\", this is a finding.\n\nNote: The SchUseStrongCrypto setting allows .NET to use TLS 1.1 and TLS 1.2. The SystemDefaultTlsVersions setting allows .NET to use the OS configuration.","false_positives":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-96209","V-81495"],"uuid":"A16F1C04-722B-1014-B3E1-91D4D55C8A60","discussion":"Use of the RC4 cipher in TLS could allow an attacker to perform man-in-the-middle attacks and recover plaintext from encrypted sessions. Applications that target .Net version 4.x running on multiple Windows versions could be vulnerable to these types of attacks. The registry settings in this requirement will prevent .Net applications that target the 4.x framework from selecting and utilizing the Schannel.dll RC4 cipher for TLS connections. Applications that use TLS when connecting to remote systems will perform a handshake and negotiate the TLS version and cipher that is to be used between the client and the server. This is standard protocol for all TLS connections. If the server and client are not configured to use the same TLS version and cipher, the TLS connection may fail. Applications should be tested with these registry settings prior to production implementation of the fix in order to avoid application outages.","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-04-01T11:54:25\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (One or more child tests must be true. (OR))\nCriteria        :   false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :     true (One or more child tests must be true. (OR))\nTest            :       false (32-bit operating system check)\nResult Analysis :            osarchitecture = '64-bit' failed test of 'equals' compared to '32-bit' \nTest            :       true (SchUseStrongCrypto key for 32 bit applications on a 64 bit system)\nTest            :     false (.NET Framework 4.6 or newer is installed) (negated)\nResult Analysis :          Test result was 'true', but content instructed to negate result to 'false'\nTest            :     true (SchUseStrongCrypto key for applications that match the bitness of the system)\nCriteria        :   false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :     false (One or more child tests must be true. (OR))\nTest            :       false (32-bit operating system check)\nResult Analysis :            osarchitecture = '64-bit' failed test of 'equals' compared to '32-bit' \nTest            :       false (SystemDefaultTlsVersions key for 32 bit applications on a 64 bit system)\nResult Analysis :            Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\\Wow6432Node\\Microsoft\\.NETFramework\\v4.0.30319\\SystemDefaultTlsVersions'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\nTest            :     true (.NET Framework 4.6 or newer is installed)\nTest            :     false (SystemDefaultTlsVersions key for applications that match the bitness of the system)\nResult Analysis :          Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\.NETFramework\\v4.0.30319\\SystemDefaultTlsVersions'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n"}],"size":16,"uuid":"A16E2E6A-722B-1014-BDE7-9A88D219B55B","display_name":"Microsoft DotNet Framework 4.0","stig_id":"MS_Dot_Net_Framework","release_info":"Release: 7 Benchmark Date: 02 Jul 2025","version":"2"},{"stig_name":"Microsoft Edge Security Technical Implementation Guide","reference_identifier":"5280","classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","rules":[{"security_override_guidance":"","group_title":"SRG-APP-000039","third_party_tools":"","rule_title":"User control of proxy settings must be disabled.","rule_id":"SV-235719r1156558","weight":"10.0","stig_uuid":"A516DDF1-722B-1014-B1EE-8476FA977258","ccis":["CCI-001414"],"ia_controls":"","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000039","id":"V-235719"},"group_id":"V-235719","mitigations":"","documentable":"false","fix_text":"Set the policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Proxy server/Proxy Settings\" to \"Enabled\" and define a value for \"ProxyMode\".\n\n\"ProxyMode\" must be defined and set to one of the following: \"direct\", \"system\", \"auto_detect\", \"fixed_servers\", or \"pac_script\".\n\nConsult Microsoft documentation for proper configuration of the text string required to define the \"Proxy Settings\" value.\n\nExample:  {\"ProxyMode\": \"fixed_servers\", \"ProxyServer\": \"127.0.0.1:8080\"}\n\n\"ProxyPacUrl\", \"ProxyServer\", or \"ProxyBypassList\" are optional.","rule_id_src":"SV-235719r1156558_rule","status":"open","group_id_src":"V-235719","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.edge:def:235719","href":"U_MS_Edge_V2R4_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV14-oval2.xml"},"reference_identifier":"5280","classification":"Unclassified","potential_impacts":"","severity":"low","responsibility":"","comments":null,"rule_version":"EDGE-00-000001","check_content":"The policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Proxy server/Proxy Settings\" must be \"Enabled\", and have a \"Proxy Settings\" value defined for \"ProxyMode\".\n\n\"ProxyMode\" must be defined and set to one of the following: \"direct\", \"system\", \"auto_detect\", \"fixed_servers\", or \"pac_script\".\n\nConsult Microsoft documentation for proper configuration of the text string required to define the \"Proxy Settings\" value.\n\nExample:  {\"ProxyMode\": \"fixed_servers\", \"ProxyServer\": \"123.123.123.123:8080\"}\n\nValues for \"ProxyPacUrl\", \"ProxyServer\", or \"ProxyBypassList\" are optional.\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\nHKLM\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\n\nIf the REG_SZ value for \"ProxySettings\" does not have \"ProxyMode\" configured, this is a finding.","false_positives":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"uuid":"A51C2373-722B-1014-B082-D0300BCED88D","discussion":"This action configures the proxy settings for Microsoft Edge.\n\nIf this policy is enabled, Microsoft Edge ignores all proxy-related options specified from the command line.\n\nIf this policy is not configured, users can choose their own proxy settings.\n\nThis policy overrides the following individual policies:\n- ProxyMode.\n- ProxyPacUrl. \n- ProxyServer. \n- ProxyBypassList.\n\nSetting the ProxySettings policy accepts the following fields:\n- ProxyMode, which allows for the proxy server used by Microsoft Edge to be specified and prevents users from changing proxy settings.\n- ProxyPacUrl, a URL to a proxy .pac file.\n- ProxyServer, a URL for the proxy server.\n- ProxyBypassList, a list of proxy hosts that Microsoft Edge bypasses.\n\nFor ProxyMode, the following values have the noted impact:\n- direct, a proxy is never used and all other fields are ignored.\n- system, the system's proxy is used and all other fields are ignored.\n- auto_detect, all other fields are ignored.\n- fixed_servers, the ProxyServer and ProxyBypassList fields are used.\n- pac_script, the ProxyPacUrl and ProxyBypassList fields are used.","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-04-01T11:55:42\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (User control of proxy settings must be disabled.)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\\ProxySettings'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n"},{"security_override_guidance":"","group_title":"SRG-APP-000073","third_party_tools":"","rule_title":"Bypassing Microsoft Defender SmartScreen prompts for sites must be disabled.","rule_id":"SV-235720r960852","weight":"10.0","stig_uuid":"A516DDF1-722B-1014-B1EE-8476FA977258","ccis":["CCI-000870"],"ia_controls":"","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000073","id":"V-235720"},"group_id":"V-235720","mitigations":"","documentable":"false","fix_text":"Set the policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/SmartScreen settings/Prevent bypassing Microsoft Defender SmartScreen prompts for sites\" to \"Enabled\".","rule_id_src":"SV-235720r960852_rule","status":"not_a_finding","group_id_src":"V-235720","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.edge:def:100","href":"U_MS_Edge_V2R4_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV14-oval.xml"},"reference_identifier":"5280","classification":"Unclassified","potential_impacts":"","severity":"medium","responsibility":"","comments":null,"rule_version":"EDGE-00-000002","check_content":"The policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/SmartScreen settings/Prevent bypassing Microsoft Defender SmartScreen prompts for sites\" must be set to \"Enabled\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\nHKLM\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\n\nIf the value for \"PreventSmartScreenPromptOverride\" is not set to \"REG_DWORD = 1\", this is a finding.\n\nIf this machine is on SIPRNet, this is Not Applicable.","false_positives":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"uuid":"A51C34EE-722B-1014-B1F4-B1190271553C","discussion":"This policy setting allows a decision to be made on whether users can override the Microsoft Defender SmartScreen warnings about potentially malicious websites.\n\nIf this setting is enabled, users cannot ignore Microsoft Defender SmartScreen warnings, and are blocked from continuing to the site.\n\nIf this setting is disabled or not configured, users can ignore Microsoft Defender SmartScreen warnings and continue to the site.","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-04-01T11:55:42\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Enable the setting 'Prevent bypassing Microsoft Defender SmartScreen prompts for sites')\n"},{"security_override_guidance":"","group_title":"SRG-APP-000073","third_party_tools":"","rule_title":"Bypassing of Microsoft Defender SmartScreen warnings about downloads must be disabled.","rule_id":"SV-235721r960852","weight":"10.0","stig_uuid":"A516DDF1-722B-1014-B1EE-8476FA977258","ccis":["CCI-000870"],"ia_controls":"","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000073","id":"V-235721"},"group_id":"V-235721","mitigations":"","documentable":"false","fix_text":"Set the policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/SmartScreen settings/Prevent bypassing of Microsoft Defender SmartScreen warnings about downloads\" must to \"Enabled\".","rule_id_src":"SV-235721r960852_rule","status":"open","group_id_src":"V-235721","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.edge:def:101","href":"U_MS_Edge_V2R4_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV14-oval.xml"},"reference_identifier":"5280","classification":"Unclassified","potential_impacts":"","severity":"medium","responsibility":"","comments":null,"rule_version":"EDGE-00-000003","check_content":"The policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/SmartScreen settings/Prevent bypassing of Microsoft Defender SmartScreen warnings about downloads\" must be set to \"Enabled\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\nHKLM\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\n\nIf the value for \"PreventSmartScreenPromptOverrideForFiles\" is not set to \"REG_DWORD = 1\", this is a finding.\n\nIf this machine is on SIPRNet, this is Not Applicable.","false_positives":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"uuid":"A51C421D-722B-1014-8302-F9FA08AB194F","discussion":"This policy setting allows a decision to be made on whether users can override Microsoft Defender SmartScreen warnings about unverified downloads.\n\nIf this setting is enabled, users cannot ignore Microsoft Defender SmartScreen warnings, and are prevented from completing the unverified downloads.\n\nIf this policy is disabled or not configured, users can ignore Microsoft Defender SmartScreen warnings and complete unverified downloads.","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-04-01T11:55:42\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Enable the setting 'Prevent bypassing Microsoft Defender SmartScreen warnings about downloads')\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\\PreventSmartScreenPromptOverrideForFiles'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n"},{"security_override_guidance":"","group_title":"SRG-APP-000073","third_party_tools":"","rule_title":"The list of domains for which Microsoft Defender SmartScreen will not trigger warnings must be allowlisted if used.","rule_id":"SV-235722r960852","weight":"10.0","stig_uuid":"A516DDF1-722B-1014-B1EE-8476FA977258","ccis":["CCI-000870"],"ia_controls":"","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000073","id":"V-235722"},"group_id":"V-235722","mitigations":"","documentable":"false","fix_text":"The policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/SmartScreen settings/Configure the list of domains for which Microsoft Defender SmartScreen will not trigger warnings\" may be set to \"allow\" for allowlisted domains.","rule_id_src":"SV-235722r960852_rule","status":"not_reviewed","group_id_src":"V-235722","check_content_ref":{"name":"ocil:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.edge:questionnaire:701","href":"U_MS_Edge_V2R4_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV14-ocil.xml"},"reference_identifier":"5280","classification":"Unclassified","potential_impacts":"","severity":"low","responsibility":"","comments":null,"rule_version":"EDGE-00-000004","check_content":"If this machine is on SIPRNet, this is Not Applicable.\n\nThis requirement for \"SmartScreenAllowListDomains\" is not required; this is optional.\n\nThe policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/SmartScreen settings/Configure the list of domains for which Microsoft Defender SmartScreen won't trigger warnings\" may be set to \"allow\" for allowlisted domains.\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\nHKLM\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\n\nSmartScreenAllowListDomains may be set as follows:\nHKLM\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\\SmartScreenAllowListDomains\\1 = mydomain.com\nHKLM\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\\SmartScreenAllowListDomains\\2 = myagency.mil\n\nIf configured, the list of domains for which Microsoft Defender SmartScreen will not trigger warnings may be allowlisted.","false_positives":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"uuid":"A51C4DA0-722B-1014-A8DA-CAF632F4A7D8","discussion":"Configure the list of Microsoft Defender SmartScreen trusted domains. This means Microsoft Defender SmartScreen will not check for potentially malicious resources, such as phishing software and other malware, if the source URLs match these domains. The Microsoft Defender SmartScreen download protection service will not check downloads hosted on these domains.\n\nIf this policy is enabled, Microsoft Defender SmartScreen trusts these domains. If the policy is disabled or not set, default Microsoft Defender SmartScreen protection is applied to all resources.","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-04-01T11:55:42\nResult: notcheckedCriteria        : NOT_TESTED (All child tests must be true.)\nTest            :   NOT_TESTED (CAT III, V-235722, SV-235722r960852, SRG-APP-000073)\n"},{"security_override_guidance":"","group_title":"SRG-APP-000080","third_party_tools":"","rule_title":"InPrivate mode must be disabled.","rule_id":"SV-235723r960864","weight":"10.0","stig_uuid":"A516DDF1-722B-1014-B1EE-8476FA977258","ccis":["CCI-000166"],"ia_controls":"","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000080","id":"V-235723"},"group_id":"V-235723","mitigations":"","documentable":"false","fix_text":"Set the policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Configure InPrivate mode availability\" to \"enabled\" and select \"InPrivate mode disabled\".","rule_id_src":"SV-235723r960864_rule","status":"open","group_id_src":"V-235723","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.edge:def:102","href":"U_MS_Edge_V2R4_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV14-oval.xml"},"reference_identifier":"5280","classification":"Unclassified","potential_impacts":"","severity":"medium","responsibility":"","comments":null,"rule_version":"EDGE-00-000005","check_content":"The policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Configure InPrivate mode availability\" must be set to \"enabled\" with the option value set to \"InPrivate mode disabled\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\nHKLM\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\n\nIf the value for \"InPrivateModeAvailability\" is not set to \"REG_DWORD = 1\", this is a finding.","false_positives":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"uuid":"A51C5899-722B-1014-A0BC-D54A019455B6","discussion":"This setting specifies whether the user can open pages in InPrivate mode in Microsoft Edge.\n\nIf this policy is not configured or set it to \"Enabled\", users can open pages in InPrivate mode.\n\nSet this policy to \"Disabled\" to stop users from using InPrivate mode.\n\nSet this policy to \"Forced\" to always use InPrivate mode.\n\nPolicy options mapping:\n- Enabled (0) = InPrivate mode available\n- Disabled (1) = InPrivate mode disabled\n- Forced (2) = InPrivate mode forced","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-04-01T11:55:42\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (InPrivate mode is disabled)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\\InPrivateModeAvailability'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n"},{"security_override_guidance":"","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","third_party_tools":"","rule_title":"Background processing must be disabled.","rule_id":"SV-235724r960963","weight":"10.0","stig_uuid":"A516DDF1-722B-1014-B1EE-8476FA977258","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"ia_controls":"","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000141","id":"V-235724"},"group_id":"V-235724","mitigations":"","documentable":"false","fix_text":"Set the policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Continue running background apps after Microsoft Edge closes\" to \"Disabled\".","rule_id_src":"SV-235724r960963_rule","status":"open","group_id_src":"V-235724","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.edge:def:103","href":"U_MS_Edge_V2R4_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV14-oval.xml"},"reference_identifier":"5280","classification":"Unclassified","potential_impacts":"","severity":"medium","responsibility":"","comments":null,"rule_version":"EDGE-00-000006","check_content":"The policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Continue running background apps after Microsoft Edge closes\" must be set to \"Disabled\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\nHKLM\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\n\nIf the value for \"BackgroundModeEnabled\" is not set to \"REG_DWORD = 0\", this is a finding.","false_positives":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"uuid":"A51C640A-722B-1014-9F8A-F53CE605A5FA","discussion":"Background processing allows Microsoft Edge processes to start at OS sign-in and keep running after the last browser window is closed. In this scenario, background apps and the current browsing session remain active, including any session cookies. An open background process displays an icon in the system tray, and can be closed from there.\n\nIf this policy is enabled, background mode is turned on.\n\nIf this policy is disabled, background mode is turned off.\n\nIf this policy is not configured, background mode is initially turned off, and the user can configure its behavior in edge://settings/system.","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-04-01T11:55:42\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Enable the setting 'Continue running background apps after Microsoft Edge closes')\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\\BackgroundModeEnabled'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n"},{"security_override_guidance":"","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","third_party_tools":"","rule_title":"The ability of sites to show pop-ups must be disabled.","rule_id":"SV-235725r960963","weight":"10.0","stig_uuid":"A516DDF1-722B-1014-B1EE-8476FA977258","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"ia_controls":"","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000141","id":"V-235725"},"group_id":"V-235725","mitigations":"","documentable":"false","fix_text":"Set the policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Content settings/Default pop-up window setting\" to \"Enabled\" with the option value set to \"Do not allow any site to show  pop-ups\".","rule_id_src":"SV-235725r960963_rule","status":"open","group_id_src":"V-235725","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.edge:def:104","href":"U_MS_Edge_V2R4_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV14-oval.xml"},"reference_identifier":"5280","classification":"Unclassified","potential_impacts":"","severity":"medium","responsibility":"","comments":null,"rule_version":"EDGE-00-000008","check_content":"The policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Content settings/Default pop-up window setting\" must be set to \"Enabled\" with the option value set to \"Do not allow any site to show  pop-ups\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\nHKLM\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\n\nIf the value for DefaultPopupsSetting is not set to \"REG_DWORD = 2\", this is a finding.","false_positives":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"uuid":"A51C6E2B-722B-1014-87AF-B3501B574EED","discussion":"Set whether websites can show pop-up windows. Pop-ups can be allowed on all websites (\"AllowPopups\") or blocked on all sites (\"BlockPopups\").\n\nIf this policy is configured, pop-up windows are blocked by default, and users can change this setting.\n\nPolicy options mapping:\n- AllowPopups (1) = Allow all sites to show pop-ups.\n- BlockPopups (2) = Do not allow any site to show pop-ups.","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-04-01T11:55:42\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Do not allow any site to show pop-ups)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\\DefaultPopupsSetting'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n"},{"security_override_guidance":"","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","third_party_tools":"","rule_title":"The default search provider must be set to use an encrypted connection.","rule_id":"SV-235726r960963","weight":"10.0","stig_uuid":"A516DDF1-722B-1014-B1EE-8476FA977258","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"ia_controls":"","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000141","id":"V-235726"},"group_id":"V-235726","mitigations":"","documentable":"false","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Manage Search Engines\".","rule_id_src":"SV-235726r960963_rule","status":"open","group_id_src":"V-235726","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.edge:def:235726","href":"U_MS_Edge_V2R4_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV14-oval2.xml"},"reference_identifier":"5280","classification":"Unclassified","potential_impacts":"","severity":"medium","responsibility":"","comments":null,"rule_version":"EDGE-00-000009","check_content":"The policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Manage Search Engines\" must be configured.\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\nHKLM\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\n\nExample REG_SZ value text for \"ManagedSearchEngines\":\n[{\"allow_search_engine_discovery\": false},{\"is_default\": true,\"name\": \"Microsoft Bing\",\"keyword\": \"bing\",\"search_url\": \"https://www.bing.com/search?q={searchTerms}\"},{\"name\": \"Google\",\"keyword\": \"google\",\"search_url\": \"https://www.google.com/search?q={searchTerms}\"}]\n\nIf any of the search URLs in the list do not begin with \"https\", this is a finding.","false_positives":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"uuid":"A51C7997-722B-1014-99BF-F83CE8D6B054","discussion":"Allows a list of list of up to 10 search engines to be configured, one of which must be marked as the default search engine. The encoding does not need to be specified. Starting in Microsoft Edge 80, the suggest_url and image_search_url parameters are optional. The optional parameter, image_search_post_params (consists of comma-separated name/value pairs), is available starting in Microsoft Edge 80.\n\nStarting in Microsoft Edge 83, search engine discovery can be enabled with the allow_search_engine_discovery optional parameter. This parameter must be the first item in the list. If allow_search_engine_discovery is not specified, search engine discovery will be disabled by default. Starting in Microsoft Edge 84, this policy can be set as a recommended policy to allow search provider discovery. The allow_search_engine_discovery optional parameter does not need to be added.\n\nIf this policy is enabled, users cannot add, remove, or change any search engine in the list. Users can set their default search engine to any search engine in the list.\n\nIf this policy is disabled or not configured, users can modify the search engines list as desired.","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-04-01T11:55:42\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (The default search provider URL must be set to perform encrypted searches.)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\\ManagedSearchEngines'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n"},{"security_override_guidance":"","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","third_party_tools":"","rule_title":"Data Synchronization must be disabled.","rule_id":"SV-235727r960963","weight":"10.0","stig_uuid":"A516DDF1-722B-1014-B1EE-8476FA977258","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"ia_controls":"","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000141","id":"V-235727"},"group_id":"V-235727","mitigations":"","documentable":"false","fix_text":"Set the policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Disable synchronization of data using Microsoft sync services\" to \"Enabled\".","rule_id_src":"SV-235727r960963_rule","status":"open","group_id_src":"V-235727","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.edge:def:105","href":"U_MS_Edge_V2R4_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV14-oval.xml"},"reference_identifier":"5280","classification":"Unclassified","potential_impacts":"","severity":"low","responsibility":"","comments":null,"rule_version":"EDGE-00-000010","check_content":"The policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Disable synchronization of data using Microsoft sync services\" must be set to \"Enabled\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\nHKLM\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\n\nIf the value for \"SyncDisabled\" is not set to \"REG_DWORD = 1\", this is a finding.","false_positives":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"uuid":"A51C86F9-722B-1014-9B82-E4CBC0C76DD3","discussion":"Disables data synchronization in Microsoft Edge. This policy also prevents the sync consent prompt from appearing.\n\nIf this policy is not set or applied as recommended, users will be able to turn sync on or off. If this policy is applied as mandatory, users will not be able to turn on sync.","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-04-01T11:55:42\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Disable Microsoft Edge data synchronization)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\\SyncDisabled'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n"},{"security_override_guidance":"","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","third_party_tools":"","rule_title":"Network prediction must be disabled.","rule_id":"SV-235728r960963","weight":"10.0","stig_uuid":"A516DDF1-722B-1014-B1EE-8476FA977258","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"ia_controls":"","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000141","id":"V-235728"},"group_id":"V-235728","mitigations":"","documentable":"false","fix_text":"Set the policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Enable network prediction\" to \"Enabled\" with the option value set to \"Don't predict network actions on any network connection\".","rule_id_src":"SV-235728r960963_rule","status":"open","group_id_src":"V-235728","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.edge:def:106","href":"U_MS_Edge_V2R4_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV14-oval.xml"},"reference_identifier":"5280","classification":"Unclassified","potential_impacts":"","severity":"medium","responsibility":"","comments":null,"rule_version":"EDGE-00-000011","check_content":"The policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Enable network prediction\" must be set to \"Enabled\" with the option value set to \"Don't predict network actions on any network connection\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\nHKLM\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\n\nIf the value for NetworkPredictionOptions is not set to \"REG_DWORD = 2\", this is a finding.","false_positives":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"uuid":"A51C9129-722B-1014-A813-BB1EA635376A","discussion":"Enables network prediction and prevents users from changing this setting.\n\nThis controls DNS prefetching, TCP and SSL pre-connection, and pre-rendering of web pages.\n\nIf this policy is not configured, network prediction is enabled but the user can change it.\n\nPolicy options mapping:\n- NetworkPredictionAlways (0) = Predict network actions on any network connection.\n- NetworkPredictionWifiOnly (1) = Not supported; if this value is used it will be treated as if \"Predict network actions on any network connection\" (0) was set.\n- NetworkPredictionNever (2) = Do not predict network actions on any network connection.","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-04-01T11:55:42\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Disable network prediction for MS Edge)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\\NetworkPredictionOptions'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n"},{"security_override_guidance":"","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","third_party_tools":"","rule_title":"Search suggestions must be disabled.","rule_id":"SV-235729r960963","weight":"10.0","stig_uuid":"A516DDF1-722B-1014-B1EE-8476FA977258","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"ia_controls":"","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000141","id":"V-235729"},"group_id":"V-235729","mitigations":"","documentable":"false","fix_text":"Set the policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Enable search suggestions\" to \"Disabled\".","rule_id_src":"SV-235729r960963_rule","status":"open","group_id_src":"V-235729","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.edge:def:107","href":"U_MS_Edge_V2R4_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV14-oval.xml"},"reference_identifier":"5280","classification":"Unclassified","potential_impacts":"","severity":"medium","responsibility":"","comments":null,"rule_version":"EDGE-00-000012","check_content":"The policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Enable search suggestions\" must be set to \"Disabled\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\nHKLM\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\n\nIf the value for \"SearchSuggestEnabled\" is not set to \"REG_DWORD = 0\", this is a finding.","false_positives":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"uuid":"A51C9D4A-722B-1014-9FC7-85D542341715","discussion":"Enables web search suggestions in the Microsoft Edge Address Bar and Auto-Suggest List, and prevents users from changing this policy.\n\nIf this policy is enabled, web search suggestions are used.\n\nIf this policy is disabled, web search suggestions are never used; however, local history and local favorites suggestions still appear. If this policy is disabled, neither the typed characters nor the URLs visited will be included in telemetry to Microsoft.\n\nIf this policy is not set, search suggestions are enabled but the user can change that.","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-04-01T11:55:42\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Disable the setting 'Enable search suggestions')\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\\SearchSuggestEnabled'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n"},{"security_override_guidance":"","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","third_party_tools":"","rule_title":"Importing of autofill form data must be disabled.","rule_id":"SV-235730r960963","weight":"10.0","stig_uuid":"A516DDF1-722B-1014-B1EE-8476FA977258","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"ia_controls":"","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000141","id":"V-235730"},"group_id":"V-235730","mitigations":"","documentable":"false","fix_text":"Set the policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Allow importing of autofill form data\" to \"disabled\".","rule_id_src":"SV-235730r960963_rule","status":"open","group_id_src":"V-235730","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.edge:def:108","href":"U_MS_Edge_V2R4_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV14-oval.xml"},"reference_identifier":"5280","classification":"Unclassified","potential_impacts":"","severity":"medium","responsibility":"","comments":null,"rule_version":"EDGE-00-000013","check_content":"The policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Allow importing of autofill form data\" must be set to \"disabled\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\nHKLM\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\n\nIf the value for \"ImportAutofillFormData\" is not set to \"REG_DWORD = 0\", this is a finding.","false_positives":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"uuid":"A51CA59A-722B-1014-A7A2-EE2638596EBB","discussion":"Allows users to import autofill form data from another browser into Microsoft Edge.\n\nIf this policy is enabled, the option to manually import autofill data is automatically selected.\n\nIf this policy is disabled, autofill form data is not imported at first run, and users cannot import it manually.\n\nIf this policy is not configured, autofill data is imported at first run, and users can choose whether to import this data manually during later browsing sessions.\n\nThis policy cannot be set as a recommendation. This means that Microsoft Edge will import autofill data on first run, but users can select or clear autofill data option during manual import.","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-04-01T11:55:42\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Disable importing of autofill form data)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\\ImportAutofillFormData'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n"},{"security_override_guidance":"","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","third_party_tools":"","rule_title":"Importing of browser settings must be disabled.","rule_id":"SV-235731r960963","weight":"10.0","stig_uuid":"A516DDF1-722B-1014-B1EE-8476FA977258","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"ia_controls":"","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000141","id":"V-235731"},"group_id":"V-235731","mitigations":"","documentable":"false","fix_text":"Set the policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Allow importing of browser settings\" to \"disabled\".","rule_id_src":"SV-235731r960963_rule","status":"open","group_id_src":"V-235731","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.edge:def:109","href":"U_MS_Edge_V2R4_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV14-oval.xml"},"reference_identifier":"5280","classification":"Unclassified","potential_impacts":"","severity":"low","responsibility":"","comments":null,"rule_version":"EDGE-00-000014","check_content":"The policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Allow importing of browser settings\" must be set to \"disabled\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\nHKLM\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\n\nIf the value for \"ImportBrowserSettings\" is not set to \"REG_DWORD = 0\", this is a finding.","false_positives":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"uuid":"A51CAC7C-722B-1014-AD99-99EF8423753B","discussion":"Allows users to import browser settings from another browser into Microsoft Edge.\n\nIf this policy is enabled, the Browser settings check box is automatically selected in the Import browser data dialog box.\n\nIf this policy is disabled, browser settings are not imported at first run, and users cannot import them manually.\n\nIf this policy is not configured, browser settings are imported at first run, and users can choose whether to import them manually during later browsing sessions.","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-04-01T11:55:42\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Disable importing of autofill form data)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\\ImportBrowserSettings'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n"},{"security_override_guidance":"","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","third_party_tools":"","rule_title":"Importing of cookies must be disabled.","rule_id":"SV-235732r960963","weight":"10.0","stig_uuid":"A516DDF1-722B-1014-B1EE-8476FA977258","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"ia_controls":"","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000141","id":"V-235732"},"group_id":"V-235732","mitigations":"","documentable":"false","fix_text":"Set the policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Allow importing of cookies\" to \"disabled\".","rule_id_src":"SV-235732r960963_rule","status":"open","group_id_src":"V-235732","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.edge:def:110","href":"U_MS_Edge_V2R4_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV14-oval.xml"},"reference_identifier":"5280","classification":"Unclassified","potential_impacts":"","severity":"medium","responsibility":"","comments":null,"rule_version":"EDGE-00-000015","check_content":"The policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Allow importing of cookies\" must be set to \"disabled\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\nHKLM\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\n\nIf the value for \"ImportCookies\" is not set to \"REG_DWORD = 0\", this is a finding.","false_positives":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"uuid":"A51CB2BD-722B-1014-83CA-C21E67F21A8B","discussion":"Allows users to import cookies from another browser into Microsoft Edge.\n\nIf this policy is disabled, cookies are not imported on first run.\n\nIf this policy is not configured, cookies are imported on first run.","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-04-01T11:55:42\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Disable importing of cookies)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\\ImportCookies'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n"},{"security_override_guidance":"","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","third_party_tools":"","rule_title":"Importing of extensions must be disabled.","rule_id":"SV-235733r960963","weight":"10.0","stig_uuid":"A516DDF1-722B-1014-B1EE-8476FA977258","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"ia_controls":"","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000141","id":"V-235733"},"group_id":"V-235733","mitigations":"","documentable":"false","fix_text":"Set the policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Allow importing of extensions\" to \"disabled\".","rule_id_src":"SV-235733r960963_rule","status":"open","group_id_src":"V-235733","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.edge:def:111","href":"U_MS_Edge_V2R4_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV14-oval.xml"},"reference_identifier":"5280","classification":"Unclassified","potential_impacts":"","severity":"medium","responsibility":"","comments":null,"rule_version":"EDGE-00-000016","check_content":"The policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Allow importing of extensions\" must be set to \"disabled\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\nHKLM\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\n\nIf the value for \"ImportExtensions\" is not set to \"REG_DWORD = 0\", this is a finding.","false_positives":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"uuid":"A51CB807-722B-1014-86E3-A60750140118","discussion":"Allows users to import extensions from another browser into Microsoft Edge.\n\nIf this policy is enabled, the Extensions check box is automatically selected in the Import browser data dialog box.\n\nIf this policy is disabled, extensions are not imported at first run, and users cannot import them manually.","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-04-01T11:55:42\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Disable importing of extensions)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\\ImportExtensions'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n"},{"security_override_guidance":"","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","third_party_tools":"","rule_title":"Importing of browsing history must be disabled.","rule_id":"SV-235734r960963","weight":"10.0","stig_uuid":"A516DDF1-722B-1014-B1EE-8476FA977258","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"ia_controls":"","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000141","id":"V-235734"},"group_id":"V-235734","mitigations":"","documentable":"false","fix_text":"Set the policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Allow importing of browsing history\" to \"disabled\".","rule_id_src":"SV-235734r960963_rule","status":"open","group_id_src":"V-235734","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.edge:def:112","href":"U_MS_Edge_V2R4_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV14-oval.xml"},"reference_identifier":"5280","classification":"Unclassified","potential_impacts":"","severity":"medium","responsibility":"","comments":null,"rule_version":"EDGE-00-000017","check_content":"The policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Allow importing of browsing history\" must be set to \"disabled\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\nHKLM\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\n\nIf the value for \"ImportHistory\" is not set to \"REG_DWORD = 0\", this is a finding.","false_positives":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"uuid":"A51CBD72-722B-1014-B2C5-E7DAD77E8DAB","discussion":"Allows users to import their browsing history from another browser into Microsoft Edge.\n\nIf this policy is enabled, the Browsing history check box is automatically selected in the Import browser data dialog box.\n\nIf this policy is disabled, browsing history data is not imported at first run, and users cannot import this data manually.","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-04-01T11:55:42\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Disable importing of browsing history)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\\ImportHistory'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n"},{"security_override_guidance":"","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","third_party_tools":"","rule_title":"Importing of home page settings must be disabled.","rule_id":"SV-235735r960963","weight":"10.0","stig_uuid":"A516DDF1-722B-1014-B1EE-8476FA977258","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"ia_controls":"","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000141","id":"V-235735"},"group_id":"V-235735","mitigations":"","documentable":"false","fix_text":"Set the policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Allow importing of home page settings\" to \"disabled\".","rule_id_src":"SV-235735r960963_rule","status":"open","group_id_src":"V-235735","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.edge:def:113","href":"U_MS_Edge_V2R4_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV14-oval.xml"},"reference_identifier":"5280","classification":"Unclassified","potential_impacts":"","severity":"medium","responsibility":"","comments":null,"rule_version":"EDGE-00-000018","check_content":"The policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Allow importing of home page settings\" must be set to \"disabled\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\nHKLM\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\n\nIf the value for \"ImportHomepage\" is not set to \"REG_DWORD = 0\", this is a finding.","false_positives":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"uuid":"A51CC2C1-722B-1014-BD09-841FB77B7A07","discussion":"Allows users to import their home page setting from another browser into Microsoft Edge.\n\nIf this policy is enabled, the option to manually import the home page setting is automatically selected.\n\nIf this policy is disabled, the home page setting is not imported at first run, and users cannot import it manually.","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-04-01T11:55:42\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Disable importing of home page settings)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\\ImportHomepage'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n"},{"security_override_guidance":"","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","third_party_tools":"","rule_title":"Importing of open tabs must be disabled.","rule_id":"SV-235736r960963","weight":"10.0","stig_uuid":"A516DDF1-722B-1014-B1EE-8476FA977258","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"ia_controls":"","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000141","id":"V-235736"},"group_id":"V-235736","mitigations":"","documentable":"false","fix_text":"Set the policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Allow importing of open tabs\" to \"disabled\".","rule_id_src":"SV-235736r960963_rule","status":"open","group_id_src":"V-235736","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.edge:def:114","href":"U_MS_Edge_V2R4_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV14-oval.xml"},"reference_identifier":"5280","classification":"Unclassified","potential_impacts":"","severity":"medium","responsibility":"","comments":null,"rule_version":"EDGE-00-000019","check_content":"The policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Allow importing of open tabs\" must be set to \"disabled\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\nHKLM\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\n\nIf the value for \"ImportOpenTabs\" is not set to \"REG_DWORD = 0\", this is a finding.","false_positives":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"uuid":"A51CC7FE-722B-1014-AC30-F5403CB0DCD7","discussion":"Allows users to import open and pinned tabs from another browser into Microsoft Edge.\n\nIf this policy is enabled, the Open tabs check box is automatically selected in the Import browser data dialog box.\n\nIf this policy is disabled, open tabs are not imported at first run, and users cannot import them manually.\n\nIf this policy is not configured, open tabs are imported at first run, and users can choose whether to import them manually during later browsing sessions.","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-04-01T11:55:42\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Disable importing of open tabs)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\\ImportOpenTabs'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n"},{"security_override_guidance":"","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","third_party_tools":"","rule_title":"Importing of payment info must be disabled.","rule_id":"SV-235737r960963","weight":"10.0","stig_uuid":"A516DDF1-722B-1014-B1EE-8476FA977258","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"ia_controls":"","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000141","id":"V-235737"},"group_id":"V-235737","