bled.","rule_id":"SV-235738r960963","weight":"10.0","stig_uuid":"A516DDF1-722B-1014-B1EE-8476FA977258","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"ia_controls":"","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000141","id":"V-235738"},"group_id":"V-235738","mitigations":"","documentable":"false","fix_text":"Set the policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Allow importing of saved passwords\" to \"disabled\".","rule_id_src":"SV-235738r960963_rule","status":"open","group_id_src":"V-235738","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.edge:def:116","href":"U_MS_Edge_V2R4_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV14-oval.xml"},"reference_identifier":"5280","classification":"Unclassified","potential_impacts":"","severity":"medium","responsibility":"","comments":null,"rule_version":"EDGE-00-000021","check_content":"The policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Allow importing of saved passwords\" must be set to \"disabled\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\nHKLM\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\n\nIf the value for \"ImportSavedPasswords\" is not set to \"REG_DWORD = 0\", this is a finding.","false_positives":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"uuid":"A51CD297-722B-1014-90C1-CE53F936F45F","discussion":"Allows users to import saved passwords from another browser into Microsoft Edge.\n\nIf this policy is enabled, the option to manually import saved passwords is automatically selected.\n\nIf this policy is disabled, saved passwords are not imported on first run, and users cannot import them manually.","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-04-01T11:55:42\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Disable importing of saved passwords)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\\ImportSavedPasswords'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n"},{"security_override_guidance":"","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","third_party_tools":"","rule_title":"Importing of search engine settings must be disabled.","rule_id":"SV-235739r960963","weight":"10.0","stig_uuid":"A516DDF1-722B-1014-B1EE-8476FA977258","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"ia_controls":"","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000141","id":"V-235739"},"group_id":"V-235739","mitigations":"","documentable":"false","fix_text":"Set the policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Allow importing of search engine settings\" to \"disabled\".","rule_id_src":"SV-235739r960963_rule","status":"open","group_id_src":"V-235739","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.edge:def:117","href":"U_MS_Edge_V2R4_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV14-oval.xml"},"reference_identifier":"5280","classification":"Unclassified","potential_impacts":"","severity":"medium","responsibility":"","comments":null,"rule_version":"EDGE-00-000022","check_content":"The policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Allow importing of search engine settings\" must be set to \"disabled\".\n\nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\nHKLM\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\n\nIf the value for \"ImportSearchEngine\" is not set to \"REG_DWORD = 0\", this is a finding.","false_positives":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"uuid":"A51CD7B9-722B-1014-B0D9-D7B5E50201A9","discussion":"Allows users to import search engine settings from another browser into Microsoft Edge.\n\nIf this policy is enabled, the option to import search engine settings is automatically selected.\n\nIf this policy is disabled, search engine settings are not imported at first run, and users cannot import them manually.","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-04-01T11:55:42\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Disable importing of search engine settings)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\\ImportSearchEngine'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n"},{"security_override_guidance":"","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","third_party_tools":"","rule_title":"Importing of shortcuts must be disabled.","rule_id":"SV-235740r960963","weight":"10.0","stig_uuid":"A516DDF1-722B-1014-B1EE-8476FA977258","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"ia_controls":"","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000141","id":"V-235740"},"group_id":"V-235740","mitigations":"","documentable":"false","fix_text":"Set the policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Allow importing of shortcuts\" to \"disabled\".","rule_id_src":"SV-235740r960963_rule","status":"open","group_id_src":"V-235740","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.edge:def:118","href":"U_MS_Edge_V2R4_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV14-oval.xml"},"reference_identifier":"5280","classification":"Unclassified","potential_impacts":"","severity":"medium","responsibility":"","comments":null,"rule_version":"EDGE-00-000023","check_content":"The policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Allow importing of shortcuts\" must be set to \"disabled\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\nHKLM\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\n\nIf the value for \"ImportShortcuts\" is not set to \"REG_DWORD = 0\", this is a finding.","false_positives":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"uuid":"A51CE345-722B-1014-B4B9-BEC2CBFA453B","discussion":"Allows users to import Shortcuts from another browser into Microsoft Edge.\n\nIf this policy is disabled, Shortcuts are not imported on first run.\n\nIf this policy is not configured, Shortcuts are imported on first run.","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-04-01T11:55:42\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Disable importing of shortcuts)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\\ImportShortcuts'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n"},{"security_override_guidance":"","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","third_party_tools":"","rule_title":"AutoplayAllowed must be set to disabled.","rule_id":"SV-235741r1007485","weight":"10.0","stig_uuid":"A516DDF1-722B-1014-B1EE-8476FA977258","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"ia_controls":"","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000141","id":"V-235741"},"group_id":"V-235741","mitigations":"","documentable":"false","fix_text":"Set the policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Allow media autoplay for websites\" to \"disabled\".","rule_id_src":"SV-235741r1007485_rule","status":"open","group_id_src":"V-235741","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.edge:def:119","href":"U_MS_Edge_V2R4_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV14-oval.xml"},"reference_identifier":"5280","classification":"Unclassified","potential_impacts":"","severity":"medium","responsibility":"","comments":null,"rule_version":"EDGE-00-000024","check_content":"The policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Allow media autoplay for websites\" must be set to \"disabled\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\nHKLM\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\n\nIf the value for \"AutoplayAllowed\" is not set to \"REG_DWORD = 0\", this is a finding.","false_positives":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"uuid":"A51CEF58-722B-1014-A090-883D9C4E0E43","discussion":"This policy sets the media autoplay policy for websites.\n\nThe default setting \"Not configured\" respects the current media autoplay settings and lets users configure their autoplay settings.\n\nSetting to \"Enabled\" sets media autoplay to \"Allow\". All websites are allowed to autoplay media. Users cannot override this policy.\n\nSetting to \"Disabled\" sets media autoplay to \"Limit\". This limits websites that are allowed to autoplay media to webpages with high media engagement and active WebRTC streams. Prior to Microsoft Edge version 92, this would set media autoplay to \"Block\". Users cannot override this policy.","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-04-01T11:55:42\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Disable autoplay)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\\AutoplayAllowed'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n"},{"security_override_guidance":"","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","third_party_tools":"","rule_title":"WebUSB must be disabled.","rule_id":"SV-235742r960963","weight":"10.0","stig_uuid":"A516DDF1-722B-1014-B1EE-8476FA977258","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"ia_controls":"","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000141","id":"V-235742"},"group_id":"V-235742","mitigations":"","documentable":"false","fix_text":"Set the policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Content settings/Control use of the WebUSB API\" to enabled\" and select \"Do not allow any site to request access to USB devices via the WebUSB API\".","rule_id_src":"SV-235742r960963_rule","status":"open","group_id_src":"V-235742","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.edge:def:120","href":"U_MS_Edge_V2R4_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV14-oval.xml"},"reference_identifier":"5280","classification":"Unclassified","potential_impacts":"","severity":"medium","responsibility":"","comments":null,"rule_version":"EDGE-00-000025","check_content":"The policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Content settings/Control use of the WebUSB API\" must be set to \"enabled\" with the option value set to \"Do not allow any site to request access to USB devices via the WebUSB API\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\nHKLM\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\n\nIf the value for \"DefaultWebUsbGuardSetting\" is not set to \"REG_DWORD = 2\", this is a finding.","false_positives":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"uuid":"A51CFAC0-722B-1014-8AD4-CC06EB2256DC","discussion":"Set whether websites can access connected USB devices. Access can be blocked completely or the user asked each time a website wants to get access to connected USB devices.\n\nOverride this policy for specific URL patterns by using the WebUsbAskForUrls and WebUsbBlockedForUrls policies.\n\nIf this policy is not configured, sites can ask users whether they can access the connected USB devices ('AskWebUsb') by default, and users can change this setting.","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-04-01T11:55:42\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (WebUSB must be disabled)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\\DefaultWebUsbGuardSetting'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n"},{"security_override_guidance":"","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","third_party_tools":"","rule_title":"Google Cast must be disabled.","rule_id":"SV-235743r960963","weight":"10.0","stig_uuid":"A516DDF1-722B-1014-B1EE-8476FA977258","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"ia_controls":"","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000141","id":"V-235743"},"group_id":"V-235743","mitigations":"","documentable":"false","fix_text":"Set the policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Cast/Enable Google Cast\" to \"disabled\".","rule_id_src":"SV-235743r960963_rule","status":"open","group_id_src":"V-235743","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.edge:def:121","href":"U_MS_Edge_V2R4_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV14-oval.xml"},"reference_identifier":"5280","classification":"Unclassified","potential_impacts":"","severity":"medium","responsibility":"","comments":null,"rule_version":"EDGE-00-000026","check_content":"The policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Cast/Enable Google Cast\" must be set to \"disabled\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\nHKLM\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\n\nIf the value for \"EnableMediaRouter\" is not set to \"REG_DWORD = 0\", this is a finding.","false_positives":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"uuid":"A51D04CD-722B-1014-861A-C543E3355178","discussion":"Enable this policy to enable Google Cast. Users will be able to launch it from the app menu, page context menus, media controls on Cast-enabled websites, and (if shown) the Cast toolbar icon.\n\nDisable this policy to disable Google Cast.\n\nBy default, Google Cast is enabled.","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-04-01T11:55:42\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Google Cast is disabled)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\\EnableMediaRouter'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n"},{"security_override_guidance":"","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","third_party_tools":"","rule_title":"Web Bluetooth API must be disabled.","rule_id":"SV-235744r960963","weight":"10.0","stig_uuid":"A516DDF1-722B-1014-B1EE-8476FA977258","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"ia_controls":"","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000141","id":"V-235744"},"group_id":"V-235744","mitigations":"","documentable":"false","fix_text":"Set the policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Content settings/Control use of the Web Bluetooth API\" to \"enabled\" with the option value set to \"Do not allow any site to request access to Bluetooth devices via the Web Bluetooth API.","rule_id_src":"SV-235744r960963_rule","status":"open","group_id_src":"V-235744","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.edge:def:122","href":"U_MS_Edge_V2R4_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV14-oval.xml"},"reference_identifier":"5280","classification":"Unclassified","potential_impacts":"","severity":"medium","responsibility":"","comments":null,"rule_version":"EDGE-00-000027","check_content":"The policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Content settings/Control use of the Web Bluetooth API\" must be set to \"enabled\" with the option value set to \"Do not allow any site to request access to Bluetooth devices via the Web Bluetooth API\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\nHKLM\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\n\nIf the value for \"DefaultWebBluetoothGuardSetting\" is not set to \"REG_DWORD = 2\", this is a finding.","false_positives":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"uuid":"A51D0F24-722B-1014-9BC5-9EF227E1CFB4","discussion":"Control whether websites can access nearby Bluetooth devices. Access can be blocked completely or the site required to ask the user each time it wants to access a Bluetooth device.\n\nIf this policy is not configured, the default value ('AskWebBluetooth', meaning users are asked each time) is used and users can change it.\n\nPolicy options mapping:\n- BlockWebBluetooth (2) = Do not allow any site to request access to Bluetooth devices via the Web Bluetooth API.\n- AskWebBluetooth (3) = Allow sites to ask the user to grant access to a nearby Bluetooth device.","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-04-01T11:55:42\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Web Bluetooth API is disabled)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\\DefaultWebBluetoothGuardSetting'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n"},{"security_override_guidance":"","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","third_party_tools":"","rule_title":"Autofill for Credit Cards must be disabled.","rule_id":"SV-235745r960963","weight":"10.0","stig_uuid":"A516DDF1-722B-1014-B1EE-8476FA977258","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"ia_controls":"","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000141","id":"V-235745"},"group_id":"V-235745","mitigations":"","documentable":"false","fix_text":"Set the policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Enable AutoFill for credit cards\" to \"disabled\".","rule_id_src":"SV-235745r960963_rule","status":"open","group_id_src":"V-235745","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.edge:def:123","href":"U_MS_Edge_V2R4_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV14-oval.xml"},"reference_identifier":"5280","classification":"Unclassified","potential_impacts":"","severity":"medium","responsibility":"","comments":null,"rule_version":"EDGE-00-000028","check_content":"The policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Enable AutoFill for credit cards\" must be set to \"disabled\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\nHKLM\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\n\nIf the value for \"AutofillCreditCardEnabled\" is not set to \"REG_DWORD = 0\", this is a finding.","false_positives":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"uuid":"A51D1997-722B-1014-A343-8F43A9DB438F","discussion":"Enables the Microsoft Edge AutoFill feature and lets users auto complete credit card information in web forms using previously stored information.\n\nIf this policy is disabled, AutoFill never suggests or fills credit card information, nor will it save additional credit card information that users might submit while browsing the web.\n\nIf this policy is enabled or not configured, users can control AutoFill for credit cards.","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-04-01T11:55:42\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Disable autofill for credit cards)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\\AutofillCreditCardEnabled'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n"},{"security_override_guidance":"","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","third_party_tools":"","rule_title":"Autofill for addresses must be disabled.","rule_id":"SV-235746r960963","weight":"10.0","stig_uuid":"A516DDF1-722B-1014-B1EE-8476FA977258","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"ia_controls":"","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000141","id":"V-235746"},"group_id":"V-235746","mitigations":"","documentable":"false","fix_text":"Set the policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Enable AutoFill for addresses\" to \"disabled\".","rule_id_src":"SV-235746r960963_rule","status":"open","group_id_src":"V-235746","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.edge:def:124","href":"U_MS_Edge_V2R4_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV14-oval.xml"},"reference_identifier":"5280","classification":"Unclassified","potential_impacts":"","severity":"medium","responsibility":"","comments":null,"rule_version":"EDGE-00-000029","check_content":"The policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Enable AutoFill for addresses\" must be set to \"disabled\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\nHKLM\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\n\nIf the value for \"AutofillAddressEnabled\" is not set to \"REG_DWORD = 0\", this is a finding.","false_positives":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"uuid":"A51D2777-722B-1014-967C-DE5DA911582F","discussion":"Enables the AutoFill feature and allows users to auto-complete address information in web forms using previously stored information.\n\nIf this policy is disabled, AutoFill never suggests or fills credit card information, nor will it save additional credit card information that users might submit while browsing the web.\n\nIf this policy is enabled or not configured, users can control AutoFill for addresses in the user interface.","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-04-01T11:55:42\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Disable autofill for addresses)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\\AutofillAddressEnabled'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n"},{"security_override_guidance":"","group_title":"SRG-APP-000175","third_party_tools":"","rule_title":"Online revocation checks must be performed.","rule_id":"SV-235747r961038","weight":"10.0","stig_uuid":"A516DDF1-722B-1014-B1EE-8476FA977258","ccis":["CCI-000185"],"ia_controls":"","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000175","id":"V-235747"},"group_id":"V-235747","mitigations":"","documentable":"false","fix_text":"Set the policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Enable online OCSP/CRL checks\" to \"Enabled\".","rule_id_src":"SV-235747r961038_rule","status":"open","group_id_src":"V-235747","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.edge:def:125","href":"U_MS_Edge_V2R4_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV14-oval.xml"},"reference_identifier":"5280","classification":"Unclassified","potential_impacts":"","severity":"medium","responsibility":"","comments":null,"rule_version":"EDGE-00-000030","check_content":"The policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Enable online OCSP/CRL checks\" must be set to \"Enabled\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\nHKLM\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\n\nIf the value for \"EnableOnlineRevocationChecks\" is not set to \"REG_DWORD = 1\", this is a finding.","false_positives":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"uuid":"A51D32AA-722B-1014-B627-C389B1633C99","discussion":"If you enable this policy, Microsoft Edge will perform soft-fail, online OCSP/CRL checks. \"Soft fail\" means that if the revocation server can't be reached, the certificate will be considered valid.\n\nIf you disable the policy or don't configure it, Microsoft Edge won't perform online revocation checks.","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-04-01T11:55:42\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Enable Enable online OCSP/CRL checks)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\\EnableOnlineRevocationChecks'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n"},{"security_override_guidance":"","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","third_party_tools":"","rule_title":"Personalization of ads, search, and news by sending browsing history to Microsoft must be disabled.","rule_id":"SV-235748r960963","weight":"10.0","stig_uuid":"A516DDF1-722B-1014-B1EE-8476FA977258","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"ia_controls":"","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000141","id":"V-235748"},"group_id":"V-235748","mitigations":"","documentable":"false","fix_text":"Set the policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Allow personalization of ads, search and news by sending browsing history to Microsoft\" to \"disabled\".","rule_id_src":"SV-235748r960963_rule","status":"open","group_id_src":"V-235748","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.edge:def:126","href":"U_MS_Edge_V2R4_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV14-oval.xml"},"reference_identifier":"5280","classification":"Unclassified","potential_impacts":"","severity":"medium","responsibility":"","comments":null,"rule_version":"EDGE-00-000031","check_content":"The policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Allow personalization of ads, search and news by sending browsing history to Microsoft\" must be set to \"disabled\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\nHKLM\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\n\nIf the value for \"PersonalizationReportingEnabled\" is not set to \"REG_DWORD = 0\", this is a finding.","false_positives":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"uuid":"A51D41FC-722B-1014-A7D1-CD7FE2535609","discussion":"This policy prevents Microsoft from collecting a user's Microsoft Edge browsing history to be used for personalizing advertising, search, news and other Microsoft services.\n\nThis setting is only available for users with a Microsoft account. This setting is not available for child accounts or enterprise accounts.\n\nIf this policy is disabled, users cannot change or override the setting. If this policy is enabled or not configured, Microsoft Edge will default to the user's preference.","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-04-01T11:55:42\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Disable personalization reporting)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\\PersonalizationReportingEnabled'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n"},{"security_override_guidance":"","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","third_party_tools":"","rule_title":"Site tracking of a userâs location must be disabled.","rule_id":"SV-235749r960963","weight":"10.0","stig_uuid":"A516DDF1-722B-1014-B1EE-8476FA977258","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"ia_controls":"","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000141","id":"V-235749"},"group_id":"V-235749","mitigations":"","documentable":"false","fix_text":"Set the policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Content settings/Default geolocation setting\" to \"enabled\" and select \"Don't allow any site to track users' physical location\".","rule_id_src":"SV-235749r960963_rule","status":"open","group_id_src":"V-235749","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.edge:def:127","href":"U_MS_Edge_V2R4_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV14-oval.xml"},"reference_identifier":"5280","classification":"Unclassified","potential_impacts":"","severity":"medium","responsibility":"","comments":null,"rule_version":"EDGE-00-000032","check_content":"The policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Content settings/Default geolocation setting\" must be set to \"enabled\" with the option value set to \"Don't allow any site to track users' physical location\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\nHKLM\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\n\nIf the value for \"DefaultGeolocationSetting\" is not set to \"REG_DWORD = 2\", this is a finding.","false_positives":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"uuid":"A51D4E5C-722B-1014-AAC4-DC49B65730EA","discussion":"Set whether websites can track users' physical locations. Tracking can be allowed by default (\"AllowGeolocation\") or denied by default (\"BlockGeolocation\"), or the user can be asked each time a website requests their location (\"AskGeolocation\").\n\nIf this policy is not configured, \"AskGeolocation\" is used and the user can change it.\n\nPolicy options mapping:\n- AllowGeolocation (1) = Allow sites to track users' physical location.\n- BlockGeolocation (2) = Do not allow any site to track users' physical location.\n- AskGeolocation (3) = Ask whenever a site wants to track users' physical location.","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-04-01T11:55:42\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Disable tracking user's location)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\\DefaultGeolocationSetting'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n"},{"security_override_guidance":"","group_title":"SRG-APP-000080","third_party_tools":"","rule_title":"Browser history must be saved.","rule_id":"SV-235750r960864","weight":"10.0","stig_uuid":"A516DDF1-722B-1014-B1EE-8476FA977258","ccis":["CCI-000166"],"ia_controls":"","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000080","id":"V-235750"},"group_id":"V-235750","mitigations":"","documentable":"false","fix_text":"Set the policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Enable deleting browser and download history\" to \"disabled\".","rule_id_src":"SV-235750r960864_rule","status":"open","group_id_src":"V-235750","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.edge:def:128","href":"U_MS_Edge_V2R4_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV14-oval.xml"},"reference_identifier":"5280","classification":"Unclassified","potential_impacts":"","severity":"medium","responsibility":"","comments":null,"rule_version":"EDGE-00-000033","check_content":"The policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Enable deleting browser and download history\" must be set to \"disabled\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\nHKLM\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\n\nIf the value for \"AllowDeletingBrowserHistory\" is not set to \"REG_DWORD = 0\", this is a finding.","false_positives":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"uuid":"A51D5A25-722B-1014-BC45-CDC4BDEFCCDB","discussion":"This setting disables deleting browser history and download history and prevents users from changing this setting.","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-04-01T11:55:42\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Check to make sure that Microsoft Edge is set to not allow deletion of browser history.)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\\AllowDeletingBrowserHistory'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n"},{"security_override_guidance":"","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","third_party_tools":"","rule_title":"Edge development tools must be disabled.","rule_id":"SV-235751r960963","weight":"10.0","stig_uuid":"A516DDF1-722B-1014-B1EE-8476FA977258","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"ia_controls":"","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000141","id":"V-235751"},"group_id":"V-235751","mitigations":"","documentable":"false","fix_text":"Set the policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Control where developer tools can be used\" to \"enabled\" and select \"Don't allow using the developer tools\".","rule_id_src":"SV-235751r960963_rule","status":"open","group_id_src":"V-235751","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.edge:def:129","href":"U_MS_Edge_V2R4_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV14-oval.xml"},"reference_identifier":"5280","classification":"Unclassified","potential_impacts":"","severity":"low","responsibility":"","comments":null,"rule_version":"EDGE-00-000034","check_content":"The policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Control where developer tools can be used\" with the option value set to \"Don't allow using the developer tools\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\nHKLM\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\n\nIf the value for \"DeveloperToolsAvailability\" is not set to \"REG_DWORD = 2\", this is a finding.","false_positives":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"uuid":"A51D64C4-722B-1014-922A-B7ED9E4A70E1","discussion":"While the risk associated with browser development tools is more related to the proper design of a web application, a risk vector remains within the browser. The developer tools allow end users and application developers to view and edit all types of web application-related data via the browser. Page elements, source code, javascript, API calls, application data, etc., may all be viewed and potentially manipulated. Manipulation could be useful for troubleshooting legitimate issues, and this may be performed in a development environment. Manipulation could also be malicious and must be addressed.","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-04-01T11:55:42\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Edge Developer Tools Availability must be disallowed.)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\\DeveloperToolsAvailability'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n"},{"security_override_guidance":"","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","third_party_tools":"","rule_title":"Download restrictions must be configured.","rule_id":"SV-235752r1156563","weight":"10.0","stig_uuid":"A516DDF1-722B-1014-B1EE-8476FA977258","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"ia_controls":"","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000141","id":"V-235752"},"group_id":"V-235752","mitigations":"","documentable":"false","fix_text":"Set the policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Allow download restrictions\" to \"Enabled\" and select one of the following: \"BlockDangerousDownloads\", \"Block potentially dangerous or unwanted downloads\", \"BlockAllDownloads\", or \"BlockMaliciousDownloads\".","rule_id_src":"SV-235752r1156563_rule","status":"open","group_id_src":"V-235752","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.edge:def:130","href":"U_MS_Edge_V2R4_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV14-oval.xml"},"reference_identifier":"5280","classification":"Unclassified","potential_impacts":"","severity":"low","responsibility":"","comments":null,"rule_version":"EDGE-00-000036","check_content":"If this machine is on SIPRNet, this is Not Applicable.\n\nThe policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Allow download restrictions\" must be set to \"Enabled\" with the option value set to \"BlockDangerousDownloads\", \"Block potentially dangerous or unwanted downloads\", or \"BlockMaliciousDownloads\". The more restrictive option, \"Block all downloads\", is also acceptable.\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\nHKLM\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\n\nIf the value for \"DownloadRestrictions\" is set to \"REG_DWORD = 0\", this is a finding.","false_positives":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"uuid":"A51D6F85-722B-1014-A4EF-C1E749C20E3F","discussion":"This configures the type of downloads that Microsoft Edge completely blocks without allowing users to override the security decision.\n\nSet \"BlockDangerousDownloads\" to allow all downloads except those that carry Microsoft Defender SmartScreen warnings of known dangerous downloads or that have dangerous file type extensions.\n\nSet \"BlockPotentiallyDangerousDownloads\" to allow all downloads except those that carry Microsoft Defender SmartScreen warnings of potentially dangerous or unwanted downloads or that have dangerous file type extensions.\n\nSet \"BlockAllDownloads\" to block all downloads.\n\nSet \"BlockMaliciousDownloads\" to allow all downloads except those that carry Microsoft Defender SmartScreen warnings of known malicious downloads.\n\nIf this policy is not configured or the \"DefaultDownloadSecurity\" option is not set, the downloads go through the usual security restrictions based on Microsoft Defender SmartScreen analysis results.\n\nPolicy options mapping:\n\nDefaultDownloadSecurity (0) = No special restrictions\n\nBlockDangerousDownloads (1) = Block malicious downloads and dangerous file types\n\nBlockPotentiallyDangerousDownloads (2) = Block potentially dangerous or unwanted downloads and dangerous file types\n\nBlockAllDownloads (3) = Block all downloads\n\nBlockMaliciousDownloads (4) = Block malicious downloads","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-04-01T11:55:42\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Download restrictions are configured)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\\DownloadRestrictions'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n"},{"security_override_guidance":"","group_title":"SRG-APP-000378","third_party_tools":"","rule_title":"URLs must be allowlisted for plugin use if used.","rule_id":"SV-235753r1015297","weight":"10.0","stig_uuid":"A516DDF1-722B-1014-B1EE-8476FA977258","ccis":["CCI-003980","CCI-001812"],"ia_controls":"","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000378","id":"V-235753"},"group_id":"V-235753","mitigations":"","documentable":"false","fix_text":"Set the policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Content settings/Allow pop-up windows on specific sites\" to \"Enabled\". A list of allowlisted URLs may be specified here.","rule_id_src":"SV-235753r1015297_rule","status":"not_reviewed","group_id_src":"V-235753","check_content_ref":{"name":"ocil:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.edge:questionnaire:6901","href":"U_MS_Edge_V2R4_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV14-ocil.xml"},"reference_identifier":"5280","classification":"Unclassified","potential_impacts":"","severity":"low","responsibility":"","comments":null,"rule_version":"EDGE-00-000039","check_content":"This requirement for \"Allow pop-up windows on specific sites\" is not required; this is optional.\n\nThe policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Content settings/Allow pop-up windows on specific sites\" must be set to \"Enabled\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\nHKLM\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\n\n\"PopupsAllowedForUrls\" must be set as follows:\nHKLM\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\\PopupsAllowedForUrls\\1 = mydomain.com\nHKLM\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\\PopupsAllowedForUrls\\2 = myagency.mil\n\nIf configured, the list of domains for which Microsoft Edge allows pop-ups may be allowlisted.","false_positives":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"uuid":"A51D7BCB-722B-1014-9433-AD4BBAA672E6","discussion":"Define a list of sites, based on URL patterns that can open pop-up windows.","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-04-01T11:55:42\nResult: notcheckedCriteria        : NOT_TESTED (All child tests must be true.)\nTest            :   NOT_TESTED (CAT III, V-235753, SV-235753r1015297, SRG-APP-000378)\n"},{"security_override_guidance":"","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","third_party_tools":"","rule_title":"Extensions installation must be blocklisted by default.","rule_id":"SV-235754r960963","weight":"10.0","stig_uuid":"A516DDF1-722B-1014-B1EE-8476FA977258","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"ia_controls":"","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000141","id":"V-235754"},"group_id":"V-235754","mitigations":"","documentable":"false","fix_text":"Set the policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Extensions/Control which extensions cannot be installed\" to \"Enabled\". A list of blocklisted extensions may then be specified.","rule_id_src":"SV-235754r960963_rule","status":"open","group_id_src":"V-235754","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.edge:def:131","href":"U_MS_Edge_V2R4_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV14-oval.xml"},"reference_identifier":"5280","classification":"Unclassified","potential_impacts":"","severity":"medium","responsibility":"","comments":null,"rule_version":"EDGE-00-000041","check_content":"The policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Extensions/Control which extensions cannot be installed\" must be set to \"Enabled\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\nHKLM\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\\ExtensionInstallBlocklist\\1\n\nIf the value for \"1\" is not set to \"REG_SZ = *\", this is a finding.","false_positives":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"uuid":"A51D8B42-722B-1014-A0DF-B0C5AA472655","discussion":"List specific extensions that users cannot install in Microsoft Edge. When this policy is deployed, any extensions on this list that were previously installed will be disabled, and the user will not be able to enable them. If an item is removed from the list of blocked extensions, the extension is automatically reenabled anywhere it was previously installed.\n\nUse \"*\" to block all extensions that are not explicitly listed in the allow list.\n\nIf this policy is not configured, users can install any extension in Microsoft Edge.","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-04-01T11:55:42\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Enable the setting 'Control which extensions cannot be installed')\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\\ExtensionInstallBlocklist\\1'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n"},{"security_override_guidance":"","group_title":"SRG-APP-000386","third_party_tools":"","rule_title":"Extensions that are approved for use must be allowlisted if used.","rule_id":"SV-235755r961479","weight":"10.0","stig_uuid":"A516DDF1-722B-1014-B1EE-8476FA977258","ccis":["CCI-001774"],"ia_controls":"","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000386","id":"V-235755"},"group_id":"V-235755","mitigations":"","documentable":"false","fix_text":"Set the policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Extensions/Allow specific extensions to be installed\" to \"Enabled\".  A list of allowlisted extensions may then be specified.","rule_id_src":"SV-235755r961479_rule","status":"not_reviewed","group_id_src":"V-235755","check_content_ref":{"name":"ocil:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.edge:questionnaire:7301","href":"U_MS_Edge_V2R4_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV14-ocil.xml"},"reference_identifier":"5280","classification":"Unclassified","potential_impacts":"","severity":"low","responsibility":"","comments":null,"rule_version":"EDGE-00-000042","check_content":"This requirement for \"Allow specific extensions to be installed\" is not required; this is optional.\n\nThe policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Extensions/Allow specific extensions to be installed\" must be set to \"Enabled\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\nHKLM\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\n\n\"ExtensionInstallAllowlist\" must be set as follows:\nHKLM\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\\ExtensionInstallAllowlist\\1 = \"extension_id1\"\nHKLM\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\\ExtensionInstallAllowlist\\2 = \"extension_id2\"\n\nIf configured, the list of extensions for which Microsoft Edge allows to be installed may be allowlisted.","false_positives":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"uuid":"A51D972C-722B-1014-B7E2-B8C8E2E72C80","discussion":"By default, all extensions are allowed. However, if all extensions are blocked by setting the \"ExtensionInstallBlockList\" policy to \"*,\" users can only install extensions defined in this policy.","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-04-01T11:55:42\nResult: notcheckedCriteria        : NOT_TESTED (All child tests must be true.)\nTest            :   NOT_TESTED (CAT III, V-235755, SV-235755r961479, SRG-APP-000386)\n"},{"security_override_guidance":"","group_title":"SRG-APP-000400","third_party_tools":"","rule_title":"The Password Manager must be disabled.","rule_id":"SV-235756r961521","weight":"10.0","stig_uuid":"A516DDF1-722B-1014-B1EE-8476FA977258","ccis":["CCI-002007"],"ia_controls":"","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000400","id":"V-235756"},"group_id":"V-235756","mitigations":"","documentable":"false","fix_text":"Set the policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Password manager and protection/Enable saving passwords to the password manager\" to \"disabled\".","rule_id_src":"SV-235756r961521_rule","status":"not_a_finding","group_id_src":"V-235756","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.edge:def:132","href":"U_MS_Edge_V2R4_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV14-oval.xml"},"reference_identifier":"5280","classification":"Unclassified","potential_impacts":"","severity":"medium","responsibility":"","comments":null,"rule_version":"EDGE-00-000043","check_content":"The policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Password manager and protection/Enable saving passwords to the password manager\" must be set to \"disabled\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\nHKLM\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\n\nIf the value for \"PasswordManagerEnabled\" is not set to \"REG_DWORD = 0\", this is a finding.","false_positives":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"uuid":"A51DA1A3-722B-1014-9673-99EBED115501","discussion":"Enable Microsoft Edge to save user passwords.\n\nIf this policy is enabled, users can save their passwords in Microsoft Edge. The next time the user visits the site, Microsoft Edge will enter the password automatically.","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-04-01T11:55:42\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Disable Microsoft Edge Password Manager)\n"},{"security_override_guidance":"","group_title":"SRG-APP-000456","third_party_tools":"","rule_title":"The version of Microsoft Edge running on the system must be a supported version.","rule_id":"SV-235758r1117151","weight":"10.0","stig_uuid":"A516DDF1-722B-1014-B1EE-8476FA977258","ccis":["CCI-002605"],"ia_controls":"","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000456","id":"V-235758"},"group_id":"V-235758","mitigations":"","documentable":"false","fix_text":"Install a supported version of Edge.","rule_id_src":"SV-235758r1117151_rule","status":"not_reviewed","group_id_src":"V-235758","check_content_ref":{"name":"ocil:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.edge:questionnaire:7701","href":"U_MS_Edge_V2R4_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV14-ocil.xml"},"reference_identifier":"5280","classification":"Unclassified","potential_impacts":"","severity":"high","responsibility":"","comments":null,"rule_version":"EDGE-00-000045","check_content":"Cross-reference the build information displayed with the Microsoft Edge site to identify, at minimum, the oldest supported build available. \n\nIf the installed version of Edge is not supported by Microsoft, this is a finding.","false_positives":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"uuid":"A51DAB96-722B-1014-BFDE-C0B0F18602DF","discussion":"Security flaws with software applications are discovered daily. Vendors are constantly updating and patching their products to address newly discovered security vulnerabilities. Organizations (including any contractor to the organization) are required to promptly install security-relevant software updates (e.g., patches, service packs, and hot fixes). Flaws discovered during security assessments, continuous monitoring, incident response activities, or information system error handling must also be addressed expeditiously. \n\nOrganization-defined time periods for updating security-relevant software may vary based on a variety of factors including, for example, the security category of the information system or the criticality of the update (i.e., severity of the vulnerability related to the discovered flaw). \n\nThis requirement will apply to software patch management solutions that are used to install patches across the enclave and also to applications themselves that are not part of that patch management solution. For example, many browsers today provide the capability to install their own patch software. Patch criticality, as well as system criticality will vary. Therefore, the tactical situations regarding the patch management process will also vary. This means that the time period used must be a configurable parameter. Time frames for application of security-relevant software updates may be dependent upon the Information Assurance Vulnerability Management (IAVM) process.\n\nThe application will be configured to check for and install security-relevant software updates within an identified time period from the availability of the update. The specific time period will be defined by an authoritative source (e.g., IAVM, CTOs, DTMs, and STIGs).","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-04-01T11:55:42\nResult: notcheckedCriteria        : NOT_TESTED (All child tests must be true.)\nTest            :   NOT_TESTED (CAT I, V-235758, SV-235758r1117151, SRG-APP-000456)\n"},{"security_override_guidance":"","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","third_party_tools":"","rule_title":"Site isolation for every site must be enabled.","rule_id":"SV-235760r960963","weight":"10.0","stig_uuid":"A516DDF1-722B-1014-B1EE-8476FA977258","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"ia_controls":"","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000141","id":"V-235760"},"group_id":"V-235760","mitigations":"","documentable":"false","fix_text":"Set the policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Enable site isolation for every site\" to \"enabled\".","rule_id_src":"SV-235760r960963_rule","status":"open","group_id_src":"V-235760","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.edge:def:135","href":"U_MS_Edge_V2R4_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV14-oval.xml"},"reference_identifier":"5280","classification":"Unclassified","potential_impacts":"","severity":"medium","responsibility":"","comments":null,"rule_version":"EDGE-00-000047","check_content":"The policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Enable site isolation for every site\" must be set to \"enabled\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\nHKLM\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\n\nIf the value for \"SitePerProcess\" is not set to \"REG_DWORD = 1\", this is a finding.","false_positives":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"uuid":"A51DB4EC-722B-1014-A473-AA2CA197CF7B","discussion":"The \"SitePerProcess\" policy can be used to prevent users from opting out of the default behavior of isolating all sites. The \"IsolateOrigins\" policy can be used to isolate additional, finer-grained origins.\n\nEnabling this policy prevents users from opting out of the default behavior where each site runs in its own process.\n\nIf this policy is not disabled or configured, a user can opt out of site isolation (e.g., by using \"Disable site isolation\" entry in edge://flags.) Disabling the policy or not configuring the policy does not turn off Site Isolation.","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-04-01T11:55:42\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Enable the setting 'Enable site isolation for every site')\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\\SitePerProcess'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n"},{"security_override_guidance":"","group_title":"SRG-APP-000142","third_party_tools":"","rule_title":"Supported authentication schemes must be configured.","rule_id":"SV-235761r1043177","weight":"10.0","stig_uuid":"A516DDF1-722B-1014-B1EE-8476FA977258","ccis":["CCI-000382"],"ia_controls":"","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000142","id":"V-235761"},"group_id":"V-235761","mitigations":"","documentable":"false","fix_text":"Set the policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/HTTP authentication/Supported authentication schemes\" to \"ntlm,negotiate\".","rule_id_src":"SV-235761r1043177_rule","status":"open","group_id_src":"V-235761","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.edge:def:136","href":"U_MS_Edge_V2R4_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV14-oval.xml"},"reference_identifier":"5280","classification":"Unclassified","potential_impacts":"","severity":"medium","responsibility":"","comments":null,"rule_version":"EDGE-00-000048","check_content":"The policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/HTTP authentication/Supported authentication schemes\" must be set to  \"ntlm,negotiate\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\nHKLM\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\n\nIf the value for \"AuthSchemes\" is not set to \"REG_SZ = ntlm,negotiate\", this is a finding.","false_positives":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"uuid":"A51DBE21-722B-1014-83A4-FC2CFDB2A32B","discussion":"This setting specifies which HTTP authentication schemes are supported.\n\nThe policy can be configured by using these values: \"basic\", \"digest\", \"ntlm\", and \"negotiate\". Separate multiple values with commas.\n\nIf this policy is not configured, all four schemes are used.","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-04-01T11:55:42\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Enable the setting 'Supported authentication schemes')\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\\AuthSchemes'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n"},{"security_override_guidance":"","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","third_party_tools":"","rule_title":"Microsoft Defender SmartScreen must be enabled.","rule_id":"SV-235763r960963","weight":"10.0","stig_uuid":"A516DDF1-722B-1014-B1EE-8476FA977258","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"ia_controls":"","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000141","id":"V-235763"},"group_id":"V-235763","mitigations":"","documentable":"false","fix_text":"Set the policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/SmartScreen settings/Configure Microsoft Defender SmartScreen\" to \"Enabled\".","rule_id_src":"SV-235763r960963_rule","status":"not_a_finding","group_id_src":"V-235763","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.edge:def:138","href":"U_MS_Edge_V2R4_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV14-oval.xml"},"reference_identifier":"5280","classification":"Unclassified","potential_impacts":"","severity":"medium","responsibility":"","comments":null,"rule_version":"EDGE-00-000050","check_content":"The policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/SmartScreen settings/Configure Microsoft Defender SmartScreen\" must be set to \"Enabled\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\nHKLM\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\n\nIf the value for \"SmartScreenEnabled\" is not set to \"REG_DWORD = 1\", this is a finding.\n\nIf this machine is on SIPRNet, this is Not Applicable.","false_positives":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"uuid":"A51DC85C-722B-1014-B0F0-C908F391725C","discussion":"This policy setting configures Microsoft Defender SmartScreen, which provides warning messages to help protect  users from potential phishing scams and malicious software. By default, Microsoft Defender SmartScreen is turned on.\n\nIf this setting is enabled, Microsoft Defender SmartScreen is turned on.\n\nIf this setting is disabled, Microsoft Defender SmartScreen is turned off.\n\nIf this setting is not configured, users can choose whether to use Microsoft Defender SmartScreen.\n\nThis policy is available only on Windows instances that are joined to a Microsoft Active Directory domain, Windows 10 Pro or Enterprise instances that enrolled for device management, or macOS instances that are that are managed via MDM or joined to a domain via MCX.","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-04-01T11:55:42\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Microsoft Defender SmartScreen must be enabled.)\n"},{"security_override_guidance":"","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","third_party_tools":"","rule_title":"Microsoft Defender SmartScreen must be configured to block potentially unwanted apps.","rule_id":"SV-235764r960963","weight":"10.0","stig_uuid":"A516DDF1-722B-1014-B1EE-8476FA977258","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"ia_controls":"","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000141","id":"V-235764"},"group_id":"V-235764","mitigations":"","documentable":"false","fix_text":"Set the policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/SmartScreen settings/Configure Microsoft Defender SmartScreen to block potentially unwanted apps\" to \"Enabled\".","rule_id_src":"SV-235764r960963_rule","status":"open","group_id_src":"V-235764","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.edge:def:139","href":"U_MS_Edge_V2R4_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV14-oval.xml"},"reference_identifier":"5280","classification":"Unclassified","potential_impacts":"","severity":"medium","responsibility":"","comments":null,"rule_version":"EDGE-00-000051","check_content":"The policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/SmartScreen settings/Configure Microsoft Defender SmartScreen to block potentially unwanted apps\" must be set to \"Enabled\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\nHKLM\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\n\nIf the value for SmartScreenPuaEnabled is not set to \"REG_DWORD = 1\", this is a finding.\n\nIf this machine is on SIPRNet, this is Not Applicable.","false_positives":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"uuid":"A51DD468-722B-1014-B363-D847C1F7E4E0","discussion":"This policy setting configures blocking for potentially unwanted apps with Microsoft Defender SmartScreen. Potentially unwanted app blocking with Microsoft Defender SmartScreen provides warning messages to help protect users from adware, coin miners, bundleware, and other low-reputation apps that are hosted by websites. Potentially unwanted app blocking with Microsoft Defender SmartScreen is turned off by default.\n\nIf this setting is enabled, potentially unwanted app blocking with Microsoft Defender SmartScreen is turned on.\n\nIf this setting is disabled, potentially unwanted app blocking with Microsoft Defender SmartScreen is turned off.\n\nIf this setting is not configured, users can choose whether to use potentially unwanted app blocking with Microsoft Defender SmartScreen.\n\nThis policy is available only on Windows instances that are joined to a Microsoft Active Directory domain, Windows 10 Pro or Enterprise instances that enrolled for device management, or macOS instances that are managed via MDM or joined to a domain via MCX.","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-04-01T11:55:42\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Microsoft Defender SmartScreen must be configured to block potentially unwanted apps.)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\\SmartScreenPuaEnabled'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n"},{"security_override_guidance":"","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","third_party_tools":"","rule_title":"The download location prompt must be configured.","rule_id":"SV-235765r960963","weight":"10.0","stig_uuid":"A516DDF1-722B-1014-B1EE-8476FA977258","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"ia_controls":"","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000141","id":"V-235765"},"group_id":"V-235765","mitigations":"","documentable":"false","fix_text":"Set the policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Ask where to save downloaded files\" to \"enabled\".","rule_id_src":"SV-235765r960963_rule","status":"open","group_id_src":"V-235765","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.edge:def:140","href":"U_MS_Edge_V2R4_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV14-oval.xml"},"reference_identifier":"5280","classification":"Unclassified","potential_impacts":"","severity":"low","responsibility":"","comments":null,"rule_version":"EDGE-00-000052","check_content":"The policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Ask where to save downloaded files\" must be set to \"enabled\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\nHKLM\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\n\nIf the value for \"PromptForDownloadLocation\" is not set to \"REG_DWORD = 1\", this is a finding.","false_positives":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"uuid":"A51DDF01-722B-1014-8C37-B708378E4AF8","discussion":"This setting provides positive feedback before a download starts, limiting the possibility of inadvertent downloads without notifying the user.","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-04-01T11:55:42\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Prompt for download location)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\\PromptForDownloadLocation'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n"},{"security_override_guidance":"","group_title":"SRG-APP-000148","third_party_tools":"","rule_title":"Tracking of browsing activity must be disabled.","rule_id":"SV-235766r1051115","weight":"10.0","stig_uuid":"A516DDF1-722B-1014-B1EE-8476FA977258","ccis":["CCI-000388"],"ia_controls":"","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000148","id":"V-235766"},"group_id":"V-235766","mitigations":"","documentable":"false","fix_text":"Set the policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Block tracking of users' web-browsing activity\" to \"Balanced\" or \"Strict\".","rule_id_src":"SV-235766r1051115_rule","status":"open","group_id_src":"V-235766","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.edge:def:141","href":"U_MS_Edge_V2R4_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV14-oval.xml"},"reference_identifier":"5280","classification":"Unclassified","potential_impacts":"","severity":"medium","responsibility":"","comments":null,"rule_version":"EDGE-00-000054","check_content":"The policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Block tracking of users' web-browsing activity\" must be set to \"Enabled\" with the option value set to \"Balanced\" or \"Strict\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\nHKLM\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\n\nIf the value for \"TrackingPrevention\" is not set to \"REG_DWORD = 2\" or \"REG_DWORD = 3\", this is a finding.","false_positives":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"uuid":"A51DE988-722B-1014-A3A0-A1D865B600F9","discussion":"The setting allows websites to be blocked from tracking users' web-browsing activity.\n\nIf this policy is disabled or is not configured, users can set their own level of tracking prevention.\n\nPolicy options mapping:\n- TrackingPreventionOff (0) = Off (no tracking prevention)\n- TrackingPreventionBasic (1) = Basic (blocks harmful trackers; content and ads will be personalized)\n- TrackingPreventionBalanced (2) = Balanced (blocks harmful trackers and trackers from sites user has not visited; content and ads will be less personalized)\n- TrackingPreventionStrict (3) = Strict (blocks harmful trackers and majority of trackers from all sites; content and ads will have minimal personalization; some parts of sites might not work)","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-04-01T11:55:42\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Tracking of browsing activity must be disabled.)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\\TrackingPrevention'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n"},{"security_override_guidance":"","group_title":"SRG-APP-000149","third_party_tools":"","rule_title":"A website's ability to query for payment methods must be disabled.","rule_id":"SV-235767r960972","weight":"10.0","stig_uuid":"A516DDF1-722B-1014-B1EE-8476FA977258","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"ia_controls":"","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000149","id":"V-235767"},"group_id":"V-235767","mitigations":"","documentable":"false","fix_text":"Set the policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Allow websites to query for available payment methods\" to \"disabled\".","rule_id_src":"SV-235767r960972_rule","status":"open","group_id_src":"V-235767","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.edge:def:142","href":"U_MS_Edge_V2R4_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV14-oval.xml"},"reference_identifier":"5280","classification":"Unclassified","potential_impacts":"","severity":"medium","responsibility":"","comments":null,"rule_version":"EDGE-00-000055","check_content":"The policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Allow websites to query for available payment methods\" must be set to \"disabled\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\nHKLM\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\n\nIf the value for PaymentMethodQueryEnabled is not set to \"REG_DWORD = 0\", this is a finding.","false_positives":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"uuid":"A51DF458-722B-1014-B063-E0EE18ED50FC","discussion":"This setting determines whether websites can check if the user has payment methods saved.\n\nIf this policy is disabled, websites that use \"PaymentRequest.canMakePayment\" or \"PaymentRequest.hasEnrolledInstrument\" API will be informed that no payment methods are available.\n\nIf this policy is enabled or is not set, websites can check to determine if the user has payment methods saved.","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-04-01T11:55:42\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Disable the setting 'Allow websites to query for available payment methods')\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\\PaymentMethodQueryEnabled'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n"},{"security_override_guidance":"","group_title":"SRG-APP-000151","third_party_tools":"","rule_title":"Suggestions of similar web pages in the event of a navigation error must be disabled.","rule_id":"SV-235768r1015298","weight":"10.0","stig_uuid":"A516DDF1-722B-1014-B1EE-8476FA977258","ccis":["CCI-000381","CCI-000767"],"ia_controls":"","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000151","id":"V-235768"},"group_id":"V-235768","mitigations":"","documentable":"false","fix_text":"Set the policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Suggest similar pages when a webpage can't be found\" to \"Disabled\".","rule_id_src":"SV-235768r1015298_rule","status":"open","group_id_src":"V-235768","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.edge:def:143","href":"U_MS_Edge_V2R4_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV14-oval.xml"},"reference_identifier":"5280","classification":"Unclassified","potential_impacts":"","severity":"medium","responsibility":"","comments":null,"rule_version":"EDGE-00-000056","check_content":"The policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Suggest similar pages when a webpage can't be found\" must be set to \"Disabled\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\nHKLM\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\n\nIf the value for AlternateErrorPagesEnabled is not set to \"REG_DWORD = 0\", this is a finding.","false_positives":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"uuid":"A51DFE90-722B-1014-A715-B9F00B1D22A2","discussion":"This setting allows Microsoft Edge to issue a connection to a web service to generate URL and search suggestions for connectivity issues such as DNS errors.\n\nIf this policy is enabled, a web service is used to generate URL and search suggestions for network errors.\n\nIf this policy is disabled, no calls to the web service are made and a standard error page is shown.\n\nIf this policy is not configured, Microsoft Edge respects the user preference that is set under Services at edge://settings/privacy. Specifically, there is a \"Suggest similar pages when a webpage can't be found\" toggle, which the user can switch on or off. \n\nNote that if this policy has been enabled (AlternateErrorPagesEnabled), the \"Suggest similar pages when a webpage can't be found setting\" is turned on, but the user cannot change the setting by using the toggle. \n\nIf this policy is disabled, the \"Suggest similar pages when a webpage can't be found\" setting is turned off, and the user cannot change the setting by using the toggle.","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-04-01T11:55:42\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Suggestions of similar web pages in the event of a navigation error must be disabled.)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\\AlternateErrorPagesEnabled'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n"},{"security_override_guidance":"","group_title":"SRG-APP-000152","third_party_tools":"","rule_title":"User feedback must be disabled.","rule_id":"SV-235769r960981","weight":"10.0","stig_uuid":"A516DDF1-722B-1014-B1EE-8476FA977258","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"ia_controls":"","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000152","id":"V-235769"},"group_id":"V-235769","mitigations":"","documentable":"false","fix_text":"Set the policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Allow user feedback\" to \"disabled\".","rule_id_src":"SV-235769r960981_rule","status":"open","group_id_src":"V-235769","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.edge:def:144","href":"U_MS_Edge_V2R4_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV14-oval.xml"},"reference_identifier":"5280","classification":"Unclassified","potential_impacts":"","severity":"medium","responsibility":"","comments":null,"rule_version":"EDGE-00-000057","check_content":"The policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Allow user feedback\" must be set to \"disabled\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\nHKLM\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\n\nIf the value for UserFeedbackAllowed is not set to \"REG_DWORD = 0\", this is a finding.","false_positives":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"uuid":"A51E07F8-722B-1014-AA41-CF3D10DB9688","discussion":"Microsoft Edge uses the Edge Feedback feature (enabled by default) to allow users to send feedback, suggestions, or customer surveys and to report any issues with the browser. By default, users cannot disable (turn off) the Edge Feedback feature.\n\nIf this policy is enabled or not configured, users can invoke Edge Feedback.\n\nIf this policy is disabled, users cannot invoke Edge Feedback.","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-04-01T11:55:42\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Disable the setting 'Allow user feedback')\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\\UserFeedbackAllowed'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n"},{"security_override_guidance":"","group_title":"SRG-APP-000153","third_party_tools":"","rule_title":"The collections feature must be disabled.","rule_id":"SV-235770r960984","weight":"10.0","stig_uuid":"A516DDF1-722B-1014-B1EE-8476FA977258","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"ia_controls":"","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000153","id":"V-235770"},"group_id":"V-235770","mitigations":"","documentable":"false","fix_text":"Set the policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Enable the Collections feature\" to \"Disabled\".","rule_id_src":"SV-235770r960984_rule","status":"open","group_id_src":"V-235770","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.edge:def:145","href":"U_MS_Edge_V2R4_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV14-oval.xml"},"reference_identifier":"5280","classification":"Unclassified","potential_impacts":"","severity":"medium","responsibility":"","comments":null,"rule_version":"EDGE-00-000058","check_content":"The policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Enable the Collections feature\" must be set to \"Disabled\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\nHKLM\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\n\nIf the value for \"EdgeCollectionsEnabled\" is not set to \"REG_DWORD = 0\", this is a finding.","false_positives":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"uuid":"A51E1122-722B-1014-B066-E51854B12FD8","discussion":"This setting allows users to access the Collections feature, where they can collect, organize, share, and export content more efficiently and with Office integration.\n\nIf this policy is enabled or not configured, users can access and use the Collections feature in Microsoft Edge.\n\nIf this policy is disabled, users cannot access and use Collections in Microsoft Edge.","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-04-01T11:55:42\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (The collections feature must be disabled.)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\\EdgeCollectionsEnabled'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n"},{"security_override_guidance":"","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","third_party_tools":"","rule_title":"The Share Experience feature must be disabled.","rule_id":"SV-235771r960963","weight":"10.0","stig_uuid":"A516DDF1-722B-1014-B1EE-8476FA977258","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"ia_controls":"","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000141","id":"V-235771"},"group_id":"V-235771","mitigations":"","documentable":"false","fix_text":"Set the policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Configure the Share experience\" to \"Don't allow using the Share experience\".","rule_id_src":"SV-235771r960963_rule","status":"open","group_id_src":"V-235771","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.edge:def:146","href":"U_MS_Edge_V2R4_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV14-oval.xml"},"reference_identifier":"5280","classification":"Unclassified","potential_impacts":"","severity":"medium","responsibility":"","comments":null,"rule_version":"EDGE-00-000059","check_content":"The policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Configure the Share experience\" must be set to \"enabled\" with the option value set to \"Don't allow using the Share experience\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\nHKLM\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\n\nIf the value for \"ConfigureShare\" is not set to \"REG_DWORD = 1\", this is a finding.","false_positives":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"uuid":"A51E1BA8-722B-1014-9EAD-F15A37A6C692","discussion":"If this policy is set to \"ShareAllowed\" (the default), users will be able to access the Windows 10 Share experience from the Settings and More menu in Microsoft Edge to share with other apps on the system.\n\nIf this policy is set to \"ShareDisallowed\", users will not be able to access the Windows 10 Share experience. If the Share button is on the toolbar, it will also be hidden.\n\nPolicy options mapping:\n- ShareAllowed (0) = Allow using the Share experience.\n- ShareDisallowed (1) = Do not allow using the Share experience.","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-04-01T11:55:42\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Enable the setting 'Enable site isolation for every site')\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\\ConfigureShare'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n"},{"security_override_guidance":"","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","third_party_tools":"","rule_title":"Guest mode must be disabled.","rule_id":"SV-235772r960963","weight":"10.0","stig_uuid":"A516DDF1-722B-1014-B1EE-8476FA977258","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"ia_controls":"","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000141","id":"V-235772"},"group_id":"V-235772","mitigations":"","documentable":"false","fix_text":"Set the policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Enable guest mode\" to \"disabled\".","rule_id_src":"SV-235772r960963_rule","status":"open","group_id_src":"V-235772","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.edge:def:147","href":"U_MS_Edge_V2R4_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV14-oval.xml"},"reference_identifier":"5280","classification":"Unclassified","potential_impacts":"","severity":"medium","responsibility":"","comments":null,"rule_version":"EDGE-00-000060","check_content":"The policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Enable guest mode\" must be set to \"disabled\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\nHKLM\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\n\nIf the value for \"BrowserGuestModeEnabled\" is not set to \"REG_DWORD = 0\", this is a finding.","false_positives":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"uuid":"A51E24D3-722B-1014-82A1-D332209389D6","discussion":"Enabling Guest mode allows the use of guest profiles in Microsoft Edge. In a guest profile, the browser does not import browsing data from existing profiles, and it deletes browsing data when all guest profiles are closed.\n\nIf this policy is enabled or not configured, Microsoft Edge lets users browse in guest profiles.\n\nIf this policy is disabled, Microsoft Edge does not let users browse in guest profiles.","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-04-01T11:55:42\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Disable Browser Guest Mode)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\\BrowserGuestModeEnabled'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n"},{"security_override_guidance":"","group_title":"SRG-APP-000156","third_party_tools":"","rule_title":"Relaunch notification must be required.","rule_id":"SV-235773r960993","weight":"10.0","stig_uuid":"A516DDF1-722B-1014-B1EE-8476FA977258","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"ia_controls":"","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000156","id":"V-235773"},"group_id":"V-235773","mitigations":"","documentable":"false","fix_text":"Set the policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Notify a user that a browser restart is recommended or required for pending updates\" web-browsing activity to \"Required\".","rule_id_src":"SV-235773r960993_rule","status":"open","group_id_src":"V-235773","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.edge:def:148","href":"U_MS_Edge_V2R4_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV14-oval.xml"},"reference_identifier":"5280","classification":"Unclassified","potential_impacts":"","severity":"medium","responsibility":"","comments":null,"rule_version":"EDGE-00-000061","check_content":"The policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Notify a user that a browser restart is recommended or required for pending updates\" must be set to \"Enabled\" with the option value set to \"Required\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\nHKLM\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\n\nIf the value for \"RelaunchNotification\" is not set to \"REG_DWORD = 2\", this is a finding.","false_positives":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"uuid":"A51E2E1F-722B-1014-B799-C68729176A8E","discussion":"Users must be required to restart the browser to finish installation of pending updates and prevent users from continually using an old/vulnerable browser version.","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-04-01T11:55:42\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Relaunch notification must be required.)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\\RelaunchNotification'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n"},{"security_override_guidance":"","group_title":"SRG-APP-000157","third_party_tools":"","rule_title":"The built-in DNS client must be disabled.","rule_id":"SV-235774r1015299","weight":"10.0","stig_uuid":"A516DDF1-722B-1014-B1EE-8476FA977258","ccis":["CCI-001941","CCI-001942"],"ia_controls":"","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000157","id":"V-235774"},"group_id":"V-235774","mitigations":"","documentable":"false","fix_text":"Set the policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Use built-in DNS client\" to \"disabled\".","rule_id_src":"SV-235774r1015299_rule","status":"open","group_id_src":"V-235774","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.edge:def:149","href":"U_MS_Edge_V2R4_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV14-oval.xml"},"reference_identifier":"5280","classification":"Unclassified","potential_impacts":"","severity":"medium","responsibility":"","comments":null,"rule_version":"EDGE-00-000062","check_content":"The policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Use built-in DNS client\" must be set to \"disabled\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\nHKLM\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\n\nIf the value for \"BuiltInDnsClientEnabled\" is not set to \"REG_DWORD = 0\", this is a finding.","false_positives":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"uuid":"A51E3756-722B-1014-AEA9-E8CB87054124","discussion":"This setting controls whether to use the built-in DNS client.\n\nThis does not affect which DNS servers are used; it only controls the software stack that is used to communicate with them. For example, if the operating system is configured to use an enterprise DNS server, that same server would be used by the built-in DNS client. However, it is however possible that the built-in DNS client will address servers in different ways by using more modern DNS-related protocols such as DNS-over-TLS.\n\nIf this policy is enabled, the built-in DNS client is used if it is available.\n\nIf this policy is disabled, the client is never used.","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-04-01T11:55:42\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Built in DNS client is disabled)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\\BuiltInDnsClientEnabled'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n"},{"security_override_guidance":"","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","third_party_tools":"","rule_title":"Use of the QUIC protocol must be disabled.","rule_id":"SV-246736r960963","weight":"10.0","stig_uuid":"A516DDF1-722B-1014-B1EE-8476FA977258","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"ia_controls":"","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000141","id":"V-246736"},"group_id":"V-246736","mitigations":"","documentable":"false","fix_text":"Set the policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Allow QUIC protocol\" to \"Disabled\".","rule_id_src":"SV-246736r960963_rule","status":"not_a_finding","group_id_src":"V-246736","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.edge:def:150","href":"U_MS_Edge_V2R4_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV14-oval.xml"},"reference_identifier":"5280","classification":"Unclassified","potential_impacts":"","severity":"medium","responsibility":"","comments":null,"rule_version":"EDGE-00-000063","check_content":"The policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Allow QUIC protocol\" must be set to \"Disabled\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\nHKLM\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\n\nIf the value for \"QuicAllowed\" is not set to \"REG_DWORD = 0\", this is a finding.","false_positives":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"uuid":"A51E4075-722B-1014-9E47-F59760384C5C","discussion":"QUIC is used by more than half of all connections from the Edge web browser to Google's servers, and this activity is undesirable in the DoD.\n\nIf you enable this policy or don't configure it, the QUIC protocol is allowed.\n\nIf you disable this policy, the QUIC protocol is blocked.","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-04-01T11:55:42\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (QUIC protocol is disabled)\n"},{"security_override_guidance":"","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","third_party_tools":"","rule_title":"The list of domains media autoplay allows must be allowlisted if used.","rule_id":"SV-251694r960963","weight":"10.0","stig_uuid":"A516DDF1-722B-1014-B1EE-8476FA977258","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"ia_controls":"","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000141","id":"V-251694"},"group_id":"V-251694","mitigations":"","documentable":"false","fix_text":"The policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Allow media autoplay on specific sites\" may be set to \"allow\" for allowlisted domains.","rule_id_src":"SV-251694r960963_rule","status":"not_reviewed","group_id_src":"V-251694","check_content_ref":{"name":"ocil:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.edge:questionnaire:10901","href":"U_MS_Edge_V2R4_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV14-ocil.xml"},"reference_identifier":"5280","classification":"Unclassified","potential_impacts":"","severity":"low","responsibility":"","comments":null,"rule_version":"EDGE-00-000064","check_content":"If this machine is on SIPRNet, this is Not Applicable.\n\nThis requirement for \"AutoplayAllowlist\" is not required; this is optional.\n\nThe policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Allow media autoplay on specific sites\" may be set to \"allow\" for allowlisted domains.\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\nHKLM\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\n\nAutoplayAllowlist may be set as follows:\nHKLM\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\\AutoplayAllowlist\\1 = mydomain.com\nHKLM\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\\AutoplayAllowlist\\2 = myagency.mil\n\nIf configured, the list of domains for which autoplay is allowed may be allowlisted.","false_positives":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"uuid":"A51E496B-722B-1014-8CF2-BC7C98C031F4","discussion":"Define a list of sites, based on URL patterns, that are allowed to autoplay media.\n\nIf this policy is not configured, the global default value from the AutoplayAllowed policy (if set) or the user's personal configuration is used for all sites.\n\nEDGE-00-000024 disables the AutoplayAllowed policy. ","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-04-01T11:55:42\nResult: notcheckedCriteria        : NOT_TESTED (All child tests must be true.)\nTest            :   NOT_TESTED (CAT III, V-251694, SV-251694r960963, SRG-APP-000141)\n"},{"security_override_guidance":"","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","third_party_tools":"","rule_title":"Visual Search must be disabled.","rule_id":"SV-260465r960963","weight":"10.0","stig_uuid":"A516DDF1-722B-1014-B1EE-8476FA977258","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"ia_controls":"","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000141","id":"V-260465"},"group_id":"V-260465","mitigations":"","documentable":"false","fix_text":"Set the policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Visual search enabled\" to \"Disabled\".","rule_id_src":"SV-260465r960963_rule","status":"open","group_id_src":"V-260465","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.edge:def:260465","href":"U_MS_Edge_V2R4_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV14-oval.xml"},"reference_identifier":"5280","classification":"Unclassified","potential_impacts":"","severity":"medium","responsibility":"","comments":null,"rule_version":"EDGE-00-000065","check_content":"Verify the policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Visual search enabled\" is set to \"Disabled\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\nHKLM\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\n\nIf the value for \"VisualSearchEnabled\" is not set to \"REG_DWORD = 0\", this is a finding.","false_positives":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"uuid":"A51E524A-722B-1014-9491-C3BB500A7352","discussion":"Visual Search allows for quick exploration of more related content about entities in an image.\n\nIf this policy is enabled or not configured, Visual Search will be enabled via image hover, context menu, and search in Sidebar.\n\nIf this policy is disabled, Visual Search will be disabled and more information about images will not be available via hover, context menu, and search in Sidebar.","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-04-01T11:55:42\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Visual Search is disabled)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\\VisualSearchEnabled'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n"},{"security_override_guidance":"","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","third_party_tools":"","rule_title":"Copilot must be disabled.","rule_id":"SV-260466r960963","weight":"10.0","stig_uuid":"A516DDF1-722B-1014-B1EE-8476FA977258","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"ia_controls":"","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000141","id":"V-260466"},"group_id":"V-260466","mitigations":"","documentable":"false","fix_text":"Set the policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Show Hubs Sidebar\" to \"Disabled\".","rule_id_src":"SV-260466r960963_rule","status":"not_a_finding","group_id_src":"V-260466","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.edge:def:260466","href":"U_MS_Edge_V2R4_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV14-oval.xml"},"reference_identifier":"5280","classification":"Unclassified","potential_impacts":"","severity":"medium","responsibility":"","comments":null,"rule_version":"EDGE-00-000066","check_content":"Verify the policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Show Hubs Sidebar\" is set to \"Disabled\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\nHKLM\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\n\nIf the value for \"HubsSidebarEnabled\" is not set to \"REG_DWORD = 0\", this is a finding.","false_positives":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"uuid":"A51E5B5A-722B-1014-9E42-AC02E750C864","discussion":"The Sidebar is a launcher bar on the right side of Microsoft Edge's screen.\n\nIf this policy is enabled or not configured, the Sidebar will be shown. If this policy is disabled, the Sidebar will never be shown.\n\nDisabling Sidebar will disable Copilot.","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-04-01T11:55:42\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Copilot is disabled)\n"},{"security_override_guidance":"","group_title":"SRG-APP-000080","third_party_tools":"","rule_title":"Session only-based cookies must be enabled.","rule_id":"SV-260467r960864","weight":"10.0","stig_uuid":"A516DDF1-722B-1014-B1EE-8476FA977258","ccis":["CCI-000166"],"ia_controls":"","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000080","id":"V-260467"},"group_id":"V-260467","mitigations":"","documentable":"false","fix_text":"Set the policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Content settings/Configure cookies\" to \"Enabled\" with the option value set to \"Keep cookies for the duration of the session, except ones listed in 'SaveCookiesOnExit'\".","rule_id_src":"SV-260467r960864_rule","status":"open","group_id_src":"V-260467","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.edge:def:260467","href":"U_MS_Edge_V2R4_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV14-oval.xml"},"reference_identifier":"5280","classification":"Unclassified","potential_impacts":"","severity":"medium","responsibility":"","comments":null,"rule_version":"EDGE-00-000067","check_content":"Verify the policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Content settings/Configure cookies\" is set to \"Enabled\" with the option value set to \"Keep cookies for the duration of the session, except ones listed in 'SaveCookiesOnExit'\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\nHKLM\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\n\nIf the value for âDefaultCookiesSettingâ is not set to \"REG_DWORD = 4\", this is a finding.","false_positives":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"uuid":"A51E6527-722B-1014-8D31-B088433B3234","discussion":"Cookies must only be allowed per session and only for approved URLs as permanently stored cookies can be used for malicious intent. \n\nApproved URLs may be allowlisted via the \"CookiesAllowedForUrls\" or \"SaveCookiesOnExit\" policy settings, but these are not requirements.","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-04-01T11:55:42\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Session only-based cookies is enabled)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\\DefaultCookiesSetting'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n"},{"security_override_guidance":"","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","third_party_tools":"","rule_title":"FriendlyURLs must be disabled.","rule_id":"SV-266981r1169858","weight":"10.0","stig_uuid":"A516DDF1-722B-1014-B1EE-8476FA977258","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"ia_controls":"","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000141","id":"V-266981"},"group_id":"V-266981","mitigations":"","documentable":"false","fix_text":"Set the policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft EdgeConfigure the default paste format of URLs copied from Microsoft Edge, and determine if additional formats will be available to users\" to \"enabled\" and select \"The plain URL without any extra information, such as the pageÂ´s title. This is the recommended option when this policy is configured. For more information, see the description.\"","rule_id_src":"SV-266981r1169858_rule","status":"open","group_id_src":"V-266981","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.edge:def:266981","href":"U_MS_Edge_V2R4_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV14-oval.xml"},"reference_identifier":"5280","classification":"Unclassified","potential_impacts":"","severity":"medium","responsibility":"","comments":null,"rule_version":"EDGE-00-000068","check_content":"The policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Configure the default paste format of URLs copied from Microsoft Edge and determine if additional formats will be available to users\" must be set to \"enabled\" with the option value set to \"The plain URL without any extra information, such as the pageÂ´s title. This is the recommended option when this policy is configured. For more information, see the description.\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\nHKLM\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\n\nIf the value for \"ConfigureFriendlyURLFormat\" is not set to \"REG_DWORD = 1\", this is a finding.","false_positives":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"uuid":"A51E6FB3-722B-1014-9351-8201921ACB45","discussion":"If FriendlyURLs are enabled, Microsoft Edge will compute additional representations of the URL and place them on the clipboard.\n\nThis policy configures what format will be pasted when the user pastes in external applications, or inside Microsoft Edge without the \"Paste As\" context menu item.\n\nIf configured, this policy makes a choice on behalf of the user. The options in edge://settings/shareCopyPaste will be grayed out, and the options in the \"Paste As\" context menu will not be available.\n\nNot configured = The user will be able to choose their preferred paste format. By default, this is set to the friendly URL format. The \"Paste As\" menu will be available in Microsoft Edge.\n\n1 = No additional formats will be stored on the clipboard. There will be no \"Paste as\" context menu item in Microsoft Edge and the only format available to paste will be the plain text URL format. Effectively, the friendly URL feature will be disabled.\n\n3 = The user will get a friendly URL whenever they paste into surfaces that accept rich text. The plain URL will still be available for non-rich surfaces. There will be no \"Paste As\" menu in Microsoft Edge.\n\n4 = (Not currently used)\n\nThe richer formats may not be well-supported in some paste destinations and/or websites. In these scenarios, the plain URL option is recommended when configuring this policy.\n\nThe recommended policy is available in Microsoft Edge 105 or later.\n\nPolicy options mapping:\n\nPlainText (1) = The plain URL without any extra information, such as the page's title. This is the recommended option when this policy is configured. For more information, see the description.\n\nTitledHyperlink (3) = Titled Hyperlink: A hyperlink that points to the copied URL, but whose visible text is the title of the destination page. This is the Friendly URL format.","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-04-01T11:55:42\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (FriendlyURLs is enabled)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\\ConfigureFriendlyURLFormat'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n"},{"security_override_guidance":"","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","third_party_tools":"","rule_title":"Access to Microsoft 365 Copilot writing assistance must be disabled.","rule_id":"SV-279940r1156561","weight":"10.0","stig_uuid":"A516DDF1-722B-1014-B1EE-8476FA977258","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"ia_controls":"","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000141","id":"V-279940"},"group_id":"V-279940","mitigations":"","documentable":"false","fix_text":"Set the policy value for \"Control access to Microsoft 365 Copilot writing assistance in Microsoft Edge for Business\" to \"disabled\".","rule_id_src":"SV-279940r1156561_rule","status":"open","group_id_src":"V-279940","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.edge:def:279940","href":"U_MS_Edge_V2R4_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV14-oval.xml"},"reference_identifier":"5280","classification":"Unclassified","potential_impacts":"","severity":"medium","responsibility":"","comments":null,"rule_version":"EDGE-00-000069","check_content":"The policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Control access to Microsoft 365 Copilot writing assistance in Microsoft Edge for Business\" must be set to \"disabled\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\nHKLM\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\n\nIf the value for \"ComposeInlineEnabled\" is not set to \"REG_DWORD = 0\", this is a finding.","false_positives":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"uuid":"A51E799C-722B-1014-A359-F8419767CCF3","discussion":"This policy controls whether users can use writing support features in Microsoft Edge for Business, such as Rewrite, which utilizes Microsoft 365 Copilot Chat.","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-04-01T11:55:42\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Access to Microsoft 365 Copilot writing assistance is disabled)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\\ComposeInlineEnabled'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n"}],"size":60,"uuid":"A516DDF1-722B-1014-B1EE-8476FA977258","display_name":"Microsoft Edge","stig_id":"MS_Edge_STIG","release_info":"Release: 4 Benchmark Date: 05 Jan 2026","version":"2"},{"stig_name":"Microsoft Office 365 ProPlus Security Technical Implementation Guide","reference_identifier":"4099","classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","rules":[{"security_override_guidance":"","group_title":"SRG-APP-000179","third_party_tools":"","rule_title":"Macros must be blocked from running in Access files from the Internet.","rule_id":"SV-223280r961050","weight":"10.0","stig_uuid":"B3EF3B6E-722B-1014-942B-D54B65175630","ccis":["CCI-001170"],"ia_controls":"","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000179","id":"V-223280"},"group_id":"V-223280","mitigations":"","documentable":"false","fix_text":"Set the policy value for User Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Microsoft Access 2016 &gt;&gt; Application Settings &gt;&gt; Security &gt;&gt; Trust Center \"Block macros from running in Office files from the Internet\" to \"Enabled\".","rule_id_src":"SV-223280r961050_rule","status":"not_applicable","group_id_src":"V-223280","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.office365:def:223280","href":"U_MS_Office_365_ProPlus_V3R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV9-oval.xml"},"reference_identifier":"4099","classification":"Unclassified","potential_impacts":"","severity":"medium","responsibility":"","comments":null,"rule_version":"O365-AC-000001","check_content":"Verify the policy value for User Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Microsoft Access 2016 &gt;&gt; Application Settings &gt;&gt; Security &gt;&gt; Trust Center \"Block macros from running in Office files from the Internet\" is set to \"Enabled\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \n\nHKCU\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Office\\16.0\\access\\security\n\nIf the value blockcontentexecutionfrominternet is REG_DWORD = 1, this is not a finding.","false_positives":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-108737","V-99633"],"uuid":"B401F05B-722B-1014-8BD1-C5C31A42B27F","discussion":"This policy setting allows you to block macros from running in Office files that come from the Internet.\n\nIf you enable this policy setting, macros are blocked from running, even if âEnable all macrosâ is selected in the Macro Settings section of the Trust Center. Also, instead of having the choice to âEnable Contentâ, users will receive a notification that macros are blocked from running. If the Office file is saved to a trusted location or was previously trusted by the user, macros will be allowed to run.\n\nIf you disable or do not configure this policy setting, the settings configured in the Macro Settings section of the Trust Center determine whether macros run in Office files that come from the Internet.","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-04-01T11:55:55\nResult: notapplicableRule Result     : Not Applicable\n"},{"security_override_guidance":"","group_title":"SRG-APP-000131","third_party_tools":"","rule_title":"Trust Bar Notifications for unsigned application add-ins in Access must be disabled and blocked.","rule_id":"SV-223281r1016166","weight":"10.0","stig_uuid":"B3EF3B6E-722B-1014-942B-D54B65175630","ccis":["CCI-003992","CCI-001749"],"ia_controls":"","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000131","id":"V-223281"},"group_id":"V-223281","mitigations":"","documentable":"false","fix_text":"Set the policy value for User Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Microsoft Access 2016 &gt;&gt; Application Settings &gt;&gt; Security &gt;&gt; Trust Center \"Disable Trust Bar Notification for unsigned application add-ins and block them\" to \"Enabled\".","rule_id_src":"SV-223281r1016166_rule","status":"not_applicable","group_id_src":"V-223281","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.office365:def:223281","href":"U_MS_Office_365_ProPlus_V3R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV9-oval.xml"},"reference_identifier":"4099","classification":"Unclassified","potential_impacts":"","severity":"medium","responsibility":"","comments":null,"rule_version":"O365-AC-000002","check_content":"Verify the policy value for User Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Microsoft Access 2016 &gt;&gt; Application Settings &gt;&gt; Security &gt;&gt; Trust Center \"Disable Trust Bar Notification for unsigned application add-ins and block them\" is set to \"Enabled\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \n\nHKCU\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Office\\16.0\\access\\security\n\nIf the value NoTBPromptUnsignedAddin is REG_DWORD = 1, this is not a finding.","false_positives":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-108739","V-99635"],"uuid":"B401F8B8-722B-1014-B0CE-CC27CAE014C8","discussion":"This policy setting controls whether the specified Office application notifies users when unsigned application add-ins are loaded or silently disable such add-ins without notification. This policy setting only applies if the \"Require that application add-ins are signed by Trusted Publisher\" policy setting is enabled, which prevents users from changing this policy setting.\n\nIf users enable this policy setting, applications automatically disable unsigned add-ins without informing users.\n\nIf this policy setting is disabled, if this application is configured to require that all add-ins be signed by a trusted publisher, any unsigned add-ins the application loads will be disabled and the application will display the Trust Bar at the top of the active window. The Trust Bar contains a message that informs users about the unsigned add-in.\n\nIf users do not configure this policy setting, the disable behavior applies, and in addition, users can configure this requirement themselves in the \"Add-ins\" category of the Trust Center for the application.","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-04-01T11:55:55\nResult: notapplicableRule Result     : Not Applicable\n"},{"security_override_guidance":"","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","third_party_tools":"","rule_title":"VBA macros not digitally signed must be blocked in Access.","rule_id":"SV-223282r1082349","weight":"10.0","stig_uuid":"B3EF3B6E-722B-1014-942B-D54B65175630","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"ia_controls":"","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000141","id":"V-223282"},"group_id":"V-223282","mitigations":"","documentable":"false","fix_text":"Set User Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Microsoft Access 2016 &gt;&gt; Application Settings &gt;&gt; Security &gt;&gt; Trust Center &gt;&gt; VBA Macro Notification Settings to \"Disable all except digitally signed macros\".","rule_id_src":"SV-223282r1082349_rule","status":"not_applicable","group_id_src":"V-223282","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.office365:def:223282","href":"U_MS_Office_365_ProPlus_V3R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV9-oval.xml"},"reference_identifier":"4099","classification":"Unclassified","potential_impacts":"","severity":"medium","responsibility":"","comments":null,"rule_version":"O365-AC-000003","check_content":"Verify the policy value for User Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Microsoft Access 2016 &gt;&gt; Application Settings &gt;&gt; Security &gt;&gt; Trust Center &gt;&gt; VBA Macro Notification Settings is set to \"Disable all except digitally signed macros\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \n\nHKCU\\software\\policies\\Microsoft\\office\\16.0\\access\\security\n\nIf the value vbawarnings is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding. A value of REG_DWORD = 2 or REG_DWORD =  4 is also acceptable. If the registry key does not exist, or is not configured properly, this is a finding.","false_positives":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-108741","V-99637"],"uuid":"B401FF28-722B-1014-8F7E-DD6EA8AB5F7D","discussion":"This policy setting controls how the specified applications warn users when Visual Basic for Applications (VBA) macros are present.\n\nIf this policy setting is enabled, choose from four options for determining how the specified applications will warn the user about macros:\n\n- Disable all with notification: The application displays the Trust Bar for all macros, whether signed or unsigned. This option enforces the default configuration in Office. This option also allows users to potentially enable unsigned/untrusted macros. If a site requires the use of macros, they must be signed/approved and added to appropriate locations listed in the Trust Center Settings. \n- Disable all except digitally signed macros: The application displays the Trust Bar for digitally signed macros, allowing users to enable them or leave them disabled. Any unsigned macros are disabled, and users are not notified.\n- Disable all without notification: The application disables all macros, whether signed or unsigned, and does not notify users.\n- Enable all macros (not recommended): All macros are enabled, whether signed or unsigned. This option can significantly reduce security by allowing dangerous code to run undetected.\n\nIf this policy setting is disabled, \"Disable all with notification\" will be the default setting.\n\nIf this policy setting is not configured, when users open files in the specified applications that contain VBA macros, the applications open the files with the macros disabled and display the Trust Bar with a warning that macros are present and have been disabled. Users can inspect and edit the files if appropriate, but cannot use any disabled functionality until they enable it by clicking \"Enable Content\" on the Trust Bar. If the user clicks \"Enable Content\", then the document is added as a trusted document.\n\nImportant: If \"Disable all except digitally signed macros\" is selected, users will not be able to open unsigned Access databases.","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-04-01T11:55:55\nResult: notapplicableRule Result     : Not Applicable\n"},{"security_override_guidance":"","group_title":"SRG-APP-000210","third_party_tools":"","rule_title":"The Macro Runtime Scan Scope must be enabled for all documents.","rule_id":"SV-223284r961092","weight":"10.0","stig_uuid":"B3EF3B6E-722B-1014-942B-D54B65175630","ccis":["CCI-001170"],"ia_controls":"","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000210","id":"V-223284"},"group_id":"V-223284","mitigations":"","documentable":"false","fix_text":"Set the policy value for User Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Microsoft Office 2016&gt;&gt; Security Settings \"Macro Runtime Scan Scope\" to \"Enable for all documents\".","rule_id_src":"SV-223284r961092_rule","status":"open","group_id_src":"V-223284","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.office365:def:223284","href":"U_MS_Office_365_ProPlus_V3R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV9-oval.xml"},"reference_identifier":"4099","classification":"Unclassified","potential_impacts":"","severity":"medium","responsibility":"","comments":null,"rule_version":"O365-CO-000001","check_content":"Verify the policy value for User Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Microsoft Office 2016&gt;&gt; Security Settings \"Macro Runtime Scan Scope\" is set to \"Enable for all documents\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \n\nHKCU\\software\\policies\\microsoft\\office\\16.0\\common\\security\n\nIf the value for macroruntimescanscope is REG_DWORD = 2, this is not a finding.\n","false_positives":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-108745","V-99641"],"uuid":"B402048D-722B-1014-B628-BBB6079678E5","discussion":"This policy setting specifies for which documents the VBA Runtime Scan feature is enabled.\n\nIf the feature is disabled for all documents, no runtime scanning of enabled macros will be performed.\n\nIf the feature is enabled for low trust documents, the feature will be enabled for all documents for which macros are enabled except:\n - Documents opened while macro security settings are set to \"Enable All Macros\"\n - Documents opened from a Trusted Location\n - Documents that are Trusted Documents\n - Documents that contain VBA that is digitally signed by a Trusted Publisher\n\nIf the feature is enabled for all documents, then the above class of documents are not excluded from the behavior.\n\nThis protocol allows the VBA runtime to report to the Anti-Virus system certain high-risk code behaviors it is about to execute and allows the Anti-Virus to report back to the process if the sequence of observed behaviors indicates likely malicious activity so the Office application can take appropriate action.\n\nWhen this feature is enabled, affected VBA projects' runtime performance may be reduced.","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-04-01T11:55:55\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :   false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :     false (Macro Runtime Scan Scope is set to Enable for all documents ntuser check)\nResult Analysis :          Registry Name Not found in user profile ntuser.dat file(s): 'Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Office\\16.0\\common\\security\\macroruntimescanscope'.  Existence requirement is 'all_exist' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n                :          For 'MAXHEALTH\\katessem.admin':  Registry Name Not found in user profile ntuser.dat file(s): 'Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Office\\16.0\\common\\security\\macroruntimescanscope'.  \n                :          For 'MAXHEALTH\\katessem':  Registry Name Not found in user profile ntuser.dat file(s): 'Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Office\\16.0\\common\\security\\macroruntimescanscope'.  \n                :          For 'MHL-PW06M2V2\\Administrator':  Registry Name Not found in user profile ntuser.dat file(s): 'Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Office\\16.0\\common\\security\\macroruntimescanscope'.  \n"},{"security_override_guidance":"","group_title":"SRG-APP-000429","third_party_tools":"","rule_title":"Document metadata for rights managed Office Open XML files must be protected.","rule_id":"SV-223285r1067544","weight":"10.0","stig_uuid":"B3EF3B6E-722B-1014-942B-D54B65175630","ccis":["CCI-002476"],"ia_controls":"","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000429","id":"V-223285"},"group_id":"V-223285","mitigations":"","documentable":"false","fix_text":"Set the policy value for User Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Microsoft Office 2016 &gt;&gt; Security Settings \"Protect document metadata for rights managed Office Open XML Files\" to \"Enabled\".","rule_id_src":"SV-223285r1067544_rule","status":"open","group_id_src":"V-223285","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.office365:def:223285","href":"U_MS_Office_365_ProPlus_V3R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV9-oval.xml"},"reference_identifier":"4099","classification":"Unclassified","potential_impacts":"","severity":"high","responsibility":"","comments":null,"rule_version":"O365-CO-000002","check_content":"Verify the policy value for User Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Microsoft Office 2016 &gt;&gt; Security Settings \"Protect document metadata for rights managed Office Open XML Files\" is set to \"Enabled\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\n\nHKCU\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Office\\16.0\\common\\security\n\nIf the value DRMEncryptProperty is REG_DWORD = 1, this is not a finding.","false_positives":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-108747","V-99643"],"uuid":"B4020AB6-722B-1014-B6EA-BF1A229304B9","discussion":"This policy setting determines whether metadata is encrypted in Office Open XML files that are protected by Information Rights Management (IRM). If this policy setting is enabled, Excel, PowerPoint, and Word encrypt metadata stored in rights-managed Office Open XML files and override any configuration changes on users' computers. \n\nIf this policy setting is enabled, Office 2016 applications cannot encrypt metadata in rights-managed Office Open XML files, which can reduce security. If this policy setting is not configured when Information Rights Management (IRM) is used to restrict access to an Office Open XML document, any metadata associated with the document is not encrypted.","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-04-01T11:55:55\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :   false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :     false (Document metadata for rights managed Office Open XML files is protected.)\nResult Analysis :          Registry Name Not found in user profile ntuser.dat file(s): 'Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Office\\16.0\\common\\security\\drmencryptproperty'.  Existence requirement is 'all_exist' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n                :          For 'MAXHEALTH\\katessem.admin':  Registry Name Not found in user profile ntuser.dat file(s): 'Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Office\\16.0\\common\\security\\drmencryptproperty'.  \n                :          For 'MAXHEALTH\\katessem':  Registry Name Not found in user profile ntuser.dat file(s): 'Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Office\\16.0\\common\\security\\drmencryptproperty'.  \n                :          For 'MHL-PW06M2V2\\Administrator':  Registry Name Not found in user profile ntuser.dat file(s): 'Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Office\\16.0\\common\\security\\drmencryptproperty'.  \n"},{"security_override_guidance":"","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","third_party_tools":"","rule_title":"The Office client must be prevented from polling the SharePoint Server for published links.","rule_id":"SV-223286r960963","weight":"10.0","stig_uuid":"B3EF3B6E-722B-1014-942B-D54B65175630","ccis":["CCI-000381","CCI-001662"],"ia_controls":"","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000141","id":"V-223286"},"group_id":"V-223286","mitigations":"","documentable":"false","fix_text":"Set the policy value for User Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Microsoft Office 2016 &gt;&gt; Server Settings &gt;&gt; Disable the Office client from polling the SharePoint Server for published links to \"Enabled\".  ","rule_id_src":"SV-223286r960963_rule","status":"open","group_id_src":"V-223286","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.office365:def:223286","href":"U_MS_Office_365_ProPlus_V3R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV9-oval.xml"},"reference_identifier":"4099","classification":"Unclassified","potential_impacts":"","severity":"medium","responsibility":"","comments":null,"rule_version":"O365-CO-000003","check_content":"Verify the policy value for User Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Microsoft Office 2016 &gt;&gt; Server Settings &gt;&gt; Disable the Office client from polling the SharePoint Server for published links is set to \"Enabled\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \n\nHKCU\\software\\policies\\microsoft\\office\\16.0\\common\\portal\n\nIf the value for linkpublishingdisabled is REG_DWORD = \"1\", this is not a finding.\n","false_positives":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-108749","V-99645"],"uuid":"B4021025-722B-1014-9F93-EE5EEC098E0F","discussion":"This policy setting controls whether Office 365 ProPlus applications can poll Office servers to retrieve lists of published links. \n\nIf this policy setting is enabled, Office 365 ProPlus applications cannot poll an Office server for published links. \n\nIf this policy setting is disabled or not configured, users of Office 365 ProPlus applications can see and use links to Microsoft SharePoint Server sites from those applications. Published links can be configured to Office applications during initial deployment, and can add or change links as part of regular operations. These links appear on the My SharePoint Sites tab of the Open, Save, and Save As dialog boxes when opening and saving documents from these applications. Links can be targeted so they only appear to users who are members of particular audiences. \n\nNote: This policy setting applies to Microsoft SharePoint Server specifically. It does not apply to Microsoft SharePoint Foundation.\n","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-04-01T11:55:55\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :   false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :     false (The Office client is prevented from polling the SharePoint Server for published links.)\nResult Analysis :          Registry Name Not found in user profile ntuser.dat file(s): 'Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Office\\16.0\\common\\portal\\linkpublishingdisabled'.  Existence requirement is 'all_exist' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n                :          For 'MAXHEALTH\\katessem.admin':  Registry Name Not found in user profile ntuser.dat file(s): 'Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Office\\16.0\\common\\portal\\linkpublishingdisabled'.  \n                :          For 'MAXHEALTH\\katessem':  Registry Name Not found in user profile ntuser.dat file(s): 'Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Office\\16.0\\common\\portal\\linkpublishingdisabled'.  \n                :          For 'MHL-PW06M2V2\\Administrator':  Registry Name Not found in user profile ntuser.dat file(s): 'Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Office\\16.0\\common\\portal\\linkpublishingdisabled'.  \n"},{"security_override_guidance":"","group_title":"SRG-APP-000516","third_party_tools":"","rule_title":"Custom user interface (UI) code must be blocked from loading in all Office applications.","rule_id":"SV-223287r961863","weight":"10.0","stig_uuid":"B3EF3B6E-722B-1014-942B-D54B65175630","ccis":["CCI-000366"],"ia_controls":"","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000516","id":"V-223287"},"group_id":"V-223287","mitigations":"","documentable":"false","fix_text":"Set the policy value for User Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Microsoft Office 2016 &gt;&gt; Global Options &gt;&gt; Customize &gt;&gt; Disable UI extending from documents and templates to Enabled: Disallow in Word; Excel; PowerPoint; Access; Outlook; Publisher; Project; Visio; InfoPath.","rule_id_src":"SV-223287r961863_rule","status":"open","group_id_src":"V-223287","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.office365:def:223287","href":"U_MS_Office_365_ProPlus_V3R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV9-oval.xml"},"reference_identifier":"4099","classification":"Unclassified","potential_impacts":"","severity":"medium","responsibility":"","comments":null,"rule_version":"O365-CO-000004","check_content":"Verify the policy value for User Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Microsoft Office 2016 &gt;&gt; Global Options &gt;&gt; Customize &gt;&gt; Disable UI extending from documents and templates is set to Enabled: Disallow in Word; Excel; PowerPoint; Access; Outlook; Publisher; Project; Visio; InfoPath\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \n\nHKCU\\software\\policies\\microsoft\\office\\16.0\\common\\toolbars\n\nIf the value noextensibilitycustomizationfromdocument is REG_DWORD = 1 for all installed Office programs, this is not a finding.","false_positives":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-108751","V-99647"],"uuid":"B402161B-722B-1014-893D-BF08604F5DA4","discussion":"This policy setting controls whether Office 365 ProPlus applications load any custom user interface (UI) code included with a document or template. Office 365 ProPlus allows developers to extend the UI with customization code that is included in a document or template. \n\nIf this policy setting is enabled, Office 365 ProPlus applications cannot load any UI customization code included with documents and templates. \n\nIf this policy setting is not configured or disabled, Office 365 ProPlus applications load any UI customization code included with a document or template when opening it.","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-04-01T11:55:55\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :   false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :     true (One or more child tests must be true. (OR))\nTest            :       false (Disable UI extending from documents and templates is set to 'Enabled' for Access)\nResult Analysis :            Registry Name Not found in user profile ntuser.dat file(s): 'Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Office\\16.0\\common\\toolbars\\Access\\noextensibilitycustomizationfromdocument'.  Existence requirement is 'all_exist' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n                :            For 'MAXHEALTH\\katessem.admin':  Registry Name Not found in user profile ntuser.dat file(s): 'Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Office\\16.0\\common\\toolbars\\Access\\noextensibilitycustomizationfromdocument'.  \n                :            For 'MAXHEALTH\\katessem':  Registry Name Not found in user profile ntuser.dat file(s): 'Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Office\\16.0\\common\\toolbars\\Access\\noextensibilitycustomizationfromdocument'.  \n                :            For 'MHL-PW06M2V2\\Administrator':  Registry Name Not found in user profile ntuser.dat file(s): 'Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Office\\16.0\\common\\toolbars\\Access\\noextensibilitycustomizationfromdocument'.  \nCriteria        :       true (All child tests must be true. (AND)) (negated)\nTest            :         false (MS Access is installed.)\nResult Analysis :              Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\nCriteria        :     false (One or more child tests must be true. (OR))\nTest            :       false (Disable UI extending from documents and templates is set to 'Enabled' for Excel)\nResult Analysis :            Registry Name Not found in user profile ntuser.dat file(s): 'Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Office\\16.0\\common\\toolbars\\Excel\\noextensibilitycustomizationfromdocument'.  Existence requirement is 'all_exist' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n                :            For 'MAXHEALTH\\katessem.admin':  Registry Name Not found in user profile ntuser.dat file(s): 'Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Office\\16.0\\common\\toolbars\\Excel\\noextensibilitycustomizationfromdocument'.  \n                :            For 'MAXHEALTH\\katessem':  Registry Name Not found in user profile ntuser.dat file(s): 'Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Office\\16.0\\common\\toolbars\\Excel\\noextensibilitycustomizationfromdocument'.  \n                :            For 'MHL-PW06M2V2\\Administrator':  Registry Name Not found in user profile ntuser.dat file(s): 'Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Office\\16.0\\common\\toolbars\\Excel\\noextensibilitycustomizationfromdocument'.  \nCriteria        :       false (All child tests must be true. (AND)) (negated)\nTest            :         true (MS Excel is installed.)\nCriteria        :     true (One or more child tests must be true. (OR))\nTest            :       false (Disable UI extending from documents and templates is set to 'Enabled' for InfoPath)\nResult Analysis :            Registry Name Not found in user profile ntuser.dat file(s): 'Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Office\\16.0\\common\\toolbars\\InfoPath\\noextensibilitycustomizationfromdocument'.  Existence requirement is 'all_exist' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n                :            For 'MAXHEALTH\\katessem.admin':  Registry Name Not found in user profile ntuser.dat file(s): 'Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Office\\16.0\\common\\toolbars\\InfoPath\\noextensibilitycustomizationfromdocument'.  \n                :            For 'MAXHEALTH\\katessem':  Registry Name Not found in user profile ntuser.dat file(s): 'Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Office\\16.0\\common\\toolbars\\InfoPath\\noextensibilitycustomizationfromdocument'.  \n                :            For 'MHL-PW06M2V2\\Administrator':  Registry Name Not found in user profile ntuser.dat file(s): 'Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Office\\16.0\\common\\toolbars\\InfoPath\\noextensibilitycustomizationfromdocument'.  \nCriteria        :       true (All child tests must be true. (AND)) (negated)\nTest            :         false (Microsoft InfoPath 2013 is installed)\nResult Analysis :              Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\nCriteria        :     false (One or more child tests must be true. (OR))\nTest            :       false (Disable UI extending from documents and templates is set to 'Enabled' for Outlook)\nResult Analysis :            Registry Name Not found in user profile ntuser.dat file(s): 'Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Office\\16.0\\common\\toolbars\\Outlook\\noextensibilitycustomizationfromdocument'.  Existence requirement is 'all_exist' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n                :            For 'MAXHEALTH\\katessem.admin':  Registry Name Not found in user profile ntuser.dat file(s): 'Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Office\\16.0\\common\\toolbars\\Outlook\\noextensibilitycustomizationfromdocument'.  \n                :            For 'MAXHEALTH\\katessem':  Registry Name Not found in user profile ntuser.dat file(s): 'Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Office\\16.0\\common\\toolbars\\Outlook\\noextensibilitycustomizationfromdocument'.  \n                :            For 'MHL-PW06M2V2\\Administrator':  Registry Name Not found in user profile ntuser.dat file(s): 'Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Office\\16.0\\common\\toolbars\\Outlook\\noextensibilitycustomizationfromdocument'.  \nCriteria        :       false (All child tests must be true. (AND)) (negated)\nTest            :         true (MS Outlook is installed.)\nCriteria        :     false (One or more child tests must be true. (OR))\nTest            :       false (Disable UI extending from documents and templates is set to 'Enabled' for PowerPoint)\nResult Analysis :            Registry Name Not found in user profile ntuser.dat file(s): 'Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Office\\16.0\\common\\toolbars\\PowerPoint\\noextensibilitycustomizationfromdocument'.  Existence requirement is 'all_exist' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n                :            For 'MAXHEALTH\\katessem.admin':  Registry Name Not found in user profile ntuser.dat file(s): 'Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Office\\16.0\\common\\toolbars\\PowerPoint\\noextensibilitycustomizationfromdocument'.  \n                :            For 'MAXHEALTH\\katessem':  Registry Name Not found in user profile ntuser.dat file(s): 'Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Office\\16.0\\common\\toolbars\\PowerPoint\\noextensibilitycustomizationfromdocument'.  \n                :            For 'MHL-PW06M2V2\\Administrator':  Registry Name Not found in user profile ntuser.dat file(s): 'Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Office\\16.0\\common\\toolbars\\PowerPoint\\noextensibilitycustomizationfromdocument'.  \nCriteria        :       false (All child tests must be true. (AND)) (negated)\nTest            :         true (MS PowerPoint is installed.)\nCriteria        :     true (One or more child tests must be true. (OR))\nTest            :       false (Disable UI extending from documents and templates is set to 'Enabled' for Project)\nResult Analysis :            Registry Name Not found in user profile ntuser.dat file(s): 'Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Office\\16.0\\common\\toolbars\\Project\\noextensibilitycustomizationfromdocument'.  Existence requirement is 'all_exist' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n                :            For 'MAXHEALTH\\katessem.admin':  Registry Name Not found in user profile ntuser.dat file(s): 'Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Office\\16.0\\common\\toolbars\\Project\\noextensibilitycustomizationfromdocument'.  \n                :            For 'MAXHEALTH\\katessem':  Registry Name Not found in user profile ntuser.dat file(s): 'Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Office\\16.0\\common\\toolbars\\Project\\noextensibilitycustomizationfromdocument'.  \n                :            For 'MHL-PW06M2V2\\Administrator':  Registry Name Not found in user profile ntuser.dat file(s): 'Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Office\\16.0\\common\\toolbars\\Project\\noextensibilitycustomizationfromdocument'.  \nCriteria        :       true (All child tests must be true. (AND)) (negated)\nTest            :         false (MS Project is installed.)\nResult Analysis :              Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\nCriteria        :     false (One or more child tests must be true. (OR))\nTest            :       false (Disable UI extending from documents and templates is set to 'Enabled' for Publisher)\nResult Analysis :            Registry Name Not found in user profile ntuser.dat file(s): 'Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Office\\16.0\\common\\toolbars\\Publisher\\noextensibilitycustomizationfromdocument'.  Existence requirement is 'all_exist' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n                :            For 'MAXHEALTH\\katessem.admin':  Registry Name Not found in user profile ntuser.dat file(s): 'Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Office\\16.0\\common\\toolbars\\Publisher\\noextensibilitycustomizationfromdocument'.  \n                :            For 'MAXHEALTH\\katessem':  Registry Name Not found in user profile ntuser.dat file(s): 'Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Office\\16.0\\common\\toolbars\\Publisher\\noextensibilitycustomizationfromdocument'.  \n                :            For 'MHL-PW06M2V2\\Administrator':  Registry Name Not found in user profile ntuser.dat file(s): 'Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Office\\16.0\\common\\toolbars\\Publisher\\noextensibilitycustomizationfromdocument'.  \nCriteria        :       false (All child tests must be true. (AND)) (negated)\nTest            :         true (MS Publisher is installed.)\nCriteria        :     true (One or more child tests must be true. (OR))\nTest            :       false (Disable UI extending from documents and templates is set to 'Enabled' for Visio)\nResult Analysis :            Registry Name Not found in user profile ntuser.dat file(s): 'Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Office\\16.0\\common\\toolbars\\Visio\\noextensibilitycustomizationfromdocument'.  Existence requirement is 'all_exist' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n                :            For 'MAXHEALTH\\katessem.admin':  Registry Name Not found in user profile ntuser.dat file(s): 'Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Office\\16.0\\common\\toolbars\\Visio\\noextensibilitycustomizationfromdocument'.  \n                :            For 'MAXHEALTH\\katessem':  Registry Name Not found in user profile ntuser.dat file(s): 'Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Office\\16.0\\common\\toolbars\\Visio\\noextensibilitycustomizationfromdocument'.  \n                :            For 'MHL-PW06M2V2\\Administrator':  Registry Name Not found in user profile ntuser.dat file(s): 'Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Office\\16.0\\common\\toolbars\\Visio\\noextensibilitycustomizationfromdocument'.  \nCriteria        :       true (All child tests must be true. (AND)) (negated)\nTest            :         false (MS Visio is installed.)\nResult Analysis :              Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\nCriteria        :     false (One or more child tests must be true. (OR))\nTest            :       false (Disable UI extending from documents and templates is set to 'Enabled' for Word)\nResult Analysis :            Registry Name Not found in user profile ntuser.dat file(s): 'Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Office\\16.0\\common\\toolbars\\Word\\noextensibilitycustomizationfromdocument'.  Existence requirement is 'all_exist' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n                :            For 'MAXHEALTH\\katessem.admin':  Registry Name Not found in user profile ntuser.dat file(s): 'Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Office\\16.0\\common\\toolbars\\Word\\noextensibilitycustomizationfromdocument'.  \n                :            For 'MAXHEALTH\\katessem':  Registry Name Not found in user profile ntuser.dat file(s): 'Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Office\\16.0\\common\\toolbars\\Word\\noextensibilitycustomizationfromdocument'.  \n                :            For 'MHL-PW06M2V2\\Administrator':  Registry Name Not found in user profile ntuser.dat file(s): 'Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Office\\16.0\\common\\toolbars\\Word\\noextensibilitycustomizationfromdocument'.  \nCriteria        :       false (All child tests must be true. (AND)) (negated)\nTest            :         true (MS Word is installed.)\n"},{"security_override_guidance":"","group_title":"SRG-APP-000488","third_party_tools":"","rule_title":"ActiveX Controls must be initialized in Safe Mode.","rule_id":"SV-223288r961779","weight":"10.0","stig_uuid":"B3EF3B6E-722B-1014-942B-D54B65175630","ccis":["CCI-002460"],"ia_controls":"","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000488","id":"V-223288"},"group_id":"V-223288","mitigations":"","documentable":"false","fix_text":"Set the policy value for User Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Microsoft Office 2016 &gt;&gt; Security Settings \"ActiveX Control Initialization\" to \"Enabled + 6\".","rule_id_src":"SV-223288r961779_rule","status":"open","group_id_src":"V-223288","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.office365:def:223288","href":"U_MS_Office_365_ProPlus_V3R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV9-oval.xml"},"reference_identifier":"4099","classification":"Unclassified","potential_impacts":"","severity":"medium","responsibility":"","comments":null,"rule_version":"O365-CO-000005","check_content":"Verify the policy value for User Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Microsoft Office 2016 &gt;&gt; Security Settings \"ActiveX Control Initialization\" is set to \"Enabled (If SFI, load the control in safe mode and use persisted values (if any). If not SFI, prompt the user and advise them that it is marked unsafe. If the user chooses No at the prompt, do not load the control. Otherwise, load it with persisted values.)\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \n\nHKCU\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Office\\Common\\Security\n\nIf the value UFIControls is set to REG_DWORD=6, this is not a finding.","false_positives":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-108753","V-99649"],"uuid":"B4021B91-722B-1014-B400-B367A21FEC67","discussion":"This policy setting specifies the Microsoft ActiveX initialization security level for all Microsoft Office applications. ActiveX controls can adversely affect a computer directly. In addition, malicious code can be used to compromise an ActiveX control and attack a computer. \n\nTo indicate the safety of an ActiveX control, developers can denote them as Safe for Initialization (SFI). SFI indicates that a control is safe to open and run, and that it is not capable of causing a problem for any computer, regardless of whether it has persisted data values or not. If a control is not marked SFI, it is possible that the control could adversely affect a computer--or it could mean that the developers did not test the control in all situations and are not sure whether it might be compromised in the future. If you enable this policy setting, you can set the ActiveX security level to a number between 1 and 6. These security levels are as follows:\n \n1. Regardless of how the control is marked, load it and use the persisted values (if any). This setting does not prompt the user. \n\n2. If SFI, load the control in safe mode and use persisted values (if any). If not SFI, load in unsafe mode with persisted values (if any), or use the default (first-time initialization) settings. This level is similar to the default configuration, but does not prompt the user. \n\n3. If SFI, load the control in unsafe mode and use persisted values (if any). If not SFI, prompt the user and advise them that it is marked unsafe. If the user chooses No at the prompt, do not load the control. Otherwise, load it with default (first-time initialization) settings. \n\n4. If SFI, load the control in safe mode and use persisted values (if any). If not SFI, prompt the user and advise them that it is marked unsafe. If the user chooses No at the prompt, do not load the control. Otherwise, load it with default (first-time initialization) settings. \n\n5. If SFI, load the control in unsafe mode and use persisted values (if any). If not SFI, prompt the user and advise them that it is marked unsafe. If the user chooses No at the prompt, do not load the control. Otherwise, load it with persisted values. \n\n6. If SFI, load the control in safe mode and use persisted values (if any). If not SFI, prompt the user and advise them that it is marked unsafe. If the user chooses No at the prompt, do not load the control. Otherwise, load it with persisted values. \n\nIf you disable or do not configure this policy setting, if a control is marked SFI, the application loads the control in safe mode and uses persisted values (if any). If the control is not marked SFI, the application loads the control in unsafe mode with persisted values (if any), or uses the default (first-time initialization) settings. In both situations, the Message Bar informs users that the controls have been disabled and prompts them to respond. \n\nImportant: Some ActiveX controls do not respect the safe mode registry setting, and therefore might load persisted data even though you configure this setting to instruct the control to use safe mode. This setting only increases security for ActiveX controls that are accurately marked as SFI. In situations that involve malicious or poorly designed code, an ActiveX control might be inaccurately marked as SFI.","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-04-01T11:55:55\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :   false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :     false (ActiveX Control Initialization is enabled and set to use SFI or to prompt the user.)\nResult Analysis :          Registry Name Not found in user profile ntuser.dat file(s): 'Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Office\\common\\security\\uficontrols'.  Existence requirement is 'all_exist' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n                :          For 'MAXHEALTH\\katessem.admin':  Registry Name Not found in user profile ntuser.dat file(s): 'Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Office\\common\\security\\uficontrols'.  \n                :          For 'MAXHEALTH\\katessem':  Registry Name Not found in user profile ntuser.dat file(s): 'Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Office\\common\\security\\uficontrols'.  \n                :          For 'MHL-PW06M2V2\\Administrator':  Registry Name Not found in user profile ntuser.dat file(s): 'Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Office\\common\\security\\uficontrols'.  \n"},{"security_override_guidance":"","group_title":"SRG-APP-000210","third_party_tools":"","rule_title":"Macros in all Office applications that are opened programmatically by another application must be opened based upon macro security level.","rule_id":"SV-223289r961092","weight":"10.0","stig_uuid":"B3EF3B6E-722B-1014-942B-D54B65175630","ccis":["CCI-001170"],"ia_controls":"","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000210","id":"V-223289"},"group_id":"V-223289","mitigations":"","documentable":"false","fix_text":"Set the policy value for User Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Microsoft Office 2016 &gt;&gt; Security Settings \"Automation Security\" to \"Enabled (Use application macro security level)\".","rule_id_src":"SV-223289r961092_rule","status":"open","group_id_src":"V-223289","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.office365:def:223289","href":"U_MS_Office_365_ProPlus_V3R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV9-oval.xml"},"reference_identifier":"4099","classification":"Unclassified","potential_impacts":"","severity":"medium","responsibility":"","comments":null,"rule_version":"O365-CO-000006","check_content":"Verify the policy value for User Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Microsoft Office 2016 &gt;&gt; Security Settings \"Automation Security\" is set to \"Enabled (Use application macro security level)\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\n\nHKCU\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Office\\Common\\Security\n\nIf the value AutomationSecurity is REG_DWORD = 2, this is not a finding.","false_positives":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-108755","V-99651"],"uuid":"B40221CF-722B-1014-8464-DBB228083894","discussion":"This policy setting controls whether macros can run in an Office 365 ProPlus application that is opened programmatically by another application. If this policy setting is enabled, the user can choose from three options for controlling macro behavior in Excel, PowerPoint, and Word when the application is opened programmatically:\n\n- Disable macros by default Â¬- all macros are disabled in the programmatically opened application. \n- Macros enabled (default) - macros can run in the programmatically opened application. This option enforces the default configuration in Excel, PowerPoint, and Word. \n- User application macro security level - macro functionality is determined by the setting in the \"Macro Settings\" section of the Trust Center. \n\nIf this policy setting is disabled or not configured, when a separate program is used to launch Microsoft Excel, PowerPoint, or Word programmatically, any macros can run in the programmatically opened application without being blocked.","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-04-01T11:55:55\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :   false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :     false (Macros in all Office applications that are opened programmatically by another application are opened based upon macro security level)\nResult Analysis :          Registry Name Not found in user profile ntuser.dat file(s): 'Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Office\\common\\security\\automationsecurity'.  Existence requirement is 'all_exist' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n                :          For 'MAXHEALTH\\katessem.admin':  Registry Name Not found in user profile ntuser.dat file(s): 'Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Office\\common\\security\\automationsecurity'.  \n                :          For 'MAXHEALTH\\katessem':  Registry Name Not found in user profile ntuser.dat file(s): 'Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Office\\common\\security\\automationsecurity'.  \n                :          For 'MHL-PW06M2V2\\Administrator':  Registry Name Not found in user profile ntuser.dat file(s): 'Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Office\\common\\security\\automationsecurity'.  \n"},{"security_override_guidance":"","group_title":"SRG-APP-000131","third_party_tools":"","rule_title":"Trust Bar notifications must be configured to display information in the Message Bar about the content that has been automatically blocked.","rule_id":"SV-223290r1016167","weight":"10.0","stig_uuid":"B3EF3B6E-722B-1014-942B-D54B65175630","ccis":["CCI-003992","CCI-001749"],"ia_controls":"","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000131","id":"V-223290"},"group_id":"V-223290","mitigations":"","documentable":"false","fix_text":"Set the policy value for User Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Microsoft Office 2016 &gt;&gt; Security Settings \"Disable all Trust Bar notifications for security issues\" to \"Disabled\".","rule_id_src":"SV-223290r1016167_rule","status":"open","group_id_src":"V-223290","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.office365:def:223290","href":"U_MS_Office_365_ProPlus_V3R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV9-oval.xml"},"reference_identifier":"4099","classification":"Unclassified","potential_impacts":"","severity":"medium","responsibility":"","comments":null,"rule_version":"O365-CO-000007","check_content":"Verify the policy value for User Configuration &gt;&gt; Microsoft Office 2016 &gt;&gt; Security Settings &gt;&gt; Disable all Trust Bar notifications for security issues is set to \"Disabled\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\n\nHKCU\\software\\policies\\microsoft\\office\\16.0\\common\\trustcenter\n\nIf the value trustbar is REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.","false_positives":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-108757","V-99653"],"uuid":"B40227B3-722B-1014-8963-958F522316CC","discussion":"This policy setting controls whether Office 365 ProPlus applications notify users when potentially unsafe features or content are detected, or whether such features or content are silently disabled without notification. \n\nThe Message Bar in Office 365 ProPlus applications is used to identify security issues, such as unsigned macros or potentially unsafe add-ins. When such issues are detected, the application disables the unsafe feature or content and displays the Message Bar at the top of the active window. The Message Bar informs the users about the nature of the security issue and, in some cases, provides the users with an option to enable the potentially unsafe feature or content, which could harm the user's computer. \n\nIf this policy setting is enabled, Office 365 ProPlus applications do not display information in the Message Bar about potentially unsafe content that has been detected or has automatically been blocked.","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-04-01T11:55:55\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :   false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :     false (Trust Bar notifications are configured to display information in the Message Bar about the content that has been automatically blocked.)\nResult Analysis :          Registry Name Not found in user profile ntuser.dat file(s): 'Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Office\\16.0\\common\\trustcenter\\trustbar'.  Existence requirement is 'all_exist' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n                :          For 'MAXHEALTH\\katessem.admin':  Registry Name Not found in user profile ntuser.dat file(s): 'Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Office\\16.0\\common\\trustcenter\\trustbar'.  \n                :          For 'MAXHEALTH\\katessem':  Registry Name Not found in user profile ntuser.dat file(s): 'Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Office\\16.0\\common\\trustcenter\\trustbar'.  \n                :          For 'MHL-PW06M2V2\\Administrator':  Registry Name Not found in user profile ntuser.dat file(s): 'Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Office\\16.0\\common\\trustcenter\\trustbar'.  \n"},{"security_override_guidance":"","group_title":"SRG-APP-000231","third_party_tools":"","rule_title":"Office applications must be configured to specify encryption type in password-protected Office 97-2003 files.","rule_id":"SV-223291r961128","weight":"10.0","stig_uuid":"B3EF3B6E-722B-1014-942B-D54B65175630","ccis":["CCI-001199"],"ia_controls":"","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000231","id":"V-223291"},"group_id":"V-223291","mitigations":"","documentable":"false","fix_text":"Set the policy value for User Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Microsoft Office 2016 &gt;&gt; Security Settings &gt;&gt; Encryption type for password protected Office 97-2003 files to Microsoft Enhanced RSA and AES Cryptographic Provider,AES 256,256.","rule_id_src":"SV-223291r961128_rule","status":"open","group_id_src":"V-223291","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.office365:def:223291","href":"U_MS_Office_365_ProPlus_V3R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV9-oval.xml"},"reference_identifier":"4099","classification":"Unclassified","potential_impacts":"","severity":"medium","responsibility":"","comments":null,"rule_version":"O365-CO-000008","check_content":"Verify the policy value for User Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Microsoft Office 2016 &gt;&gt; Security Settings &gt;&gt; Encryption type for password protected Office 97-2003 files is set to Microsoft Enhanced RSA and AES Cryptographic Provider,AES 256,256.\n \nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\n\nHKCU\\software\\policies\\microsoft\\office\\16.0\\common\\security\n\nIf the value defaultencryption12 is set to REG_SZ = \"Microsoft Enhanced RSA and AES Cryptographic Provider,AES 256,256\", this is not a finding.","false_positives":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-108759","V-99655"],"uuid":"B4022D36-722B-1014-9F54-A48682606A28","discussion":"This policy setting enables you to specify an encryption type for password-protected Office 97-2003 files.\n\nIf you enable this policy setting, you can specify the type of encryption that Office applications will use to encrypt password-protected files in the older Office 97-2003 file formats. The chosen encryption type must have a corresponding cryptographic service provider (CSP) installed on the computer that encrypts the file. See the HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Cryptography\\Defaults\\Provider\\ registry key for a list of CSPs installed on the local computer. Specify the encryption type to use by entering it in the provided text box in the following form:\n\n&lt;Encryption Provider&gt;,&lt;Encryption Algorithm&gt;,&lt;Encryption Key Length&gt;.\nFor example, Microsoft Enhanced Cryptographic Provider v1.0,RC4,128\n\nIf you do not configure this policy setting, Excel, PowerPoint, and Word use Office 97/2000 Compatible encryption, a proprietary encryption method, to encrypt password-protected Office 97-2003 files.","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-04-01T11:55:55\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :   false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :     false (Encryption type for password protected Office 97-2003 files is set to 'Microsoft Enhanced RSA and AES Cryptographic Provider,AES 256,256')\nResult Analysis :          Registry Name Not found in user profile ntuser.dat file(s): 'Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Office\\16.0\\common\\security\\defaultencryption12'.  Existence requirement is 'all_exist' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n                :          For 'MAXHEALTH\\katessem.admin':  Registry Name Not found in user profile ntuser.dat file(s): 'Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Office\\16.0\\common\\security\\defaultencryption12'.  \n                :          For 'MAXHEALTH\\katessem':  Registry Name Not found in user profile ntuser.dat file(s): 'Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Office\\16.0\\common\\security\\defaultencryption12'.  \n                :          For 'MHL-PW06M2V2\\Administrator':  Registry Name Not found in user profile ntuser.dat file(s): 'Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Office\\16.0\\common\\security\\defaultencryption12'.  \n"},{"security_override_guidance":"","group_title":"SRG-APP-000231","third_party_tools":"","rule_title":"Office applications must be configured to specify encryption type in password-protected Office Open XML files.","rule_id":"SV-223292r961128","weight":"10.0","stig_uuid":"B3EF3B6E-722B-1014-942B-D54B65175630","ccis":["CCI-001199"],"ia_controls":"","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000231","id":"V-223292"},"group_id":"V-223292","mitigations":"","documentable":"false","fix_text":"Set the policy value for User Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Microsoft Office 2016 &gt;&gt; Security Settings &gt;&gt; Encryption type for password protected Office Open XML files to Microsoft Enhanced RSA and AES Cryptographic Provider,AES 256,256.","rule_id_src":"SV-223292r961128_rule","status":"open","group_id_src":"V-223292","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.office365:def:223292","href":"U_MS_Office_365_ProPlus_V3R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV9-oval.xml"},"reference_identifier":"4099","classification":"Unclassified","potential_impacts":"","severity":"medium","responsibility":"","comments":null,"rule_version":"O365-CO-000009","check_content":"Verify the policy value for User Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Microsoft Office 2016 &gt;&gt; Security Settings &gt;&gt; Encryption type for password protected Office Open XML files is set to Microsoft Enhanced RSA and AES Cryptographic Provider,AES 256,256.\n \nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\n\nHKCU\\software\\policies\\microsoft\\office\\16.0\\common\\security\n\nIf the value OpenXMLEncryption is REG_SZ = \"Microsoft Enhanced RSA and AES Cryptographic Provider,AES 256,256\", this is not a finding.","false_positives":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-108761","V-99657"],"uuid":"B4023360-722B-1014-9865-C55D4B3FD494","discussion":"This policy setting allows you to specify an encryption type for Office Open XML files.\n\nIf you enable this policy setting, you can specify the type of encryption that Office applications use to encrypt password-protected files in the Office Open XML file formats used by Excel, PowerPoint, and Word. The chosen encryption type must have a corresponding cryptographic service provider (CSP) installed on the computer that encrypts the file. See the HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Cryptography\\Defaults\\Provider\\ registry key for a list of CSPs installed on the local computer. Specify the encryption type to use by entering it in the provided text box in the following form:\n\n&lt;Encryption Provider&gt;,&lt;Encryption Algorithm&gt;,&lt;Encryption Key Length&gt;\n\nFor example: Microsoft Enhanced Cryptographic Provider v1.0,RC4,128\n\nIf you disable or do not configure this policy setting, the default CSP is used. The default cryptographic service provider (CSP) is Microsoft Enhanced RSA and AES Cryptographic Provider, AES-128, 128-bit.\n\nNote: This policy setting does not take effect unless the registry key \nHKEY_CURRENT_USER\\Software\\Microsoft\\Office\\16.0\\&lt;office application name&gt;\\Security\\Crypto\\CompatMode is set to 0. By default the CompatMode registry key is set to 1.","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-04-01T11:55:55\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :   false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :     false (Encryption type for password protected Office Open XML files is enabled and set to Microsoft Enhanced RSA and AES Cryptographic Provider,AES 256,256.)\nResult Analysis :          Registry Name Not found in user profile ntuser.dat file(s): 'Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Office\\16.0\\common\\security\\OpenXMLEncryption'.  Existence requirement is 'all_exist' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n                :          For 'MAXHEALTH\\katessem.admin':  Registry Name Not found in user profile ntuser.dat file(s): 'Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Office\\16.0\\common\\security\\OpenXMLEncryption'.  \n                :          For 'MAXHEALTH\\katessem':  Registry Name Not found in user profile ntuser.dat file(s): 'Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Office\\16.0\\common\\security\\OpenXMLEncryption'.  \n                :          For 'MHL-PW06M2V2\\Administrator':  Registry Name Not found in user profile ntuser.dat file(s): 'Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Office\\16.0\\common\\security\\OpenXMLEncryption'.  \n"},{"security_override_guidance":"","group_title":"SRG-APP-000340","third_party_tools":"","rule_title":"Users must be prevented from creating new trusted locations in the Trust Center.","rule_id":"SV-223293r961353","weight":"10.0","stig_uuid":"B3EF3B6E-722B-1014-942B-D54B65175630","ccis":["CCI-002235"],"ia_controls":"","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000340","id":"V-223293"},"group_id":"V-223293","mitigations":"","documentable":"false","fix_text":"Set the policy value for User Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Microsoft Office 2016 &gt;&gt; Security Settings &gt;&gt; Trust Center &gt;&gt; Allow mix of policy and user locations to \"Disabled\".","rule_id_src":"SV-223293r961353_rule","status":"open","group_id_src":"V-223293","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.office365:def:223293","href":"U_MS_Office_365_ProPlus_V3R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV9-oval.xml"},"reference_identifier":"4099","classification":"Unclassified","potential_impacts":"","severity":"medium","responsibility":"","comments":null,"rule_version":"O365-CO-000010","check_content":"Verify the policy value for User Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Microsoft Office 2016\\Security Settings\\Trust Center &gt;&gt; Allow mix of policy and user locations is set to \"Disabled\".\n \nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \n\nHKCU\\software\\policies\\microsoft\\office\\16.0\\common\\security\\trusted locations\n\nIf the value for allow user locations is set to REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.","false_positives":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-108763","V-99659"],"uuid":"B4023888-722B-1014-BF76-C0E29B061FD2","discussion":"This policy setting controls whether trusted locations can be defined by users, the Office Customization Tool (OCT), and Group Policy, or if they must be defined by Group Policy alone.\n\nIf you enable this policy setting, users can specify any location as a trusted location, and a computer can have a combination of user-created, OCT-created, and Group Policy-created trusted locations.\n\nIf you disable this policy setting, all trusted locations that are not created by Group Policy are disabled and users cannot create new trusted locations in the Trust Center.\n\nIf you do not configure this policy setting, the behavior is the equivalent of setting the policy to Enabled.\n\nNote: InfoPath and Outlook do not recognize trusted locations, and therefore are unaffected by this policy setting.","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-04-01T11:55:55\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :   false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :     false (Users are prevented from creating new trusted locations in the Trust Center.)\nResult Analysis :          Registry Name Not found in user profile ntuser.dat file(s): 'Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\office\\16.0\\common\\security\\trusted locations\\allow user locations'.  Existence requirement is 'all_exist' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n                :          For 'MAXHEALTH\\katessem.admin':  Registry Name Not found in user profile ntuser.dat file(s): 'Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\office\\16.0\\common\\security\\trusted locations\\allow user locations'.  \n                :          For 'MAXHEALTH\\katessem':  Registry Name Not found in user profile ntuser.dat file(s): 'Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\office\\16.0\\common\\security\\trusted locations\\allow user locations'.  \n                :          For 'MHL-PW06M2V2\\Administrator':  Registry Name Not found in user profile ntuser.dat file(s): 'Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\office\\16.0\\common\\security\\trusted locations\\allow user locations'.  \n"},{"security_override_guidance":"","group_title":"SRG-APP-000516","third_party_tools":"","rule_title":"Office applications must not load XML expansion packs with Smart Documents.","rule_id":"SV-223294r961863","weight":"10.0","stig_uuid":"B3EF3B6E-722B-1014-942B-D54B65175630","ccis":["CCI-000366"],"ia_controls":"","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000516","id":"V-223294"},"group_id":"V-223294","mitigations":"","documentable":"false","fix_text":"Set the policy value for User Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Microsoft Office 2016 &gt;&gt; Smart Documents (Word, Excel) &gt;&gt; Disable Smart Document's use of manifests to \"Enabled\".","rule_id_src":"SV-223294r961863_rule","status":"open","group_id_src":"V-223294","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.office365:def:223294","href":"U_MS_Office_365_ProPlus_V3R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV9-oval.xml"},"reference_identifier":"4099","classification":"Unclassified","potential_impacts":"","severity":"medium","responsibility":"","comments":null,"rule_version":"O365-CO-000012","check_content":"Verify the policy value for User Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Microsoft Office 2016 &gt;&gt; Smart Documents (Word, Excel) &gt;&gt; Disable Smart Document's use of manifests is set to \"Enabled\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\n\nHKCU\\software\\policies\\microsoft\\office\\common\\smart tag\n\nIf the value for neverloadmanifests is REG_DWORD = 1, this is not a finding.","false_positives":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-108767","V-99663"],"uuid":"B4023E79-722B-1014-8AA5-9F24168DC80A","discussion":"This policy setting controls whether Office 365 ProPlus applications can load an XML expansion pack manifest file with a Smart Document.","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-04-01T11:55:55\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :   false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :     false (Office applications do not load XML expansion packs with Smart Documents.)\nResult Analysis :          Registry Name Not found in user profile ntuser.dat file(s): 'Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Office\\common\\smart tag\\neverloadmanifests'.  Existence requirement is 'all_exist' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n                :          For 'MAXHEALTH\\katessem.admin':  Registry Name Not found in user profile ntuser.dat file(s): 'Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Office\\common\\smart tag\\neverloadmanifests'.  \n                :          For 'MAXHEALTH\\katessem':  Registry Name Not found in user profile ntuser.dat file(s): 'Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Office\\common\\smart tag\\neverloadmanifests'.  \n                :          For 'MHL-PW06M2V2\\Administrator':  Registry Name Not found in user profile ntuser.dat file(s): 'Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Office\\common\\smart tag\\neverloadmanifests'.  \n"},{"security_override_guidance":"","group_title":"SRG-APP-000207","third_party_tools":"","rule_title":"The load of controls in Forms3 must be blocked.","rule_id":"SV-223295r961086","weight":"10.0","stig_uuid":"B3EF3B6E-722B-1014-942B-D54B65175630","ccis":["CCI-001662"],"ia_controls":"","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000207","id":"V-223295"},"group_id":"V-223295","mitigations":"","documentable":"false","fix_text":"Set the policy value for User Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Microsoft Office 2016 &gt;&gt; Security Settings \"Load Controls in Forms3\" to \"Enabled:1\" or set it to \"Disabled.\"   ","rule_id_src":"SV-223295r961086_rule","status":"not_a_finding","group_id_src":"V-223295","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.office365:def:223295","href":"U_MS_Office_365_ProPlus_V3R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV9-oval.xml"},"reference_identifier":"4099","classification":"Unclassified","potential_impacts":"","severity":"medium","responsibility":"","comments":null,"rule_version":"O365-CO-000013","check_content":"Verify the policy value for User Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Microsoft Office 2016 &gt;&gt; Security Settings \"Load Controls in Forms3\" is set to Enabled and 1 from drop down. (For a UFI or SFI signed control that supports safe and unsafe mode, load the control in unsafe mode. For an SFI signed control that only supports a safe mode configuration, load the control in safe mode. This option enforces the default configuration.)\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\n\nHKCU\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\VBA\\Security\n\nIf the value LoadControlsInForms is REG_DWORD=1, this is not a finding.\n\nIf the value LoadControlsInForms does not exist, this is not a finding.","false_positives":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-108769","V-99665"],"uuid":"B402441E-722B-1014-825D-8AECE2D7B887","discussion":"This policy setting allows the user to control how ActiveX controls in UserForms should be initialized based upon whether they are Safe for Initialization (SFI) or Unsafe for Initialization (UFI). \n \nActiveX controls are Component Object Model (COM) objects and have unrestricted access to users' computers. ActiveX controls can access the local file system and change the registry settings of the operating system. If a malicious user repurposes an ActiveX control to take over a user's computer, the effect could be significant. To help improve security, ActiveX developers can mark controls as SFI, which means that the developer states that the controls are safe to open and run and not capable of causing harm to any computers. If a control is not marked SFI, the control could adversely affect a computer, or the developers may not have tested the control in all situations and are not sure whether their control might be compromised at some future date. SFI controls run in safe mode, which limits their access to the computer. For example, a worksheet control can both read and write files when it is in unsafe mode, but perhaps only read from files when it is in safe mode. This functionality allows the control to be used in very powerful ways when safety was not important, but the control would still be safe for use in a Web page. If a control is not marked as SFI, it is marked UFI, which means that it is capable of affecting a user's computer. If UFI ActiveX controls are loaded, they are always loaded in unsafe mode. \n \nIf this policy setting is enabled, choose from four options for loading controls in UserForms: \n \n1. For a UFI or SFI signed control that supports safe and unsafe mode, load the control in unsafe mode. For an SFI signed control that only supports a safe mode configuration, load the control in safe mode. This option enforces the default configuration. \n \n2. Users are prompted to determine how UserForm forms will load. The prompt only displays once per session within an application. When users respond to the prompt, loading continues based on whether the control is UFI or SFI: \n \n- For a UFI signed control, if users respond \"Yes\" to the prompt, load the control in unsafe mode. If users respond \"No\", load the control using the default properties. \n- For an SFI signed control that supports both safe and unsafe modes, if users respond \"Yes\" to the prompt, load the control in unsafe mode. If users respond \"No\", load the control using safe mode. If the SFI control can only support safe mode, load the control in safe mode. This option is the default configuration in the Microsoft Office 365 ProPlus release. \n \n3. Users are prompted to determine how UserForm forms will load. The prompt only displays once per session within an application. When users respond to the prompt, loading continues based on whether the control is UFI or SFI: \n \n- For a UFI signed control, if users respond \"Yes\" to the prompt, load the control in unsafe mode. If users respond \"No\", load the control with its default properties. \n- For an SFI signed control, load in safe mode. \n \n4. For a UFI signed control, load with the default properties of the control. For an SFI signed control, load in safe mode (considered to be the safest mode). \n \nIf  this policy setting is disabled or not configured, the behavior is as if this policy setting is enabled and then select option \"1\".","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-04-01T11:55:55\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :   true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :     true (Check to see if 'Load Controls in Forms3' is enabled and set to 1)\n"},{"security_override_guidance":"","group_title":"SRG-APP-000207","third_party_tools":"","rule_title":"Add-on Management must be enabled for all Office 365 ProPlus programs.","rule_id":"SV-223296r961086","weight":"10.0","stig_uuid":"B3EF3B6E-722B-1014-942B-D54B65175630","ccis":["CCI-001662"],"ia_controls":"","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000207","id":"V-223296"},"group_id":"V-223296","mitigations":"","documentable":"false","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Microsoft Office 2016 (Machine) &gt;&gt; Security Settings &gt;&gt; IE Security \"Add-on Management\" to \"Enabled\" and select the check boxes for  all installed Office programs.","rule_id_src":"SV-223296r961086_rule","status":"open","group_id_src":"V-223296","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.office365:def:223296","href":"U_MS_Office_365_ProPlus_V3R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV9-oval.xml"},"reference_identifier":"4099","classification":"Unclassified","potential_impacts":"","severity":"medium","responsibility":"","comments":null,"rule_version":"O365-CO-000014","check_content":"Verify the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Microsoft Office 2016 (Machine) &gt;&gt; Security Settings &gt;&gt; IE Security \"Add-on Management\" is set to \"Enabled\" and the check box is selected for every installed Office program.\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\n\nHKLM\\Software\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_ADDON_MANAGEMENT\n\nIf the value for each installed Office Program is REG_DWORD = 1, this is not a finding.","false_positives":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-108771","V-99667"],"uuid":"B40249E0-722B-1014-8018-9B3A2A7BDD08","discussion":"Internet Explorer add-ons are pieces of code, run in Internet Explorer, to provide additional functionality. Rogue add-ons may contain viruses or other malicious code. Disabling or not configuring this setting could allow malicious code or users to become active on user computers or the network. For example, a malicious user can monitor and then use keystrokes that user's type into Internet Explorer. Even legitimate add-ons may demand resources, compromising the performance of Internet Explorer and the operating systems for user computers.","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-04-01T11:55:55\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :   false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :     true (One or more child tests must be true. (OR))\nTest            :       false (IE Security 'Add-on Management' is set to 'Enabled' and the check box is selected for Access)\nResult Analysis :            Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_ADDON_MANAGEMENT\\msaccess.exe'.  Existence requirement is 'all_exist' and no items were collected, so result is false.\nCriteria        :       true (All child tests must be true. (AND)) (negated)\nTest            :         false (MS Access is installed.)\nResult Analysis :              Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\nCriteria        :     false (One or more child tests must be true. (OR))\nTest            :       false (IE Security 'Add-on Management' is set to 'Enabled' and the check box is selected for Excel)\nResult Analysis :            Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_ADDON_MANAGEMENT\\excel.exe'.  Existence requirement is 'all_exist' and no items were collected, so result is false.\nCriteria        :       false (All child tests must be true. (AND)) (negated)\nTest            :         true (MS Excel is installed.)\nCriteria        :     true (One or more child tests must be true. (OR))\nTest            :       false (IE Security 'Add-on Management' is set to 'Enabled' and the check box is selected for Groove and OneDrive)\nResult Analysis :            Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_ADDON_MANAGEMENT\\groove.exe'.  Existence requirement is 'all_exist' and no items were collected, so result is false.\nCriteria        :       true (All child tests must be true. (AND)) (negated)\nTest            :         false (Microsoft OneDrive for Business 2016 is installed)\nResult Analysis :              Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\nCriteria        :     false (One or more child tests must be true. (OR))\nTest            :       false (IE Security 'Add-on Management' is set to 'Enabled' and the check box is selected for Outlook)\nResult Analysis :            Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_ADDON_MANAGEMENT\\outlook.exe'.  Existence requirement is 'all_exist' and no items were collected, so result is false.\nCriteria        :       false (All child tests must be true. (AND)) (negated)\nTest            :         true (MS Outlook is installed.)\nCriteria        :     false (One or more child tests must be true. (OR))\nTest            :       false (IE Security 'Add-on Management' is set to 'Enabled' and the check box is selected for PowerPoint)\nResult Analysis :            Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_ADDON_MANAGEMENT\\powerpnt.exe'.  Existence requirement is 'all_exist' and no items were collected, so result is false.\nCriteria        :       false (All child tests must be true. (AND)) (negated)\nTest            :         true (MS PowerPoint is installed.)\nCriteria        :     true (One or more child tests must be true. (OR))\nTest            :       false (IE Security 'Add-on Management' is set to 'Enabled' and the check box is selected for Project)\nResult Analysis :            Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_ADDON_MANAGEMENT\\winproj.exe'.  Existence requirement is 'all_exist' and no items were collected, so result is false.\nCriteria        :       true (All child tests must be true. (AND)) (negated)\nTest            :         false (MS Project is installed.)\nResult Analysis :              Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\nCriteria        :     false (One or more child tests must be true. (OR))\nTest            :       false (IE Security 'Add-on Management' is set to 'Enabled' and the check box is selected for Publisher)\nResult Analysis :            Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_ADDON_MANAGEMENT\\mspub.exe'.  Existence requirement is 'all_exist' and no items were collected, so result is false.\nCriteria        :       false (All child tests must be true. (AND)) (negated)\nTest            :         true (MS Publisher is installed.)\nCriteria        :     true (One or more child tests must be true. (OR))\nTest            :       false (IE Security 'Add-on Management' is set to 'Enabled' and the check box is selected for Visio)\nResult Analysis :            Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_ADDON_MANAGEMENT\\visio.exe'.  Existence requirement is 'all_exist' and no items were collected, so result is false.\nCriteria        :       true (All child tests must be true. (AND)) (negated)\nTest            :         false (MS Visio is installed.)\nResult Analysis :              Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\nCriteria        :     false (One or more child tests must be true. (OR))\nTest            :       false (IE Security 'Add-on Management' is set to 'Enabled' and the check box is selected for Word)\nResult Analysis :            Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_ADDON_MANAGEMENT\\winword.exe'.  Existence requirement is 'all_exist' and no items were collected, so result is false.\nCriteria        :       false (All child tests must be true. (AND)) (negated)\nTest            :         true (MS Word is installed.)\nCriteria        :     false (One or more child tests must be true. (OR))\nTest            :       false (IE Security 'Add-on Management' is set to 'Enabled' and the check box is selected for OneNote)\nResult Analysis :            Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_ADDON_MANAGEMENT\\onenote.exe'.  Existence requirement is 'all_exist' and no items were collected, so result is false.\nCriteria        :       false (All child tests must be true. (AND)) (negated)\nTest            :         true (Microsoft OneNote 2016 is installed)\nCriteria        :     true (One or more child tests must be true. (OR))\nTest            :       false (IE Security 'Add-on Management' is set to 'Enabled' and the check box is selected for SharePoint Designer)\nResult Analysis :            Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_ADDON_MANAGEMENT\\spdesign.exe'.  Existence requirement is 'all_exist' and no items were collected, so result is false.\nCriteria        :       true (One or more child tests must be true. (OR)) (negated)\nTest            :         false (Check if the SharePoint Designer 2013 key is present)\nResult Analysis :              Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\\Wow6432Node\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Uninstall\\Office15.SharePointDesigner\\'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\nTest            :         false (Check if the SharePoint Designer 2013 key is present)\nResult Analysis :              Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Uninstall\\Office15.SharePointDesigner\\'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\nCriteria        :     true (One or more child tests must be true. (OR))\nTest            :       true (PowerPoint Viewer Install path) (negated)\nTest            :       false (IE Security 'Add-on Management' is set to 'Enabled' and the check box is selected for PowerPoint Viewer)\nResult Analysis :            Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_ADDON_MANAGEMENT\\pptview.exe'.  Existence requirement is 'all_exist' and no items were collected, so result is false.\nCriteria        :     true (One or more child tests must be true. (OR))\nTest            :       true (Microsoft Expressions Install path) (negated)\nTest            :       false (IE Security 'Add-on Management' is set to 'Enabled' and the check box is selected for Microsoft Expressions)\nResult Analysis :            Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_ADDON_MANAGEMENT\\exprwd.exe'.  Existence requirement is 'all_exist' and no items were collected, so result is false.\nCriteria        :     true (One or more child tests must be true. (OR))\nTest            :       true (Microsoft Exchange Install path) (negated)\nTest            :       false (IE Security 'Add-on Management' is set to 'Enabled' and the check box is selected for Microsoft Exchange)\nResult Analysis :            Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_ADDON_MANAGEMENT\\mse7.exe'.  Existence requirement is 'all_exist' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n"},{"security_override_guidance":"","group_title":"SRG-APP-000179","third_party_tools":"","rule_title":"Consistent MIME handling must be enabled for all Office 365 ProPlus programs.","rule_id":"SV-223297r961050","weight":"10.0","stig_uuid":"B3EF3B6E-722B-1014-942B-D54B65175630","ccis":["CCI-000803"],"ia_controls":"","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000179","id":"V-223297"},"group_id":"V-223297","mitigations":"","documentable":"false","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Microsoft Office 2016 (Machine) &gt;&gt; Security Settings &gt;&gt; IE Security \"Consistent Mime Handling\" to \"Enabled\" and select the check boxes for all installed Office programs.","rule_id_src":"SV-223297r961050_rule","status":"open","group_id_src":"V-223297","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.office365:def:223297","href":"U_MS_Office_365_ProPlus_V3R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV9-oval.xml"},"reference_identifier":"4099","classification":"Unclassified","potential_impacts":"","severity":"medium","responsibility":"","comments":null,"rule_version":"O365-CO-000015","check_content":"Verify the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Microsoft Office 2016 (Machine) &gt;&gt; Security Settings &gt;&gt; IE Security &gt;&gt; Consistent Mime Handling is set to \"Enabled\" and the check box is selected for every installed Office program.\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\n\nHKLM\\software\\microsoft\\internet explorer\\main\\featurecontrol\\feature_mime_handling\n\nIf the value for all installed Office programs is set to is REG_DWORD=1, this is not a finding.","false_positives":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-108773","V-99669"],"uuid":"B4024F4F-722B-1014-8630-C1EC72F2362D","discussion":"Encryption is only as good as the encryption modules utilized. Unapproved cryptographic module algorithms cannot be verified and cannot be relied on to provide confidentiality or integrity, and DoD data may be compromised due to weak algorithms. The use of TLS provides confidentiality of data in transit between the application server and client. FIPS 140-2 approved TLS versions include TLS V1.0 or greater. \n\nTLS must be enabled and non-FIPS-approved SSL versions must be disabled. NIST SP 800-52 specifies the preferred configurations for government systems.","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-04-01T11:55:55\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :   false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :     true (One or more child tests must be true. (OR))\nTest            :       false (IE Security 'Local Machine Zone Lockdown Security' is set to 'Enabled' and the check box is