ue. (OR)) (negated)\nTest            :         false (Check if the SharePoint Designer 2013 key is present)\nResult Analysis :              Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\\Wow6432Node\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Uninstall\\Office15.SharePointDesigner\\'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\nTest            :         false (Check if the SharePoint Designer 2013 key is present)\nResult Analysis :              Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Uninstall\\Office15.SharePointDesigner\\'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\nCriteria        :     true (One or more child tests must be true. (OR))\nTest            :       true (PowerPoint Viewer Install path) (negated)\nTest            :       false (Information Bar is set to 'Enabled' for Powerpoint Viewer)\nResult Analysis :            Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\Feature_securityband\\pptview.exe'.  Existence requirement is 'all_exist' and no items were collected, so result is false.\nCriteria        :     true (One or more child tests must be true. (OR))\nTest            :       true (Microsoft Expressions Install path) (negated)\nTest            :       false (Information Bar is set to 'Enabled' for Expressions)\nResult Analysis :            Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\Feature_securityband\\exprwd.exe'.  Existence requirement is 'all_exist' and no items were collected, so result is false.\nCriteria        :     true (One or more child tests must be true. (OR))\nTest            :       true (Microsoft Exchange Install path) (negated)\nTest            :       false (Information Bar is set to 'Enabled' for Exchange)\nResult Analysis :            Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\Feature_securityband\\mse7.exe'.  Existence requirement is 'all_exist' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n"},{"security_override_guidance":"","group_title":"SRG-APP-000516","third_party_tools":"","rule_title":"The Local Machine Zone Lockdown Security must be enabled in all Office programs.","rule_id":"SV-223300r961863","weight":"10.0","stig_uuid":"B3EF3B6E-722B-1014-942B-D54B65175630","ccis":["CCI-000366"],"ia_controls":"","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000516","id":"V-223300"},"group_id":"V-223300","mitigations":"","documentable":"false","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Microsoft Office 2016 (Machine) &gt;&gt; Security Settings &gt;&gt; IE Security &gt;&gt; Local Machine Zone Lockdown to \"Enabled\" and select the check boxes for  all installed Office programs.","rule_id_src":"SV-223300r961863_rule","status":"open","group_id_src":"V-223300","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.office365:def:223300","href":"U_MS_Office_365_ProPlus_V3R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV9-oval.xml"},"reference_identifier":"4099","classification":"Unclassified","potential_impacts":"","severity":"medium","responsibility":"","comments":null,"rule_version":"O365-CO-000018","check_content":"Verify the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Microsoft Office 2016 (Machine) &gt;&gt; Security Settings &gt;&gt; IE Security &gt;&gt; Local Machine Zone Lockdown Security is set to \"Enabled\" and the check box is selected for every installed Office program.\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\n\nHKLM\\software\\microsoft\\internet explorer\\main\\featurecontrol\\feature_localmachine_lockdown\n\nIf the value for all installed Office programs is REG_DWORD = 1, this is not a finding.","false_positives":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-108779","V-99675"],"uuid":"B4025F1A-722B-1014-B25C-A74713E67042","discussion":"Internet Explorer places restrictions on each web page users can use the browser to open. Web pages on a user's local computer have the fewest security restrictions and reside in the Local Machine zone, making this security zone a prime target for malicious users and code. Disabling or not configuring this setting could allow pages in the Internet zone to navigate to pages in the Local Machine zone to then run code to elevate privileges. This could allow malicious code or users to become active on user computers or the network.","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-04-01T11:55:55\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :   false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :     true (One or more child tests must be true. (OR))\nTest            :       false (IE Security 'Local Machine Zone Lockdown Security' is set to 'Enabled' and the check box is selected for Access)\nResult Analysis :            Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_LOCALMACHINE_LOCKDOWN\\msaccess.exe'.  Existence requirement is 'all_exist' and no items were collected, so result is false.\nCriteria        :       true (All child tests must be true. (AND)) (negated)\nTest            :         false (MS Access is installed.)\nResult Analysis :              Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\nCriteria        :     false (One or more child tests must be true. (OR))\nTest            :       false (IE Security 'Local Machine Zone Lockdown Security' is set to 'Enabled' and the check box is selected for Excel)\nResult Analysis :            Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_LOCALMACHI