ain\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_LOCALMACHINE_LOCKDOWN\\exprwd.exe'.  Existence requirement is 'all_exist' and no items were collected, so result is false.\nCriteria        :     true (One or more child tests must be true. (OR))\nTest            :       true (Microsoft Exchange Install path) (negated)\nTest            :       false (IE Security 'Local Machine Zone Lockdown Security' is set to 'Enabled' and the check box is selected for Microsoft Exchange)\nResult Analysis :            Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_LOCALMACHINE_LOCKDOWN\\mse7.exe'.  Existence requirement is 'all_exist' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n"},{"security_override_guidance":"","group_title":"SRG-APP-000179","third_party_tools":"","rule_title":"The MIME Sniffing safety feature must be enabled in all Office programs.","rule_id":"SV-223301r961050","weight":"10.0","stig_uuid":"B3EF3B6E-722B-1014-942B-D54B65175630","ccis":["CCI-000803"],"ia_controls":"","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000179","id":"V-223301"},"group_id":"V-223301","mitigations":"","documentable":"false","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Microsoft Office 2016 (Machine) &gt;&gt; Security Settings &gt;&gt; IE Security &gt;&gt; Mime Sniffing Safety Feature to \"Enabled\" for all installed Office programs.","rule_id_src":"SV-223301r961050_rule","status":"open","group_id_src":"V-223301","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.office365:def:223301","href":"U_MS_Office_365_ProPlus_V3R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV9-oval.xml"},"reference_identifier":"4099","classification":"Unclassified","potential_impacts":"","severity":"medium","responsibility":"","comments":null,"rule_version":"O365-CO-000019","check_content":"Verify the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Microsoft Office 2016 (Machine) &gt;&gt; Security Settings &gt;&gt; IE Security &gt;&gt; Mime Sniffing Safety Feature is set to \"Enabled\" and the check box is selected for every installed Office program.\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\n\nHKLM\\software\\microsoft\\internet explorer\\main\\featurecontrol\\feature_mime_sniffing\n\nIf the value for all installed Office Programs is REG_DWORD = 1, this is not a finding.","false_positives":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-108781","V-99677"],"uuid":"B40264C0-722B-1014-9016-94F1E194F8C4","discussion":"Encryption is only as good as the encryption modules utilized. Unapproved cryptographic module algorithms cannot be verified and cannot be relied upon to provide confidentiality or integrity, and DoD data may be compromised due to weak algorithms. The use of TLS provides confidentiality of data in transit between the application server and client. FIPS 140-2 approved TLS versions include TLS V1.0 or greater. \n\nTLS must be enabled and non-FIPS-approved SSL versions must be disabled. NIST SP 800-52 specifies the preferred configurations for government systems.","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-04-01T11:55:55\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :   false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :     true (One or more child tests must be true. (OR))\nTest            :       false (IE Security 'Mime Sniffing Safety Feature' is set to 'Enabled' and the check box is selected for Access)\nResult Analysis :            Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_MIME_SNIFFING\\msaccess.exe'.  Existence requirement is 'all_exist' and no items were collected, so result is false.\nCriteria        :       true (All child tests must be true. (AND)) (negated)\nTest            :         false (MS Access is installed.)\nResult Analysis :            