y":"medium","responsibility":"","comments":null,"rule_version":"O365-CO-000021","check_content":"Verify the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Microsoft Office 2016 (Machine) &gt;&gt; Security Settings &gt;&gt; IE Security &gt;&gt; Object Caching Protection is set to \"Enabled\" and the check box is selected for every installed Office program.\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\n\nHKLM\\software\\microsoft\\internet explorer\\main\\featurecontrol\\feature_object_caching\n\nIf the value for all installed programs is REG_DWORD = 1, this is not a finding.","false_positives":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-108785","V-99681"],"uuid":"B4026F81-722B-1014-86F0-BB33A7F4CEAF","discussion":"Encryption is only as good as the encryption modules utilized. Unapproved cryptographic module algorithms cannot be verified and cannot be relied upon to provide confidentiality or integrity, and DoD data may be compromised due to weak algorithms. The use of TLS provides confidentiality of data in transit between the application server and client. FIPS 140-2 approved TLS versions include TLS V1.0 or greater. \n\nTLS must be enabled and non-FIPS-approved SSL versions must be disabled. NIST SP 800-52 specifies the preferred configurations for government systems.","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-04-01T11:55:55\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :   false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :     true (One or more child tests must be true. (OR))\nTest            :       false (Object Caching Protection is set to 'Enabled' for Access)\nResult Analysis :            Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\Feature_object_caching\\msaccess.exe'.  Existence requirement is 'all_exist' and no items were collec