ere collected, so result is false.\nCriteria        :     true (One or more child tests must be true. (OR))\nTest            :       true (Microsoft Expressions Install path) (negated)\nTest            :       false (Saved from URL is set to 'Enabled' for Expressions)\nResult Analysis :            Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\Feature_unc_savedfilecheck\\exprwd.exe'.  Existence requirement is 'all_exist' and no items were collected, so result is false.\nCriteria        :     true (One or more child tests must be true. (OR))\nTest            :       true (Microsoft Exchange Install path) (negated)\nTest            :       false (Saved from URL is set to 'Enabled' for Exchange)\nResult Analysis :            Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\Feature_unc_savedfilecheck\\mse7.exe'.  Existence requirement is 'all_exist' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n"},{"security_override_guidance":"","group_title":"SRG-APP-000112","third_party_tools":"","rule_title":"Scripted Windows Security restrictions must be enabled in all Office programs.","rule_id":"SV-223308r960921","weight":"10.0","stig_uuid":"B3EF3B6E-722B-1014-942B-D54B65175630","ccis":["CCI-001695"],"ia_controls":"","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000112","id":"V-223308"},"group_id":"V-223308","mitigations":"","documentable":"false","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Microsoft Office 2016 (Machine) &gt;&gt; Security Settings &gt;&gt; IE Security &gt;&gt;Scripted Window Security Restrictions to \"Enabled\" and select the check boxes for  all installed Office programs.","rule_id_src":"SV-223308r960921_rule","status":"open","group_id_src":"V-223308","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.office365:def:223308","href":"U_MS_Office_365_ProPlus_V3R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV9-oval.xml"},"reference_identifier":"4099","classification":"Unclassified","potential_impacts":"","severity":"medium","responsibility":"","comments":null,"rule_version":"O365-CO-000026","check_content":"Verify the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Microsoft Office 2016 (Machine) &gt;&gt; Security Settings &gt;&gt; IE Security &gt;&gt; Scripted Window Security Restrictions is set to \"Enabled\" and the check box is selected for every installed Office program.\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\n\nHKLM\\Software\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_WINDOW_RESTRICTIONS\n\nIf the value for all installed programs is REG_DWORD = 1, this is not a finding.","false_positives":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-108795","V-99691"],"uuid":"B4028B3B-722B-1014-8CA9-C86780C7DE45","discussion":"Malicious websites often try to confuse or trick users into giving a site permission to perform an action allowing the site to take control of the users' computers in some manner. Disabling or not configuring this setting allows unknown websites to:\n- Create browser windows appearing to be from the local operating system.\n- Draw active windows displaying outside of the viewable areas of the screen capturing keyboard input.\n- Overlay parent windows with their own browser windows to hide important system information, choices, or prompts.","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-04-01T11:55:55\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :   false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :     true (One or more child tests must be true. (OR))\nTest            :       false (IE Security 'Scripted Window Security Restrictions' is set to 'Enabled' and the check box is selected for Access)\nResult Analysis :            Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_WINDOW_RESTRICTIONS\\msaccess.exe'.  Existence requirement is 'all_exist' and no items were collected, so result is false.\nCriteria        :       true (All child tests must be true. (AND)) (negated)\nTest            :         false (MS Access is installed.)\nResult Analysis :              Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\nCriteria        :     false (One or more child tests must be true. (OR))\nTest            :       false (IE Security 'Scripted Window Security Restrictions' is set to 'Enabled' and the check box is selected for Excel)\nResult Analysis :            Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_WINDOW_RESTRICTIONS\\excel.exe'.  Existence requirement is 'all_exist' and no items were collected, so result is false.\nCriteria        :       false (All child tests must be true. (AND)) (negated)\nTest            :         true (MS Excel is installed.)\nCriteria        :     true (One or more child tests must be true. (OR))\nTest            :       false (IE Security 'Scripted Window Security Restrictions' is set to 'Enabled' and the check box is selected for Groove and OneDrive)\nResult Analysis :            Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_WINDOW_RESTRICTIONS\\groove.exe'.  Existence requirement is 'all_exist' and no items were collected, so result is false.\nCriteria        :       true (All child tests must be true. (AND)) (negated)\nTest            :         false (Microsoft OneDrive for Business 2016 is installed)\nResult Analysis :              Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\nCriteria        :     false (One or more child tests must be true. (OR))\nTest            :       false (IE Security 'Scripted Window Security Restrictions' is set to 'Enabled' and the check box is selected for Outlook)\nResult Analysis :            Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_WINDOW_RESTRICTIONS\\outlook.exe'.  Existence requirement is 'all_exist' and no items were collected, so result is false.\nCriteria        :       false (All child tests must be true. (AND)) (negated)\nTest            :         true (MS Outlook is installed.)\nCriteria        :     false (One or more child tests must be true. (OR))\nTest            :       false (IE Security 'Scripted Window Security Restrictions' is set to 'Enabled' and the check box is selected for PowerPoint)\nResult Analysis :            Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_WINDOW_RESTRICTIONS\\powerpnt.exe'.  Existence requirement is 'all_exist' and no items were collected, so result is false.\nCriteria        :       false (All child tests must be true. (AND)) (negated)\nTest            :         true (MS PowerPoint is installed.)\nCriteria        :     true (One or more child tests must be true. (OR))\nTest            :       false (IE Security 'Scripted Window Security Restrictions' is set to 'Enabled' and the check box is selected for Project)\nResult Analysis :            Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_WINDOW_RESTRICTIONS\\winproj.exe'.  Existence requirement is 'all_exist' and no items were collected, so result is false.\nCriteria        :       true (All child tests must be true. (AND)) (negated)\nTest            :         false (MS Project is installed.)\nResult Analysis :              Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\nCriteria        :     false (One or more child tests must be true. (OR))\nTest            :       false (IE Security 'Scripted Window Security Restrictions' is set to 'Enabled' and the check box is selected for Publisher)\nResult Analysis :            Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_WINDOW_RESTRICTIONS\\mspub.exe'.  Existence requirement is 'all_exist' and no items were collected, so result is false.\nCriteria        :       false (All child tests must be true. (AND)) (negated)\nTest            :         true (MS Publisher is installed.)\nCriteria        :     true (One or more child tests must be true. (OR))\nTest            :       false (IE Security 'Scripted Window Security Restrictions' is set to 'Enabled' and the check box is selected for Visio)\nResult Analysis :            Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_WINDOW_RESTRICTIONS\\visio.exe'.  Existence requirement is 'all_exist' and no items were collected, so result is false.\nCriteria        :       true (All child tests must be true. (AND)) (negated)\nTest            :         false (MS Visio is installed.)\nResult Analysis :              Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\nCriteria        :     false (One or more child tests must be true. (OR))\nTest            :       false (IE Security 'Scripted Window Security Restrictions' is set to 'Enabled' and the check box is selected for Word)\nResult Analysis :            Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_WINDOW_RESTRICTIONS\\winword.exe'.  Existence requirement is 'all_exist' and no items were collected, so result is false.\nCriteria        :       false (All child tests must be true. (AND)) (negated)\nTest            :         true (MS Word is installed.)\nCriteria        :     false (One or more child tests must be true. (OR))\nTest            :       false (IE Security 'Scripted Window Security Restrictions' is set to 'Enabled' and the check box is selected for OneNote)\nResult Analysis :            Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_WINDOW_RESTRICTIONS\\onenote.exe'.  Existence requirement is 'all_exist' and no items were collected, so result is false.\nCriteria        :       false (All child tests must be true. (AND)) (negated)\nTest            :         true (Microsoft OneNote 2016 is installed)\nCriteria        :     true (One or more child tests must be true. (OR))\nTest            :       false (IE Security 'Scripted Window Security Restrictions' is set to 'Enabled' and the check box is selected for SharePoint Designer)\nResult Analysis :            Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_WINDOW_RESTRICTIONS\\spdesign.exe'.  Existence requirement is 'all_exist' and no items were collected, so result is false.\nCriteria        :       true (One or more child tests must be true. (OR)) (negated)\nTest            :         false (Check if the SharePoint Designer 2013 key is present)\nResult Analysis :              Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\\Wow6432Node\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Uninstall\\Office15.SharePointDesigner\\'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\nTest            :         false (Check if the SharePoint Designer 2013 key is present)\nResult Analysis :              Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Uninstall\\Office15.SharePointDesigner\\'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\nCriteria        :     true (One or more child tests must be true. (OR))\nTest            :       true (PowerPoint Viewer Install path) (negated)\nTest            :       false (IE Security 'Scripted Window Security Restrictions' is set to 'Enabled' and the check box is selected for PowerPoint Viewer)\nResult Analysis :            Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_WINDOW_RESTRICTIONS\\pptview.exe'.  Existence requirement is 'all_exist' and no items were collected, so result is false.\nCriteria        :     true (One or more child tests must be true. (OR))\nTest            :       true (Microsoft Expressions Install path) (negated)\nTest            :       false (IE Security 'Scripted Window Security Restrictions' is set to 'Enabled' and the check box is selected for Microsoft Expressions)\nResult Analysis :            Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_WINDOW_RESTRICTIONS\\exprwd.exe'.  Existence requirement is 'all_exist' and no items were collected, so result is false.\nCriteria        :     true (One or more child tests must be true. (OR))\nTest            :       true (Microsoft Exchange Install path) (negated)\nTest            :       false (IE Security 'Scripted Window Security Restrictions' is set to 'Enabled' and the check box is selected for Microsoft Exchange)\nResult Analysis :            Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_WINDOW_RESTRICTIONS\\mse7.exe'.  Existence requirement is 'all_exist' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n"},{"security_override_guidance":"","group_title":"SRG-APP-000488","third_party_tools":"","rule_title":"Flash player activation must be disabled in all Office programs.","rule_id":"SV-223309r961779","weight":"10.0","stig_uuid":"B3EF3B6E-722B-1014-942B-D54B65175630","ccis":["CCI-002460"],"ia_controls":"","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000488","id":"V-223309"},"group_id":"V-223309","mitigations":"","documentable":"false","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; MS Security Guide &gt;&gt; Block Flash activation in Office documents &gt;&gt; Enabled &gt;&gt; Block all activation to \"Enabled\" (Block all activation).","rule_id_src":"SV-223309r961779_rule","status":"open","group_id_src":"V-223309","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.office365:def:223309","href":"U_MS_Office_365_ProPlus_V3R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV9-oval.xml"},"reference_identifier":"4099","classification":"Unclassified","potential_impacts":"","severity":"medium","responsibility":"","comments":null,"rule_version":"O365-CO-000027","check_content":"Verify the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; MS Security Guide &gt;&gt; Block Flash activation in Office documents &gt;&gt; Enabled &gt;&gt; Block all activation is set to \"Enabled\" Block all activation.\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\n\nHKLM\\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Office\\Common\\COM Compatibility\n\nIf the value for COMMENT is REG_SZ = Block all Flash activation, this is not a finding.","false_positives":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-108797","V-99693"],"uuid":"B40290B3-722B-1014-BD7C-D4E7ACBF8D97","discussion":"This policy setting controls whether the Adobe Flash control can be activated by Office documents. Note that activation blocking applies only within Office processes.\n\nIf you enable this policy setting, you can choose from three options to control whether and how Flash is blocked from activation:\n\n1. \"Block all activation\" prevents the Flash control from being loaded, whether directly referenced by the document or indirectly by another embedded object.\n2. \"Block embedding/linking, allow other activation\" prevents the Flash control from being loaded when directly referenced by the document, but does not prevent activation through another object.\n3. \"Allow all activation\" restores Office's default behavior, allowing the Flash control to be activated.\n\nBecause this setting is not a true Group Policy setting and \"tattoos\" the registry, enabling the \"Allow all activation\" option is the only way to restore default behavior after either of the \"Block\" options has been applied. It is not recommended to configure this setting to \"Disabled\" or \"Not Configured\" after it has been enabled.","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-04-01T11:55:55\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :   false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :     false (Flash player activation is disabled.)\nResult Analysis :          Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\Software\\Microsoft\\Office\\Common\\COM Compatibility\\COMMENT'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n"},{"security_override_guidance":"","group_title":"SRG-APP-000210","third_party_tools":"","rule_title":"Trusted Locations on the network must be disabled in Excel.","rule_id":"SV-223310r961092","weight":"10.0","stig_uuid":"B3EF3B6E-722B-1014-942B-D54B65175630","ccis":["CCI-001170"],"ia_controls":"","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000210","id":"V-223310"},"group_id":"V-223310","mitigations":"","documentable":"false","fix_text":"Set the policy value for User Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Microsoft Excel 2016 &gt;&gt; Excel Options &gt;&gt; Security &gt;&gt; Trust Center &gt;&gt; Trusted Locations \"Allow Trusted Locations on the network\" to \"Disabled\".","rule_id_src":"SV-223310r961092_rule","status":"open","group_id_src":"V-223310","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.office365:def:223310","href":"U_MS_Office_365_ProPlus_V3R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV9-oval.xml"},"reference_identifier":"4099","classification":"Unclassified","potential_impacts":"","severity":"medium","responsibility":"","comments":null,"rule_version":"O365-EX-000001","check_content":"Verify the policy value for User Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Microsoft Excel 2016 &gt;&gt; Excel Options &gt;&gt; Security &gt;&gt; Trust Center &gt;&gt; Trusted Locations \"Allow Trusted Locations on the network\" is set to \"Disabled\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\n\nHKCU\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Office\\16.0\\excel\\security\\trusted locations\n\nIf the value AllowNetworkLocations is REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.","false_positives":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-108799","V-99695"],"uuid":"B4029874-722B-1014-9522-E6E08F0874A8","discussion":"This policy setting controls whether trusted locations on the network can be used.\n\nIf you enable this policy setting, users can specify trusted locations on network shares or in other remote locations that are not under their direct control by selecting the \"Allow Trusted Locations on my network (not recommended)\" check box in the Trusted Locations section of the Trust Center. Content, code, and add-ins are allowed to load from trusted locations with minimal security and without prompting the user for permission.\n\nIf you disable or do not configure this policy setting, the selected application ignores any network locations listed in the Trusted Locations section of the Trust Center. Disabling this policy setting does not delete any network locations from the Trusted Locations list. Instead, it forces the selected application to treat the locations as non-trusted and prevents users from adding new network locations to the list.\n\nIf you also deploy Trusted Locations via Group Policy, you should verify whether any of them are remote locations. If any of them are remote locations and you do not allow remote locations via this policy setting, those policy keys that point to remote locations will be ignored on client computers.\n\nDisabling this policy setting will cause disruption for users who add network locations to the Trusted Locations list. However, it is not recommended to enable this policy setting (as the \"Allow Trusted Locations on my network (not recommended)\" check box itself states), so in practice it should be possible to disable this policy setting in most situations without causing significant usability issues for most users.","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-04-01T11:55:55\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :   false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :     false (Trusted Locations on the network are disabled in Excel.)\nResult Analysis :          Registry Name Not found in user profile ntuser.dat file(s): 'Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Office\\16.0\\excel\\security\\trusted locations\\AllowNetworkLocations'.  Existence requirement is 'all_exist' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n                :          For 'MAXHEALTH\\katessem.admin':  Registry Name Not found in user profile ntuser.dat file(s): 'Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Office\\16.0\\excel\\security\\trusted locations\\AllowNetworkLocations'.  \n                :          For 'MAXHEALTH\\katessem':  Registry Name Not found in user profile ntuser.dat file(s): 'Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Office\\16.0\\excel\\security\\trusted locations\\AllowNetworkLocations'.  \n                :          For 'MHL-PW06M2V2\\Administrator':  Registry Name Not found in user profile ntuser.dat file(s): 'Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Office\\16.0\\excel\\security\\trusted locations\\AllowNetworkLocations'.  \n"},{"security_override_guidance":"","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","third_party_tools":"","rule_title":"VBA Macros not digitally signed must be blocked in Excel.","rule_id":"SV-223311r960963","weight":"10.0","stig_uuid":"B3EF3B6E-722B-1014-942B-D54B65175630","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"ia_controls":"","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000141","id":"V-223311"},"group_id":"V-223311","mitigations":"","documentable":"false","fix_text":"Set the policy value for User Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Microsoft Excel 2016 &gt;&gt; Excel Options &gt;&gt; Security &gt;&gt; Trust Center &gt;&gt; \"Macro Notification Settings\" is set to \"Enabled\" and select \"Disable VBA macros except digitally signed macros\" from the Options.","rule_id_src":"SV-223311r960963_rule","status":"open","group_id_src":"V-223311","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.office365:def:223311","href":"U_MS_Office_365_ProPlus_V3R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV9-oval.xml"},"reference_identifier":"4099","classification":"Unclassified","potential_impacts":"","severity":"medium","responsibility":"","comments":null,"rule_version":"O365-EX-000002","check_content":"Verify the policy value for User Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Microsoft Excel 2016 &gt;&gt; Excel Options &gt;&gt; Security &gt;&gt; Trust Center &gt;&gt; \"Macro Notification Settings\" is set to \"Enabled\" and \"Disable VBA macros except digitally signed macros\" from the Options is selected.\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\nHKCU\\software\\policies\\Microsoft\\office\\16.0\\excel\\security\n\nIf the value vbawarnings is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding. A value of REG_DWORD =  4 is also acceptable. If the registry key does not exist or is not configured properly, this is a finding.","false_positives":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-108801","V-99697"],"uuid":"B402A03E-722B-1014-9643-A130B2026F70","discussion":"This policy setting controls how the specified applications warn users when Visual Basic for Applications (VBA) macros are present.\n\nIf you enable this policy setting, you can choose from four options for determining how the specified applications will warn the user about macros:\n\n- Disable all with notification: The application displays the Trust Bar for all macros, whether signed or unsigned. This option enforces the default configuration in Office. This option also allows users to potentially enable unsigned/untrusted macros.  If a site requires the use of macros, they must be signed /approved and added to appropriate locations listed in the Trust Center Settings. \n- Disable all except digitally signed macros: The application displays the Trust Bar for digitally signed macros, allowing users to enable them or leave them disabled. Any unsigned macros are disabled, and users are not notified.\n- Disable all without notification: The application disables all macros, whether signed or unsigned, and does not notify users.\n- Enable all macros (not recommended): All macros are enabled, whether signed or unsigned. This option can significantly reduce security by allowing dangerous code to run undetected.","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-04-01T11:55:55\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :   false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :     false ('Macro Notification Settings' is set to Enabled and 'Disable VBA macros except digitally signed macros' from the Options is selected.)\nResult Analysis :          Registry Name Not found in user profile ntuser.dat file(s): 'Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Office\\16.0\\excel\\security\\vbawarnings'.  Existence requirement is 'all_exist' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n                :          For 'MAXHEALTH\\katessem.admin':  Registry Name Not found in user profile ntuser.dat file(s): 'Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Office\\16.0\\excel\\security\\vbawarnings'.  \n                :          For 'MAXHEALTH\\katessem':  Registry Name Not found in user profile ntuser.dat file(s): 'Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Office\\16.0\\excel\\security\\vbawarnings'.  \n                :          For 'MHL-PW06M2V2\\Administrator':  Registry Name Not found in user profile ntuser.dat file(s): 'Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Office\\16.0\\excel\\security\\vbawarnings'.  \n"},{"security_override_guidance":"","group_title":"SRG-APP-000207","third_party_tools":"","rule_title":"Dynamic Data Exchange (DDE) server launch in Excel must be blocked.","rule_id":"SV-223312r961086","weight":"10.0","stig_uuid":"B3EF3B6E-722B-1014-942B-D54B65175630","ccis":["CCI-001662"],"ia_controls":"","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000207","id":"V-223312"},"group_id":"V-223312","mitigations":"","documentable":"false","fix_text":"Set policy value for User Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Microsoft Excel 2016 &gt;&gt; Excel Options &gt;&gt; Security &gt;&gt; Trust Center &gt;&gt; External Content &gt;&gt; Don't allow Dynamic Data Exchange (DDE) server launch in Excel to \"Enabled\".","rule_id_src":"SV-223312r961086_rule","status":"open","group_id_src":"V-223312","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.office365:def:223312","href":"U_MS_Office_365_ProPlus_V3R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV9-oval.xml"},"reference_identifier":"4099","classification":"Unclassified","potential_impacts":"","severity":"medium","responsibility":"","comments":null,"rule_version":"O365-EX-000003","check_content":"Verify the policy value for User Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Microsoft Excel 2016 &gt;&gt; Excel Options &gt;&gt; Security &gt;&gt; Trust Center &gt;&gt; External Content &gt;&gt; Don't allow Dynamic Data Exchange (DDE) server launch in Excel is set to \"Enabled\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\n\nHKCU\\software\\policies\\microsoft\\office\\16.0\\excel\\security\\external content\n\nIf the value for \"disableddeserverlaunch\" is REG_DWORD = 1, this is not a finding.","false_positives":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-108803","V-99699"],"uuid":"B402A8D5-722B-1014-A756-E9CB27ECE95E","discussion":"This policy setting allows you to control whether Dynamic Data Exchange (DDE) server launch is allowed.\n\nBy default, DDE server launch is turned off, but users can turn on DDE server launch by going to File &gt;&gt; Options &gt;&gt; Trust Center &gt;&gt; Trust Center Settings &gt;&gt; External Content.\n\nFor security reasons, turning on DDE server launch is not recommended.\n\nNote: For DDE server launch to work, Dynamic Data Exchange (DDE) server lookup must be turned on. Be sure that the âDon't allow Dynamic Data Exchange (DDE) server lookupâ policy setting is not enabled, because enabling that policy setting turns off DDE server lookup.\n\nIf you enable this policy setting, DDE server launch is not allowed, and users cannot turn on DDE server launch in the Trust Center.\n\nIf you disable this policy setting, DDE server launch is allowed, and users cannot turn off DDE server launch in the Trust Center. For security reasons, this is not recommended.\n\nIf you do not configure this policy setting, DDE server launch is turned off, but users can turn on DDE server launch in the Trust Center.\n\nNote: This policy setting only applies to subscription versions of Office, such as Office 365 ProPlus.","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-04-01T11:55:55\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :   false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :     false (Don't allow Dynamic Data Exchange (DDE) server launch in Excel is Enabled.)\nResult Analysis :          Registry Name Not found in user profile ntuser.dat file(s): 'Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Office\\16.0\\excel\\security\\external content\\disableddeserverlaunch'.  Existence requirement is 'all_exist' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n                :          For 'MAXHEALTH\\katessem.admin':  Registry Name Not found in user profile ntuser.dat file(s): 'Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Office\\16.0\\excel\\security\\external content\\disableddeserverlaunch'.  \n                :          For 'MAXHEALTH\\katessem':  Registry Name Not found in user profile ntuser.dat file(s): 'Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Office\\16.0\\excel\\security\\external content\\disableddeserverlaunch'.  \n                :          For 'MHL-PW06M2V2\\Administrator':  Registry Name Not found in user profile ntuser.dat file(s): 'Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Office\\16.0\\excel\\security\\external content\\disableddeserverlaunch'.  \n"},{"security_override_guidance":"","group_title":"SRG-APP-000207","third_party_tools":"","rule_title":"Dynamic Data Exchange (DDE) server lookup in Excel must be blocked.","rule_id":"SV-223313r961086","weight":"10.0","stig_uuid":"B3EF3B6E-722B-1014-942B-D54B65175630","ccis":["CCI-001662"],"ia_controls":"","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000207","id":"V-223313"},"group_id":"V-223313","mitigations":"","documentable":"false","fix_text":"Set policy value for User Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Microsoft Excel 2016 &gt;&gt; Excel Options &gt;&gt; Security &gt;&gt; Trust Center &gt;&gt; External Content &gt;&gt; Don't allow Dynamic Data Exchange (DDE) server lookup in Excel to \"Enabled\".","rule_id_src":"SV-223313r961086_rule","status":"open","group_id_src":"V-223313","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.office365:def:223313","href":"U_MS_Office_365_ProPlus_V3R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV9-oval.xml"},"reference_identifier":"4099","classification":"Unclassified","potential_impacts":"","severity":"medium","responsibility":"","comments":null,"rule_version":"O365-EX-000004","check_content":"Verify the policy value for User Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Microsoft Excel 2016 &gt;&gt; Excel Options &gt;&gt; Security &gt;&gt; Trust Center &gt;&gt; External Content &gt;&gt; Don't allow Dynamic Data Exchange (DDE) server lookup in Excel is set to \"Enabled\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\n\nHKCU\\software\\policies\\microsoft\\office\\16.0\\excel\\security\\external content\n\nIf the value for \"disableddeserverlookup\" is REG_DWORD = 1, this is not a finding.","false_positives":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-108805","V-99701"],"uuid":"B402B17D-722B-1014-B0AB-DBC0F1CFA8FB","discussion":"This policy setting allows you to control whether Dynamic Data Exchange (DDE) server lookup is allowed.\n\nBy default, DDE server lookup is turned on, but users can turn off DDE server lookup by going to File &gt;&gt; Options &gt;&gt; Trust Center &gt;&gt; Trust Center Settings &gt;&gt; External Content.\n\nIf you enable this policy setting, DDE server lookup is not allowed, and users cannot turn on DDE server lookup in the Trust Center.\n\nNote: If you are using Dynamic Data Exchange (DDE) server launch, which is not recommended, do not enable this policy setting, because DDE server launch requires DDE server lookup to be on.\n\nIf you disable or do not configure this policy setting, DDE server lookup is turned on, but users can turn off DDE server lookup in the Trust Center.\n\nNote: This policy setting only applies to subscription versions of Office, such as Office 365 ProPlus.","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-04-01T11:55:55\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :   false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :     false (The Dynamic Data Exchange (DDE) server lookup in Excel is blocked)\nResult Analysis :          Registry Name Not found in user profile ntuser.dat file(s): 'Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Office\\16.0\\excel\\security\\external content\\disableddeserverlookup'.  Existence requirement is 'all_exist' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n                :          For 'MAXHEALTH\\katessem.admin':  Registry Name Not found in user profile ntuser.dat file(s): 'Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Office\\16.0\\excel\\security\\external content\\disableddeserverlookup'.  \n                :          For 'MAXHEALTH\\katessem':  Registry Name Not found in user profile ntuser.dat file(s): 'Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Office\\16.0\\excel\\security\\external content\\disableddeserverlookup'.  \n                :          For 'MHL-PW06M2V2\\Administrator':  Registry Name Not found in user profile ntuser.dat file(s): 'Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Office\\16.0\\excel\\security\\external content\\disableddeserverlookup'.  \n"},{"security_override_guidance":"","group_title":"SRG-APP-000207","third_party_tools":"","rule_title":"Open/save of dBase III / IV format files must be blocked.","rule_id":"SV-223314r961086","weight":"10.0","stig_uuid":"B3EF3B6E-722B-1014-942B-D54B65175630","ccis":["CCI-001662"],"ia_controls":"","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000207","id":"V-223314"},"group_id":"V-223314","mitigations":"","documentable":"false","fix_text":"Set the policy value for User Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Microsoft Excel 2016 &gt;&gt; Excel Options &gt;&gt; Security &gt;&gt; Trust Center &gt;&gt; File Block Settings \"dBase III / IV files\" to \"Enabled: Open/Save blocked, use open policy\".","rule_id_src":"SV-223314r961086_rule","status":"open","group_id_src":"V-223314","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.office365:def:223314","href":"U_MS_Office_365_ProPlus_V3R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV9-oval.xml"},"reference_identifier":"4099","classification":"Unclassified","potential_impacts":"","severity":"medium","responsibility":"","comments":null,"rule_version":"O365-EX-000005","check_content":"Verify the policy value for User Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Microsoft Excel 2016 &gt;&gt; Excel Options &gt;&gt; Security &gt;&gt; Trust Center &gt;&gt; File Block Settings \"dBase III / IV files\" is set to \"Enabled: Open/Save blocked, use open policy\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\n\nHKCU\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Office\\16.0\\excel\\security\\fileblock\n\nIf the value DBaseFiles is REG_DWORD = 2, this is not a finding.","false_positives":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-108807","V-99703"],"uuid":"B402BAAE-722B-1014-B130-8321E0BD7DD8","discussion":"This policy setting allows you to determine whether users can open, view, edit, or save Excel files with the format specified by the title of this policy setting.\n\nIf you enable this policy setting, you can specify whether users can open, view, edit, or save files.\n\nThe options that can be selected are below. Note: Not all options may be available for this policy setting.\n\n- Do not block: The file type will not be blocked.\n- Save blocked: Saving of the file type will be blocked.\n- Open/Save blocked, use open policy: Both opening and saving of the file type will be blocked. The file will open based on the policy setting configured in the \"default file block behavior\" key.\n- Block: Both opening and saving of the file type will be blocked, and the file will not open.\n- Open in Protected View: Both opening and saving of the file type will be blocked, and the option to edit the file type will not be enabled.\n- Allow editing and open in Protected View: Both opening and saving of the file type will be blocked, and the option to edit will be enabled.\n\nIf you disable or do not configure this policy setting, the file type will not be blocked.","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-04-01T11:55:55\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :   false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :     false (Open/save of dBase III / IV format files are blocked.)\nResult Analysis :          Registry Name Not found in user profile ntuser.dat file(s): 'Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Office\\16.0\\excel\\security\\fileblock\\DBaseFiles'.  Existence requirement is 'all_exist' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n                :          For 'MAXHEALTH\\katessem.admin':  Registry Name Not found in user profile ntuser.dat file(s): 'Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Office\\16.0\\excel\\security\\fileblock\\DBaseFiles'.  \n                :          For 'MAXHEALTH\\katessem':  Registry Name Not found in user profile ntuser.dat file(s): 'Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Office\\16.0\\excel\\security\\fileblock\\DBaseFiles'.  \n                :          For 'MHL-PW06M2V2\\Administrator':  Registry Name Not found in user profile ntuser.dat file(s): 'Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Office\\16.0\\excel\\security\\fileblock\\DBaseFiles'.  \n"},{"security_override_guidance":"","group_title":"SRG-APP-000207","third_party_tools":"","rule_title":"Open/save of Dif and Sylk format files must be blocked.","rule_id":"SV-223315r961086","weight":"10.0","stig_uuid":"B3EF3B6E-722B-1014-942B-D54B65175630","ccis":["CCI-001662"],"ia_controls":"","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000207","id":"V-223315"},"group_id":"V-223315","mitigations":"","documentable":"false","fix_text":"Set the policy value for User Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Microsoft Excel 2016 &gt;&gt; Excel Options &gt;&gt; Security &gt;&gt; Trust Center &gt;&gt; File Block Settings \"Dif and Sylk files\" to \"Enabled: Open/Save blocked, use open policy\".","rule_id_src":"SV-223315r961086_rule","status":"open","group_id_src":"V-223315","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.office365:def:223315","href":"U_MS_Office_365_ProPlus_V3R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV9-oval.xml"},"reference_identifier":"4099","classification":"Unclassified","potential_impacts":"","severity":"medium","responsibility":"","comments":null,"rule_version":"O365-EX-000006","check_content":"Verify the policy value for User Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Microsoft Excel 2016 &gt;&gt; Excel Options &gt;&gt; Security &gt;&gt; Trust Center &gt;&gt; File Block Settings \"Dif and Sylk files\" is set to \"Enabled: Open/Save blocked, use open policy\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\n\nHKCU\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Office\\16.0\\excel\\security\\fileblock\n\nIf the value DifandSylkFiles is REG_DWORD = 2, this is not a finding.","false_positives":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-108809","V-99705"],"uuid":"B402C505-722B-1014-A385-E6B58047AB97","discussion":"This policy setting allows you to determine whether users can open, view, edit, or save Excel files with the format specified by the title of this policy setting. If you enable this policy setting, you can specify whether users can open, view, edit, or save files. The options that can be selected are below. Note: Not all options may be available for this policy setting.\n\n- Do not block: The file type will not be blocked.\n- Save blocked: Saving of the file type will be blocked.\n- Open/Save blocked, use open policy: Both opening and saving of the file type will be blocked. The file will open based on the policy setting configured in the \"default file block behavior\" key.\n- Block: Both opening and saving of the file type will be blocked, and the file will not open.\n- Open in Protected View: Both opening and saving of the file type will be blocked, and the option to edit the file type will not be enabled.\n- Allow editing and open in Protected View: Both opening and saving of the file type will be blocked, and the option to edit will be enabled. \n\nIf you disable or do not configure this policy setting, the file type will not be blocked.","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-04-01T11:55:55\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :   false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :     false ('Dif and Sylk files' is set to 'Enabled: Open/Save blocked, use open policy')\nResult Analysis :          Registry Name Not found in user profile ntuser.dat file(s): 'Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Office\\16.0\\excel\\security\\fileblock\\DifandSylkFiles'.  Existence requirement is 'all_exist' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n                :          For 'MAXHEALTH\\katessem.admin':  Registry Name Not found in user profile ntuser.dat file(s): 'Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Office\\16.0\\excel\\security\\fileblock\\DifandSylkFiles'.  \n                :          For 'MAXHEALTH\\katessem':  Registry Name Not found in user profile ntuser.dat file(s): 'Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Office\\16.0\\excel\\security\\fileblock\\DifandSylkFiles'.  \n                :          For 'MHL-PW06M2V2\\Administrator':  Registry Name Not found in user profile ntuser.dat file(s): 'Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Office\\16.0\\excel\\security\\fileblock\\DifandSylkFiles'.  \n"},{"security_override_guidance":"","group_title":"SRG-APP-000207","third_party_tools":"","rule_title":"Open/save of Excel 2 macrosheets and add-in files must be blocked.","rule_id":"SV-223316r961086","weight":"10.0","stig_uuid":"B3EF3B6E-722B-1014-942B-D54B65175630","ccis":["CCI-001662"],"ia_controls":"","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000207","id":"V-223316"},"group_id":"V-223316","mitigations":"","documentable":"false","fix_text":"Set the policy value for User Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Microsoft Excel 2016 &gt;&gt; Excel Options &gt;&gt; Security &gt;&gt; Trust Center &gt;&gt; File Block Settings \"Excel 2 macrosheets and add-in files\" to \"Enabled: Open/Save blocked, use open policy\".","rule_id_src":"SV-223316r961086_rule","status":"open","group_id_src":"V-223316","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.office365:def:223316","href":"U_MS_Office_365_ProPlus_V3R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV9-oval.xml"},"reference_identifier":"4099","classification":"Unclassified","potential_impacts":"","severity":"medium","responsibility":"","comments":null,"rule_version":"O365-EX-000007","check_content":"Verify the policy value for User Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Microsoft Excel 2016 &gt;&gt; Excel Options &gt;&gt; Security &gt;&gt; Trust Center &gt;&gt; File Block Settings \"Excel 2 macrosheets and add-in files\" is set to \"Enabled: Open/Save blocked, use open policy\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\n\nHKCU\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Office\\16.0\\excel\\security\\fileblock\n\nIf the value XL2Macros is REG_DWORD = 2, this is not a finding.","false_positives":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-108811","V-99707"],"uuid":"B402CB4A-722B-1014-9487-EDCEB5507723","discussion":"This policy setting allows you to determine whether users can open, view, edit, or save Excel files with the format specified by the title of this policy setting. If you enable this policy setting, you can specify whether users can open, view, edit, or save files. The options that can be selected are below. Note: Not all options may be available for this policy setting.\n\n- Do not block: The file type will not be blocked.\n- Save blocked: Saving of the file type will be blocked.\n- Open/Save blocked, use open policy: Both opening and saving of the file type will be blocked. The file will open based on the policy setting configured in the \"default file block behavior\" key.\n- Block: Both opening and saving of the file type will be blocked, and the file will not open.\n- Open in Protected View: Both opening and saving of the file type will be blocked, and the option to edit the file type will not be enabled.\n- Allow editing and open in Protected View: Both opening and saving of the file type will be blocked, and the option to edit will be enabled. \n\nIf you disable or do not configure this policy setting, the file type will not be blocked.","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-04-01T11:55:55\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :   false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :     false (Excel 2 macrosheets and add-in files is set to Enabled:Open/Save blocked, use open policy.)\nResult Analysis :          Registry Name Not found in user profile ntuser.dat file(s): 'Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Office\\16.0\\excel\\security\\fileblock\\xl2macros'.  Existence requirement is 'all_exist' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n                :          For 'MAXHEALTH\\katessem.admin':  Registry Name Not found in user profile ntuser.dat file(s): 'Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Office\\16.0\\excel\\security\\fileblock\\xl2macros'.  \n                :          For 'MAXHEALTH\\katessem':  Registry Name Not found in user profile ntuser.dat file(s): 'Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Office\\16.0\\excel\\security\\fileblock\\xl2macros'.  \n                :          For 'MHL-PW06M2V2\\Administrator':  Registry Name Not found in user profile ntuser.dat file(s): 'Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Office\\16.0\\excel\\security\\fileblock\\xl2macros'.  \n"},{"security_override_guidance":"","group_title":"SRG-APP-000207","third_party_tools":"","rule_title":"Open/save of Excel 2 worksheets must be blocked.","rule_id":"SV-223317r961086","weight":"10.0","stig_uuid":"B3EF3B6E-722B-1014-942B-D54B65175630","ccis":["CCI-001662"],"ia_controls":"","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000207","id":"V-223317"},"group_id":"V-223317","mitigations":"","documentable":"false","fix_text":"Set the policy value for User Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Microsoft Excel 2016 &gt;&gt; Excel Options &gt;&gt; Security &gt;&gt; Trust Center &gt;&gt; File Block Settings \"Excel 2 worksheets\" to \"Enabled: Open/Save blocked, use open policy\".","rule_id_src":"SV-223317r961086_rule","status":"open","group_id_src":"V-223317","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.office365:def:223317","href":"U_MS_Office_365_ProPlus_V3R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV9-oval.xml"},"reference_identifier":"4099","classification":"Unclassified","potential_impacts":"","severity":"medium","responsibility":"","comments":null,"rule_version":"O365-EX-000008","check_content":"Verify the policy value for User Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Microsoft Excel 2016 &gt;&gt; Excel Options &gt;&gt; Security &gt;&gt; Trust Center &gt;&gt; File Block Settings \"Excel 2 worksheets\" is set to \"Enabled: Open/Save blocked, use open policy\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \n\nHKCU\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Office\\16.0\\excel\\security\\fileblock\n\nIf the value XL2Worksheets is REG_DWORD = 2, this is not a finding.","false_positives":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-108813","V-99709"],"uuid":"B402D096-722B-1014-BE6F-D1152EAFDF73","discussion":"This policy setting allows you to determine whether users can open, view, edit, or save Excel files with the format specified by the title of this policy setting. If you enable this policy setting, you can specify whether users can open, view, edit, or save files. The options that can be selected are below. Note: Not all options may be available for this policy setting.\n\n- Do not block: The file type will not be blocked.\n- Save blocked: Saving of the file type will be blocked.\n- Open/Save blocked, use open policy: Both opening and saving of the file type will be blocked. The file will open based on the policy setting configured in the \"default file block behavior\" key.\n- Block: Both opening and saving of the file type will be blocked, and the file will not open.\n- Open in Protected View: Both opening and saving of the file type will be blocked, and the option to edit the file type will not be enabled.\n- Allow editing and open in Protected View: Both opening and saving of the file type will be blocked, and the option to edit will be enabled. \n\nIf you disable or do not configure this policy setting, the file type will not be blocked.","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-04-01T11:55:55\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :   false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :     false (Open/save of Excel 2 worksheets is blocked.)\nResult Analysis :          Registry Name Not found in user profile ntuser.dat file(s): 'Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Office\\16.0\\excel\\security\\fileblock\\xl2worksheets'.  Existence requirement is 'all_exist' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n                :          For 'MAXHEALTH\\katessem.admin':  Registry Name Not found in user profile ntuser.dat file(s): 'Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Office\\16.0\\excel\\security\\fileblock\\xl2worksheets'.  \n                :          For 'MAXHEALTH\\katessem':  Registry Name Not found in user profile ntuser.dat file(s): 'Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Office\\16.0\\excel\\security\\fileblock\\xl2worksheets'.  \n                :          For 'MHL-PW06M2V2\\Administrator':  Registry Name Not found in user profile ntuser.dat file(s): 'Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Office\\16.0\\excel\\security\\fileblock\\xl2worksheets'.  \n"},{"security_override_guidance":"","group_title":"SRG-APP-000207","third_party_tools":"","rule_title":"Open/save of Excel 3 macrosheets and add-in files must be blocked.","rule_id":"SV-223318r961086","weight":"10.0","stig_uuid":"B3EF3B6E-722B-1014-942B-D54B65175630","ccis":["CCI-001662"],"ia_controls":"","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000207","id":"V-223318"},"group_id":"V-223318","mitigations":"","documentable":"false","fix_text":"Set the policy value for User Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Microsoft Excel 2016 &gt;&gt; Excel Options &gt;&gt; Security &gt;&gt; Trust Center &gt;&gt; File Block Settings \"Excel 3 macrosheets and add-in files\" to \"Enabled: Open/Save blocked,